content: I dont like the latest update. I've used the Asda app for years. I used to be able to click on individual items in previous orders and add them to my shop. Now you can't do that and if you try to add an entire previous trolley, it wipes what is currently in it! Each item you add now has to be searched for individually. More time consuming and not helpful anymore!

Sneaky asda, dont share offer ends dates, but worse prices change even after purchase - price should be secured once checked out! Makes shopping carefully to save money very difficult. App is very glitchy but has got better of late. You can't: add items from previous order easily, search your favourites for those on offer or add a reminder easily with correct date and time (it requires manual changes). Refine categories and search are poor too and way too many sponsored items!!!

Worst App...EVER!! It freezes every single time I use it, I've tried everything, but it just won't stop freezing & closing the app. What used to take 25 minutes to do a weeks grocery shop now takes TWO HOURS!!! Had enough of it, going to revert back to Tesco, at least they run a decent App Sort it out ASDA!!!

I would love this app to include a feature where we can permanently opt out of substitutes. Maybe in settings have Accept substitutes YES/NO. I find it very annoying when I order something and receive something else totally random so if it's not in stock just don't send anything rather than something I don't want. My example I ordered tuna in brine and received sardines in tomato sauce its not even close. Still no changes now going from 3 star to 1 star.

It's bloody awful. Sometimes the app freezes up. Sometimes the driver can't take a hint, even with clear instructions. Sometimes it logs out. Alot of times the app doesn't update well enough on where is the driver is at. Sometimes the refund doesnt work even when the products is returned. Also I have to re enter things when just making amends.

How this app was signed off by the QA testing team is beyond me. As many people are reporting for months, it constantly crashes (no exaggeration), it's painfully slow, and often becomes unresponsive. Surely their IT/devops teams use the app and are aware? Yet, no fix for months or no acknowledgement they are aware. I've temporarily switched to another online supermarket as ordering via the app is a chore of constantly needing to close and reopen after adding an item/performing a simple action.

Absolutely rubbish App.. been trying to check out for more than an hour with 2 different cards, and after you confirm it's you the Check Out blue button won't highlight at all. Tried to confirm with bank app, mobile nr and nothing. Useless and rubbish just like Brexit new crazy prices..!

Don't use this app if you actually want to receive your items. I ordered yesterday and when it arrived this morning half my stuff was missing. When I checked my receipt it was missing there too. To add insult to injury I had been charged for delivery because my order was too small and I was charged full price for items that were on offer because some of the items for the offer were missing. Customer service is useless.

It's terrible on tablet due to the fact that it doesn't load everything at once and you have to keep scrolling down to force it to load, such a stupid design. Just give us an option to load all on the page, and yes, I KNOW it's deliberately done to make us view the sponsored items, but all it does is make me not want them due to it.

The "I'm on my way" button is so often missing, so set off and arrive at the pickup point.I press "I'm here". That feature never,ever works! So very often,I have to sit for lengthy periods looking for a staff member.There's a phone number to call there, but at Accrington at least,that never works either. So, stuff picked by Asda in date is out of date by the time I get it! (Hyperbole, but you get the point!)

Will not accept card. Every week I have same issue. I've tried calling them, no help. I've tried uninstalling, reinstalling, restarting phone, signing in and out. Nothing works but then a few hours later it works! Each time I try to pay it asks me to approve in bank app. I do that and it says card failed. Worst app EVER!!!!!!

The app is constantly, and I mean constantly, either shutting down on me, extremely slow, app opens up on wrong page, or locks my phone. Its so buggy, and yes I have the updated version. Just an awful experience. (Update) app had been updated again, and its still extremely bad. I'll be lucky if I can get 3 items in the cart, before it shuts down. It's also actually so bad that it even crashes when trying to submit feedback, and fails. Laughable. I'm pulling my hair out.

there needs to be an option to delete previous addresses. my address has reverted back to my old address, and I lost my shopping! asda said there was nothing they could do about the shopping,or about the preference to address!! how ridiculous asda! sort it out,as again,Iv just had a similar problem,and had to cancel my shopping, because the address keeps reverting back to my old address!!

Since the update, one minute I can sign into the app no problem, try to sign into the rewards app, says my accounts locked and change my password, do that and I can log into the rewards app but not this one. Get the systems sorted.

UNHAPPY:VERY creepy privacy policy repeatedly pops up & resets each time.all denied permissions switched back on! logs you out & forces repeated login. attempts to infiltrare & hijack your personal data & get concent to scan your device ID & location to share with COUNTLESS DODGY CORPORATIONS.use to be good. TOO MANY UPDATES.Not user-friendly.Should be able to pin shopping list to top so quick & easy to see esp if dyslexic as visually busy.forced adds & sections given priority over practical use

Please sort this app out, it is continuously crashing whilst I'm trying to book a delivery. I thought it might have been due to high demand, but it's been going on for months now, and at different days and times, please fix this issue.

Over that last year/ish. This app is getting from bad to worse. When are sanitary products in the same category as carrots? 4 November Can't cancel orders, through the app now. Why can you just read the reviews on random days? Why on some days you can't see the product reviews and on other days you can? AND When shopping you can't sort the items from high price to low price etc? Asda is going to the pots!
This app is so poorly optimised. I can't do anything, constant errors, slow, crashes, hard to checkout after booking slot. I give up and just use the website

Rubbish. Has pointless sort options. They refuse to listen to customer feedback. Substitute suggestions are woeful. Order tracking isn't great. Same-day delivery is confusing. Searches bring forth a multitude of unrequested items. Pages take an age to load. Use your browser to create a link on your homepage instead of downloading this. Sadly, I still think they're one of (if not THE) the cheapest online supermarket's; otherwise they'd be binned in a heartbeat.

I have had to uninstall the app to be able to pay for my shopping. When I try to log in on the web with the app installed it insists you use the app. Trying to pay for my shopping with a Nationwide card in the app it rejects my card. I suspect the app doesn't work with Nationwide's identity check stuff. I have to pay by using the Asda website.

At almost 80, and housebound, I rely on delivery services. Asda were never the best, but they seemed for a while to be the least bad. But I'm now sick to death of half deliveries, constant excuses - and, most of all, being fobbed off with short-dated stuff that ought to be half price. Just delivered of a week's worth of bake at home bread - with just a day to bake and eat it. I'm done with these profiteers. I'm desperate - I hope I'm never THAT desperate again. Byeee....
I haven't been able to use this app for sometime now. I have deleted it and reinstalled. All I get is sorry, there has been a problem loading this page message when I open it up. So I can't use it
I can't use ASDA rewards because it's rubbish every time I log in it rejects my information and kicks me out, I have to log in again and again, I'm finished, it's a complete waste of time.
Absolutely shocking app tried ordering 15 times since yesterday and everytime been kicked off! If I could give zero stars I would I'll happily change the rating when I'm able to complete my order!
Shockingly slow and keeps crashing. Could do the shopping in a quarter of the time in store.
Awful. All important items in my order out of stock. Pointless delivery as still now need to go to the shops to actually make a full meal. Know your stock levels and do better.
this app is terrible. constant crashes and a significant drain on my battery. it takes me nearly an hour to do a simple shop on this app due to ot crashing constantly. please fix it üôà
Still incredibly glitchy and slow, still freezes all the time, when is someone going to fix this or get new developers? Practically unusable.
Charged for unavailable items. Tried Click and Collect, however 3 items were missing. And there was no way I could reach out for a refund despite they said "you have not been charged".
Really poor experience. Logs me out all the time. Can't see reviews... if I click on them it just asks me to leave a review instead of showing them. Constantly freezing also
All I get is the error...Sorry there has been an issue loading this page. Have attempted to reinstall and with and without WiFi but still no luck
Less contenient than using the website. The fact that it requires a login every time and won't remember login details is useless.
Now, I have to approve payment to Asda through my online banking app. I do this then on returning to the Asda app, I find myself unable to confirm the order.

Waited over 4 hours last night for a delivery which did not appear. No calls or messages just left hanging! Had to reorder manually as system still states its out for delivery. Very poor customer service, this is the 2nd time in a matter of months this has happened! unreliable recently!

Horrible service. My first order was not delivered. Before few minutes of the delivery the app updated that the driver was few blocks away and then after an hour the app showed there was a problem with the order and contact Asda if needed. Next day I called Asda and got to know about order cancellation! The annoying thing here is the customer service does not provide any reason for cancellation and they informed that delivery can't be rescheduled! My LAST try with ASDA's sloppy service.

App is very slow and constantly freezes. It doesn't allow you to sort items by price/any other category even when you select it, unless you specifically type an item into he search bar. Deleting the app and updating it makes no difference. The app is not very good.

App is slow and frustrating! Once you finally get to the Isle you want, it doesn't allow you to sort low to high. When searching it brings up completely irrelevant items. Not only that, it constantly brings up items that Asda are trying to flog. This app used to be good now Asda are just trying to fleece everyone. I changed to Aldi due to Asdas poor fresh food section and the prices (per item) are much cheaper. Essential range is yellow so everyone knows you're a povvo!! Shame on you Asda.

Absolutely outrageous. The first time I ordered from them everything was delivered on time. On my second order there were no updates on the app and I never received my order. Had two call Asda twice they accepted the order was never delivered but I am still waiting for a refund. Shame on you Asda. Never making the mistake of using this App !
Uber driver canceled my order again as he could not understand the directions to my house , asda did nothing to help with this. Absolutely rubbish customer service.
last few weeks the app has been shocking.it took me 2 hours to do my shopping as it kept freezing then closing down..I updated the app today and its just as bad!
Wouldn't refund rotten food. Food was unopened and in fridge the whole time, went rotten within the best before date, full of mould. Requested refunded, which was reviewed and denied. Not acceptable.

This app: ‚Ä¢crashes after adding one or two items ‚Ä¢sets up reminders at the current time, not at the time of delivery ‚Ä¢adds sponsored products at the top of the list after a delay so (for example) instead of clicking on butter, you get a premium brand peanut butter. It usually crashes as you're undoing the action
For two or three months I've been stuck on 'sorry there's been an issue loading the page' on every page/search
Absolute bilge of an app in EVERY way. Worst app & search engine in 30 years (apart from even worse DIRE Amazon). Abysmal rubbish!

This app is rubbish, I've tried so many times to use a voucher code I've been offered for Easter, but every time, I would receive the same message: Failed to apply voucher. I even called customer service, and they said that it's a technical problem and they can not help me right away, so I have to wait for someone to get in touch with me from a different department. Guess what...,? Nobody contacted me. What a scam. Didn't expect this level of service from Asda.

Absolutely rubbish app & customer service! Can NOT check out due to multiple problems with the app & online website. Every card I tried to use is declined. Phone customer service is useless. What a joke of a company.... Most definitely will delete my account and do my shopping somewhere else. By the way I use to spend over 300¬£/month at Asda. Nope... Not anymore.... Enough is enough. Zero stars!

Product's have become terrible since Walmart sold out. Far too many items unavailable in favourites list and to make it worse, deliveries arrive with too many product's not available after confirmed in basket at check out. Time to go to Tesco!

App is fine delivery drivers not. Need to put a tracker on the drivers so we can see where they are on the road. Mine was 3 hrs late then cancelled so I ordered the next day again 3 hrs late called them up they can't get through to my local store and they can't do anything else which is fair enough, it's my local drivers and store issue.

Latest update has new issues. Cramming 4 products onto each line of the search results now means that you can't read the description for any of them! Do you actually get any app users to beta test your updates?
The grocery delivery is fine, but the app keeps crashing on my phone running android 12, Samsung galaxy s22 ultra. Edit: still the same frequent crashes after 2 months. The iOS app is so much better.

Yous want to get it together the app is atrocious constantly loading miss putting things into basket so have to go over shop several times No wonder a end up missing my delivery slots with the amount of problems with app What a proper joke I want to order my shop but you are on the app more than the time you actually want to spend on it which can become frustrating after time that you end up shopping with another retailer because the site doesn't function properly or in a timely fashion.
multiple times required to approve orders via bank, app stalls and does not update very temperamental...have used Tesco's in desperation multiple times
The dreadful app is slow unresponsive and full of advertising
keep receiving texts saying shopping will be late and giving another time slot but then delivering early when no one is there!
Filters and sorting in the app haven't worked in years. Fix it.
They have taken my money and not delivered my order twice now it is an absolute joke takes two weeks for a refund. Only get this app if you want them to steal your money for two weeks.

Stuff missing off order yet I know for a fact I ordered them, making me think I've lost my mind! üò° I know for a fact I added them, it's crazy ü§Ø Been good for a while, but now wont put items in low-high order when clicked on! üò° Won't sort brands either Is this app having a laugh! Seriously sort this app out!

Terrible app, sort function not working,prices fluctuate,out of stock items,terrible substitutes,slow scroll loading, i would give it 0 stars if i could. App develepers dont listen to feedback worst of all so none of these issues get fixed. Is there a way to report this as it seems like a scam is happening or something

Just don't EVER expect to get what you ordered and when you have a problem, the customer service is Diabolical to NON-EXISTENT and mostly in India. I have nothing against foreign people but they are unlikely to know much about things in our country. INCLUDING THE ENGLISH LANGUAGE. FOR THE WORST ONLINE SHOPPING EXPERIENCE ON EARTH, PLACE YOUR ORDER HERE. THIS WILL BE MY LAST ORDER AND THE ONLY REASON FOR IT IS THAT I HAVE ¬£10 WORTH OF VOUCHERS THAT NEED USING.

When clicking the button to amend an order, it takes you back to the previous page. If you do manage to get on to amend order page, the search bar disappears so you need to manually scroll through all the products to find what you want. Then 9/10 times, there will be a massive list of items unavailable. Yet when I physically go to the store (which this order is packed in,) they are there. Very disappointing.

This app is incredibly intermittent. Bug infestation I suppose! It freezes a lot. Doesn't let me access my orders. When using the search bar it's 50/50 whether it shows me the new results or my last search. It's a huge source of stress and irritation in my every day life. Thank goodness I'm not reliant on this app and I can use the website on my computer. Although that's also difficult to move.

Previous versions of this app where not too bad, but the recent updates are awful particularly with favourite items. Wish they group items together better, for example all the frozen stuff together... When you select a product to view more information and then go back to favourite list it takes you back to the beginning of my 458 item list! And you used to have a drop down menu to go to items from a department. That is no longer there. Shame as I used to use this app for deliveries once or twice a week.

This used to be a great app but recently the problems and glitching have become frequent. It's at the point now where it is forever asking me to sign-in and when I do it just resets and asks again and again... And again. It's ridiculous now and no option to send feedback or contact. The latest update hasn't fixed any bugs but has amplified them and just for good measure have thrown in some more! Thanks!

The app is very slow constantly crashes and doesn't laod my orders which makes it very difficult to make amendments. It also signs me out all the time and when I try to log back in it just keeps taking me back to the sign in page. It takes several tries before I can get back in. I have tried uninstalling and reinstalling several times but it doesn't make a difference. Very disappointing.....

Favourites not working any more. Take a leaf out of the Tesco app which works like a charm and has more features. Oh and while you're fixing it, can you not go right back to the start of your favourites list every time you search for alternative products. Those of us with big favourite lists end up having to scroll all the way back to where we were. Use a 'back to start' button instead. Thanks.

This used to be a good app that worked well but recently (Feb 2021) it's turned into an awful mess that makes online shopping a real nightmare. The search function is broken, everything is reported as out of stock even when it's in your basket, the shop by department often freezes and hangs forcing you to quit the app and restart... I could go on but I don't have enough characters left! Needs a really good sort out to get even the basics working.

The app used to be great, but recently it's become nearly impossible to use. The search option very rarely works properly, the favourites lists often get stuck on the first page so I have to look for every item separately, if I add delivery instructions I can't confirm my order, and the substitutes page pings back to the top of the page every time I select an item. PLEASE sort it out!

Terrible app. It doesn't work. Yes, I can do a click and collect shop and then check out(eventually) if I then try to amend my order it simple won't check out. Either it wants more contact info(it's already there) or it simply freezes. The web version isn't much better. Maybe it's time to start shopping elsewhere. Life is to short to waste on this rubbish app. Do yourself a favour and don't bother. Love Asda but it's fine to switch.

Wow, this app is more of a mess than usual. It's always been full of bugs, and seems to go through phases where I have to constantly restart it, or have to sign in over and over again, but lately it's decided not to show me all the products available when I search. Like if you search for something, half the options disappear before you can click on them. Sometimes you can find them in another menu like "favourites," but you have to get lucky. What a stupid bug. Makes it harder than ever to use.

Terrible app and terrible service . The app constantly crashes and freezes . Even at the best of times the app struggles but it seems to especially struggle late at night or early in the morning . I have never been able to view my order in the morning , the app just freezes on a loading screen . I've tried reinstalling the app several times and it's even made my phone freeze , it's just a buggy and poorly made app . Plus it has to be the worst app for saying something is in stock when it isn't .

Bug fixes and performance enhancement? More like bug creation and performance deterioration. Each alleged upgrade over the past few years has worsened the app. I have to reload the app several times before it will actually add any items to my trolley and continue to reload it multiple times during the course of the shopping experience. Items say available on 1 screen and not available on another. Sometimes the add button works and sometimes it doesn't. It is ridiculous.

The app used to be full of bugs but was useable. After the latest update, it's downright useless. For example, you can scroll through your favourites because it keeps crashing to begin with and then it just stops as if your favourites didn't exist. We live in the 21st century and it's embarrassing for a huge business like Asda to have such an awful app. If you want to keep your customers, fix the app!

An extremely broken app. Searching for "Meal Deal" crashes the app, the search box diappears out the left of the screen so the first few letters you type in aren't visible, the app sometime refuses to do any more searches until you restart it and sometimes there is no indication that something is out of stock until you try to add it to your basket and either a generic error appears or nothing happens. Also every checkbox on the substitutions list returns you to the top of the list immediately.

App getting steadily worse: hangs when adding items to trolley (or just randomly); only one order shows up on home screen; "on my way" button doesn't appear. Having to resort to using the website rather than app to shop the last couple of weeks. Please sort!! 02/04/21 Just when you think it can't any worse, most of my favourites now seem to have disappeared - can only see about a quarter of them - won't scroll any further or keeps jumping back to start. This is happening on phone and tablet.

The worst app I have ever come across. I have spent an hour trying to log in but just get a blank ok message and then can't do anything. I have tried numerous accounts and devices. It just continually crashes meaning you have to uninstall and reinstall it multiple times and then that doesn't work either. How is this possible in 2021. Have had enough.

This app was fine to start with, but the more I've used it, the more I've realised how truly rubbish it is. It cannot cope with search results that are filtered down by more than ONE category! Also, I've placed an order for click and collect but for some reason the app is showing a different date to the one on the confirmation email. I've got the same issue for a delivery that I've placed for another date. Once again Asda, you've proved how truly incompetent you are!

Have been using this for years and it's very temperamental especially after updates. I'm now getting fed up and considering using a different supermarket since the last update. - Items constantly showing as out of stock when they are actually in stock inside the store. - Items which are available in store do not even show up on the app. - New glitch with the search function, the top one or two search results disappear immediately after they appear and cannot be found again.

Hard to see how this app could get any worse but judging by my experience of the past few updates I'm sure that they'll come up with something! Right now my favourites list is like a game of lucky dip, I spend longer trying to sort out an order than I do putting it away, cooking it, eating it and clearing up combined and I have to uninstall then re install it every time I want to check it amend my order. I've also had regular delivery slots disappear, and then reappear leading to a double order

The app used to be annoying before, but I could deal with it. Lately, it's nothing but buggy. I have to go out of the confirmation screen a few times before it actually lets me confirm my order amends. And whenever I try to put in my substitute options - if I want them or not - it always sends me to the top of the list every single time I check or uncheck something. Half my favourite list won't load. And it keeps taking me back to the top of the page, even when I'm not touching it. Fix this!

The latest version 22.20 sucks bigtime! The previous version was intuitive and flexible. That's GONE! This was not just about fixing bugs, it was a complete redesign. Shopping is more restrictive and suggested alternatives are now completely irrelevant. How is that helpful? Please, is it possible to roll back the update to the previous version??! I used to consider the ASDA Groceries app to be the best and most easy to use but not any more. It's now just another in a myriad of the mundane.

This app is so glitchy it is barely useable. Quite often I am unable to check out and am forced to abandon the app and use a Web browser. It doesn't recognise the 2 factor authentication no matter which one I choose. Also you cannot leave items in your basket if they are unavailable the day you make the order. I would prefer to chance they might be there on the day of delivery. So each time you amend you have to remove all unavailable items. The whole app crashes often. Very frustrating!

Used to be fine. The app itself is OK, particularly since the last big update (though it doesn't make it clear when you amend an order what has gone out of stock, just shows you an item with zero context or explanation, and you can only search some items by finding them on a browser and telling it to open the link on the app), but the last few deliveries have been useless in terms of ridiculous substitutions and poor stock levels. To the extent it's time to change supermarkets... again
Crashing constantly. It's very slow when it does work. Either freezes or kicks me off app continuously. Its so frustrating. I've gone to Sainsburys app to shop instead.

What have you done!! This worked perfectly before the update. Now it won't load my orders unless uninstall and reinstall the app. It amend order just keeps going back to the previous page. The categorys have gone on the items I have put on the basket so just on on all jumbled up then when scrolling down it reorderes itself. It constantly crashes all the time. I've used this app for years and this is the worst its been. Its awful. I've had to install it and reinstall it at least 8 times in 2 days

I had to write a review to advise that this app has turned to absolute garbage in the last couple of weeks. Consistent errors and freezing, I'm constantly having to reset in the middle of making an order and it's now literally impossible to amend any orders. It's almost completely unusable, to the point I've just downloaded the sainsbury's app, because I cannot stand the frustration any longer.

This app continues to be total junk. Several updates and still random issues occur, scrolling favourites before being put back to the top of the list. Search doesn't work, back button gives random results. App crashes, loses items from the basket. Often payment screens don't load, I could go on for hours! Getting impossible to use, really thinking about changing retailer.

Used to be decent, but the latest update has messed up the ability to amend orders already placed. If availability of any products has changed it gives you the option to go back and change the delivery slot, or "continue". The 2nd option puts you back to the first page and you're then in a infinite loop unable to amend! So frustrating! Please sort it out... Edited to add - can't even log in now.

Terrible app. Full of bugs and getting worse over time. (Website is not much better.) Trying to do a weekly online shop is a painful, frustrating, infuriating experience. (Been using for over a year and only stick with it due to lower cost compared to others.) Favourites randomly disappear from favourites list, items added to basket don't show up as such in lists, items shown as in stock suddenly say they're not when you try to add them or check out, search often doesn't work...

It use to be so smooth to use all be it a bit dated. I would use the basket as a shopping list and remove as I shopped. But then someone had the bright idea to try and 'improve' it and they ruined it. Department view doesnt work anymore. Which was really helpful when shopping as asda like to put things in random places. It will often not let me search and I have to keep closing the app. Why try and fix something that isnt broken? It's so frustrating to use these days. It use to be so simple.
Worst app ever crashes and freezes every 30 seconds, impossible to do a shop

Uses to be great, but now a frustrating app. I frequently have to give up and go and boot up the laptop, kind of defeats the object of having a mobile app. Poor experience. Update: Reduced my rating from 2 to 1. This App is complete shite. Can't even amend an existing order, asks if I want to add the items in my trolley to the existing order and then just reverts back to the start screen... Awful.

The latest update has broken the search feature. You type in your search criteria, the suggested (initial short results) appear but when you press GO, nothing happens so you cannot see the entire results of your search. The app is also slower to respond now. You click add to add an item and it takes about 2 seconds before the spinner comes and a further second for it to add to your basket. Very poor update
Like others have stated, terrible app. Freezes and crashes constantly. Even worse with the newest update. UX might be the worst on the playstore.

Bad UI and unstable. The lazy loading is a nightmare, takes forever to browse a category. Performance generally is glacial. Functionality is often broken, e.g. asks if you want to add basket when amending order, then doesn't do it, or showing just a few items when using "view all" in a category. Constantly needs to be closed and reopened every time something goes wrong, or else it just stops working completely.
didn't email me to tell me it could not process my order after I approved the transaction on my bank app so lost my delivery slot.

The app is better but asda has gone terrible not only do u get lots of substitutes but the quality isnt as good and products are out of date. Its easy to ask for refund however they dont always give you it, which they did last time when i received out of date products. The time before i had 8 subs and 5 not available i complained and got voucher that didn't work and ive had no reply. So im done, im not spending with them anymore they've gone down hill like many other companies.

I have numerous problems with this app since Summer 2020, it seems to have been changed so that actions you could do before, no longer work the same way, and are FAR less intuitive. Recently, the app has been unable to retrieve shopping lists, and tells you there is an error, try later; it also fails to retrieve previous orders. To satisfy myself that it wasn't a problem with me or my tablet, I uninstalled and reinstalled it. Now I can't log in with my existing account details. Not very useful!

Full of bugs and now unusable. Search button randomly disappears... substitution page jumps back to the top after any box is ticked...and then if you do happen to make it as far as the payment page, you find that the confirm order button is disabled. Apps are supposed to enhance web functionality - all this one now does is make the shopping experience more frustrating and stressful. Please stop messing with something that didn't need fixing and roll back the changes immediately!

This app is guaranteed to give you high blood pressure. Just some of the highlights of the last year: Throws you out every time add an item to the basket. Half my favourites have been deleted. The option to request a refund was removed. The back button doesn't go back, it goes back to the home screen EVERY TIME. Couldn't add a new payment card. I will be using Tesco from now on, their app just WORKS.

I spent ¬£108 in shopping yesterday, a very long time to order. In they morning, I received an email stating that some of the items ordered were out of stock. When I tried to eliminate them on the app, there wasn't an option for it. They make it so difficult to eliminate the items THEY WANT TO SUBSTITUTE even though it has an "amend" option, but they make it so difficult to JUST SIMPLY eliminate the substitutes that "were out of stock". It was a very unpleasant experience, so I had to cancel it.

Sadly yet another major supermarket who wishes to charge extorniate prices for produce that literally goes out of date with 2 days of it being delivered. Time staff were trained to pick better dates as we pay a fee for the picking of it, or stop using bots like at ocado. Shameful and total waste of money for such poor quality food
CAN YOU STOP DOING BANK PAYMENT CONFIRMATIONS EVERY SINGLE TIME! I've shopped with you every week for over two years, it's ridiculous and frustrating

replyContent:
Hi Norman, thank you for your patience. We just released a Beta that fixes the reviews issue: https://play.google.com/apps/testing/com.asda.android
This fix will also be in our normal release to Google Play within the next two weeks. The ability to pick the items from the order to reorder will be in the following release (at the end of April).

No back button. If I search for something then look at something from that search I cannot go back to the search results, I have to start the search again.
Poor. Regularly logs me out. Frustratingly hard to use. Not noticeably better after two years of use.

I can't walk far enough to do a full shop so, for now, I'm trying the click and collect. This is my third week and so far, so good.

A good app for doing your online shop, BUT it's Very Sloowww to use, at least 5 seconds for every page to load! Also very prone to crashing and freezing at random times. Infuriating when you're trying to do your weekly shop in a hurry. Speed the app up and optimise the code and I would give 5 stars.

The app is generally easy to use but throws wobblies every few weeks, sometimes freezing whilst adding more than one of an item to the basket, sometimes suddenly deleting or doubling the basket contents, sometimes saying everything in the basket is "free" (nice!). There are often irritating messages when opening a saved basket for amendment which simply list an item or items in the basket without any explanation (I've found this can mean unavailability or a price change or nothing I can see).

The app has changed its soo slow and keeps crashing, this need to be sorted. It does have some good features on how it keeps your regular buys which makes it easier to add to your shop. Easy to use and navigate.
What has happened to this app over the last few week. CONSTANTLY freezing and closing itself down. Takes twice as long to complete and order now.
easy to order and staff are lovely at the collection point. unfortunately they never seem to have the stock. Every time same story. very frustrating üòï

used to be ok but now continuous problems with payments.Today order was cancelled for a delivery in 2 days time because payment couldn't be taken,but why take payment this early,there are no payment issues with my card! had a lot of problems with my previous account which ended up cancelling & creating another as orders just weren't turning up & your customer service was shocking, the team are looking into it but 6 weeks later nothing.Too many issues to keep using if this problem persists
Not much cheaper anymore and the quality of fruit and veg is really bad and never lasts. I will be changing supermarket
very friendly drivers. half the time its missing items, or close to end by date food. if the prices continue to rise, I will be shopping else where or limit what I do by from asda
The app is okay but does have some inadequacies I think they could improve on. Ive made my thoughts known to Asda but it falls on deaf ears - as usual with Asda.
favourite menu saves everything you buy as a favourite. Need to stop this as favourites is full of random stuff
Great app and convenient but I can't amend an order I have to use a desktop or ipad which is very annoying

All is ok on the app apart from the fact you can't order items in price order when looking through the actual sections of food I.E clicking in cupboard foods, then to multipack crisps then filter then arranging them in price order upon clicking on price order nothing actually happens

I like to use this app because it makes shopping much easier when you buy a lot and have no car. Unfortunately, it is really frustrating when you try to add items to your basket and it says that it isn't available even when it isn't labelled as sold out. Another really frustrating thing... when you finally successfully finish your shopping and want to pay.... suddenly it shows you that half of the items you tried to order is no longer available.You need to figure out a better way to manage this

Been using this app for about 1 year. These problems have always been there. If you're inactive for a couple of mins, the next page you want to go to will not load. Need to close app and reopen. Click on an item from favourites and go 'back', you'll go back to beginning of the list, not where you left off. Book a delivery slot, need to close and reopen the app for it to accept the slot. Will keep asking you to book otherwise. would be great if the last 2 would be fixed

After the recent updates the app has stopped displaying items in the Shop - Special Offers - the bottom 6 categories such as Easter, Ramadan, Big Night In etc.. The ability to change settings for alternative products are the after check out, not easy to go back to. The good thing about the app is that the basket is categories in 'departments'/categories. I find it so helpful

You have to go to the home page each time you want to search something which is annoying and often it won't search. It doesn't register in the quantity section when you have added to trolley. I've found to fix checkout issues close down all your tabs and open apps on your phone and start again. It's just about usable, could be and should be better.

A few things missing. When I go into an item I don't want to be taken back to the top of the menu. Far too many sub menus I will only go from the favourite list and would prefer to go from the frequently bought list which is an option on the website. I just use this to get enough stuff for a basic order and will amend later on the website.
continued more missing items... the price of goods continued going up every couple of weeks... Disgusted with the Profiteering

Decent app, but there's a major bug. If your contact details aren't complete (fort instance, you haven't set your title as Mr, Mrs etc) it prompts you to complete them whenever you try to complete your order. This version of the window is completely broken and won't let you confirm so you can't check out. I had to go to the account page to set my details before it let me complete my order.

If something isn't available, mark it on the app!!! As I've seen it's not only my problem that for the last 6 weeks there are many items unavailable and the substitutes(if there are any...) are completely rubbish! As much as I like the app, and I've been using it for years, the reliability of asda service is unacceptable lately. I'm seriously considering going back to Tesco...

Good but used to be better. The app used to group products of the same type, eg meat, together in your basket which made it easy to see what you were ordering. It doesn't group product types now until after you've confirmed your order and this makes it more difficult to make sure youve added everything you want and means I have to amend my order numerous times. Would be good if I was changed to be like that again But other than that the app is good and I use it for all my grocery shopping.

The app is terrible, but not 1 star terrible. The shopping/paying part is actually quite good. Categorised or able to search with no issues. If items get subbed you either get reduced price or better items at no extra cost. It does sign me out often or buffers constantly so I can't see my orders and the pick up button isn't always there when collecting. Other than that it does the job.
online app is a nightmare. Other ways to shop asdas online no better .Always same old things out of stock.
asdas home shopping range is getting less and less on choices .

Although the app has improved from the disastrous update in March, it still has major issues. Font is so small it's inaccessible in places, huge adverts in the way, favourites missing, items marked as both in and out of stock in different views, took away option to set no substitutes as a default, and often the checkout tab doesn'teven work. Come on Asda, you took a great app and "improved" it so it's unusable half the time.

Almost never my order has been delivered when I wanted. I'm not talking about a seconds or a minutes, but dozens of minutes, at least. And, the second problem, substitutes. It's OK, if you have a time to change your order. But, if you have a message about the substitute two hours before the delivery time, you can change nothing. The third time is availability of certain items. You have seen them at a store one hour ago, actually a huge pile of them, but in the app it's not available.
App is easy to use, but it is constantly shutting down/freezing.

Very frustrating at the moment. Besides not being able to read the reviews as other people have mentioned, when I go to book a slot sometimes they are all crossed out because it has allowed me to add products that are out of stock but I have no idea which ones as it doesn't say! Also the recipes I have saved as favourites will not load.....previously I have had no issues, I'm hoping these will be fixed soon

Probably OK for actually ordering stuff (I generally do it from my PC though). The 'check in' functionality is pretty rubbish from my (limited) experience. Every time I check in to say I'm on my way, the app crashes. I had to use the kiosk at the store to collect my order. [edit]I tried using the check-in feature again in August 2019 and it actually worked for the first time, so have added another star.
Errors when trying to pay... Every. Single. Time!

As I've seen in prev reviews, the favourites is quite annoying if u open am item for details or by accident as it returns you to the beginning of the favourites list. It's ok but sorting by price doest work. And it's so annoying takes forever to have to scroll through everything to find a reasonable product.
Useful app easy to use and navigate, but seriously what is the point of the refine option as it doesn't refine anything.

They sorted out many of the previous issues, I don't have an issue with the app being slow. What is driving me nuts is deleting items without you knowing. Then I get an order with items I'm expecting missing. Missing items are when there has been a packaging change - doesn't tell you just deletes it, doesn't suggest new items. Today just deleted water and no AJ from an old order. Very random, very annoying. No easy way to feedback to you the problems so here's a review to tell you.

There are always things missing and the substitutes don't always make sense. Last time I ticked no substitutions and I got the wrong item anyway, except there was no warning and I only noticed when putting it away. My refund request was rejected in a matter of seconds, I doubt anyone looked into it. Really unreliable, too many times I had to go out shopping after anyway. I don't think I'll use it again.

Why are you forced to remove out of stock items each time I checkout an amendment to an order? The items might not be out of stock on the actual picking/delivery day, so why would I want to remove the items from my order potentially several days before? Surely it would be better to just leave the items on the order. Also, when choosing a delivery slot you can't scroll left/right without going to the top of the time slots. Not ideal if you are just looking for a free evening slot.

Good app, when it works. The basics are often out of stock and half of your order is often substituted so you end up with groceries totally different to your initial list. Options are also very limited - esp in World Foods, so unless you're ordering every day items, you're better off going in store. I never order fresh produce either, they choose the stuff right near expiry date - last time I received a bag of rotten potatoes, and bread due to expire in 2 days. I won't even go near their fruit.

Glad to see ongoing glitches that were present for months have been sorted out. However, now there's another problem/inconvenience. Why has the feature to de-select automatic substitutes on all products in basket disappeared from online and app? It is highly frustrating to have to untick every item in my list individually as I normally untick everything and prefer to choose the items I want subs for!!! I've increased my rating accordingly, but sincerely hope this feature will be reinstated soon.

After the last 2 updates the app removes items from the favourite list, I go and find the missing items and reselect as favourite but as soon as app closes it removes them. I believe it might have something to do with the ads that have been put in each favourite section. If I wanted the ads items I'd select them, I don't need prompted into buying a more expensive version of what's in my favourite list. It's favourite because I'm happy with what I've ordered. Fix favourite list and I'll rate 5*

Generally a good app but a few issues. Once the basket contains over ¬£100 of shopping you can't get at the search button any more! Annoying that you can't put things in your basket as you think of them, it won't let you unless you've already booked a slot. Shopping lists are very useful.

The app has a lot of useful features including scan function and it remembers previous searches well. all parts of the app run fast enough except order history which takes literally 30-45 seconds to load every time! The quality of Asda produce is well below other supermarkets and often arrives so damaged and sad that I request refunds almost weekly , but the app should really let you give details/pictures on nature of the issue as otherwise there's no way specific problems can be addressed
Payment option sometimes does not work in the app and I have to go to the website.

Very frustrating. Delivery/ collection dates have two days of 'tomorrow' with different dates and also chronological order of dates does not exist! I got this app so I didn't have to use my laptop, but that is where I have to double check everything. This bug has returned after the most recent update! Please fix ASAP !!

Apps fine but just essentials don't show up in their own category, when you click on it nothing comes up, Sometimes they just cancel your order on the day and sometimes the app glitches when you swipe down the list of items to fast, Otherwise it's fine does the job.

The feature that tracks your location and automatically lets the store know you're there doesn't actually work... was frustrating to see people who got there after me get served 1st because I trusted it. Other than that it's a pretty good app, a lot easier than shopping in store

love the convenience. sometimes the substitutes can be off putting or a bonus, the problem I do have is if you order meat, fruit, potatoes etc you just get the first pack/ bag that they pick up, which when you get them home, sometimes they are not what I would have chosen. refunds are quite quick.
could be vastly improved, but it does the job
Slow, very slow. Lots of other issues.

I've been using this app for over a year and its been excellent! Now since the update recently its diabolical,!! Good app but all too often when clicking to amend an order, and then selecting add basket to my order, it does the opposite and deletes all of the items in my my basket. What's happened? This used to be a good app and after recent updates it's awful. App now keeps freezing and logging me out while trying to make an order. It's also slow. This used to be a fabulous app but now it's become frustrating. I really liked this app as I don't drive and it sometimes it helped with doing a bigger shop that I would find hard to carry home on my own. Asda is the best priced supermarket for the products I need, however the app is mostly bad. I can cope with slow apps but an app that doesn't provide 30% of what it should do may certainly mean that I have to swap to another delivery supermarket.

It's great I've been using it for years, it's simple to use with all the information that you want to see for allergy sufferers e.g. is there. Uninstalled the app as every time I went to use it, it asked me to log in with my email and password (time consuming on a mobile phone). Useful app for an everyday shopping. It would be absolutely a game changer if I could use it also to shop in store and it would work the same way as scan and go. Ability of custom shopping list, scanning directly with phone would help to be more organized.

Generally great and easy to use. The biggest flaw is that if you use the "back" button it doesnt aways take you back to where you were in the previous list. App is ok but could be better. If items are unavailable "see alternative" sometimes comes up with nothing. Its OK but not great. Often I search items and they are out of stock, but once I hit checkout then items are suddenly there in the suggested item to add to my bag. This doesn't sound like such a problem until you realise what this means, when they oversell items (which they always do) they will obviously switch the peoples orders who have substitutions allowed first, so you will lose out of getting your items and are sent stuff you don't want without being told and refunds take days!

It works but the search is awful. So if you search "Ellas kitchen carrot" you just get lots of results and you have to keep repeating the search to find the one that you want.

A lot of items have disappeared from the app, which i know are in the store because on occasion I've had to go in store expecially to get them. This is very frustrating. I've used the app and click and collect for years and this has only been a problem in the last 6 months or so.

Not very good when two people are editing the same basket at the same time. We have to take it in turns to add something. It's almost like the app locks the database for a short period of time while adding or removing something, but the period of time is many seconds.

I've been trying all day to do my weekly food order and basically the app is saying there's no stock available in all the department's. I have uninstalled and reinstalled the app but still having the same problems !!!! Getting frustrated now because I have been using Asda app for years and never experienced a problem until now

In general, it's an ok app but could be loads better. Something that does bug me with favourites though is when you click on an item and goes back it goes all the way back to the first item so you have to scroll all the way back down. Please sort this.

(Amended after previous bank validation was fixed.) It's ok, the search bugs out every now and again so you end up constantly backing out to the homepage to make it work. Also I searched the word "picnic" and it tried to force me to open a browser... not sure why

This app gets really annoying when you got to keep putting in your email and password each time! You add things to the basket then they are out of stock. After you complete your order, the items you couldn't get before are suddenly back in stock......

Updated and made worse. New update has categorised favourites into various different groups which is very annoying as you keep having to select "frequently purchased" to stop seeing favourites in the order Asda decide to automatically present to you. I don't want to see "ice cream parlour' up first. The idea of a supermarket shopping app is to make the buying experience quicker not longer and more labour intensive.

I can't see comments in the app for all the products. Everything else is fine but if I want to read what's bad or good about a product I have to open the website in the browser, which is super annoying. I'm uninstalling and reinstalling the app..hope it'll fix the errors.

Why has the app changed layout, you add stuff to basket then add from previous order and you lose it all? When viewing whole order it's all jumbled up not department order, so cant see if missing anything as all over the place! Very annoying, used the app for over 2 years and never had a problem now its driving me mad.

Some improvements. App keeps logging me out. Freezes when I go back in. The auto fill isn't working properly, it puts email address in the "forgotten password" field so I have to fill in the email address myself anyway. Why to I have to accept privacy settings every time I have to log back in?

The app itself is very good, easily added too, keeps favourites, review past orders. However after that stage when its passed to Asda stores, well anything can happen. out of 5 last orders via app, I have managed to get 1 order. non delivery to house, not at click n collect, no show, cancelled with no warning, you name it. Diabolical. went for my shopping tonight, well not there again. I'm dine with it. spend hours doing the shop for you to get Nothing! But the money still leaves your account !!

The app is okay but has bugs and issues that need fixing. Before the latest update, I was able to add items to my basket and click on how many I want. For example - cheese doritos, 2 packs. Asda please fix this.

It's signs me out EVERY TIME and doesn't remember my password, so I have to go and find my password and copy and paste it back into the app!? If it wasn't for this, it would be pretty darn good, but it's just annoying if I want to add one thing to my shopping list and spend 5 minutes signing in...

Generally I find it clumsy in comparison with other supermarkets. Navigating between pages when amending orders is time consuming. It's very frustating and time consuming. It must be annoying for staff too.

Love Asda but app is woeful. If I want an item it won't search properly. I go to the website, it's there, I want to amend an order and add that item it won't find it. Try in the website and it crashes. Can be in I e section, select a filter and it takes you to another section. Sort it out Asda

App is alright and easy to use. But there are not all options available. I had to still log in on web to add my gift card and when i have something in cart that becomes available only option it gives me on check out is to remove items, I would appreciate if I can choose alternatives or check out with unavailable items as I am checking few days in advance and those items can become available later,or get an alternatives on the day of delivery.

The petrol price is a good idea but useless as it doesn't work. Price at midday was 116.9p, the app says it was 118.7p. The app itself is really useful, I use it to build a shopping list for the store. Be good to have a function like that.

Latest update makes editing substitution preferences a real pain - every time you tick an item it scrolls you right back to the top of the list! And PLEASE add option to add notes to items like other stores do - then can at least potentially avoid some of the inappropriate substitutes I've received!

Its quick and easy. But always says items are out of stock...and I know for a fact its not always the case. Also the app sneakily removes your favourite items and replaces them with more expensive alternatives.

Some suggestions : *ordering loose vegetables - give separate options for amount and weight. I ordered two peppers but received 4 because the packer went by approximate weight and not amount. *allow the out of stock items to be added to basket - the item might be out of stock just before the cut off midnight time for amendments - but if i have an order that is coming at 7pm the next day the item may become available.

Generally fine except for one frustrating quirk of the keyword search where the auto suggested terms change just as you are about to tap so you end up clicking on the wrong result. It's a small thing but frustrating when it happens 10 times in one shop üò°
OK but could be much better. Would be good to be able to store your favourite store for collection. The ability to check-in for collection keeps disappearing. Navigation is a bit glitchy too.

One of the more affordable home delivery services across London and UK for fresh food, groceries and home essentials. Great potential but actually use of home delivery service leave you wishing for essential improvements in live stock and personalisation for family use. Poor feedback process and overly complicated contact support. Fingers cross for further updates to app and website.

Version 22.20 no longer allows items from an EXISTING order to be added to the basket, that is, you cannot select and add items from undelivered orders. This is a nuisance! Selecting previous orders - either for editing or adding to the basket - now requires two taps to open them. Why? üçåüò§

I use the app as I am a carer and need to get my shopping delivered. On days I can't get it delivered, I use click and collect. The products I use can sometimes be out of stock online, but 9 times out of 10 when I go into store the items are there. I found it is the items that would save me the most money.

Barcode scanner doesn't work. Just results in a blank page as if items found but display of results not possible. Also what's with the single penny pending transactions everyone I make an amendment. Tesco app doesn't do this.

Works fairly well however have increasingly found recently that items show as in stock until you try and add them or not until check out. Also I'll get a text to say I have substitutions on the day of the order but I can't view the order in the app, it just doesn't display, I have to log onto the website.

When you type pizza in the search it doesn't do anything. When you click on something in your favourites then go back it takes it back to the top of the list again instead of where you were last looking so have to scroll down again everytime, so annoying.

Had no problems with this app until recent update. Now I'm unable to select individual items from previous orders to add to my trolley. So I'm left with searching and shopping instead for every item. Very frustrating!!!

app is great and easy to use but my first order got cancelled for no reason and no message why. Called customer services and after 20 mins on the call they also had no idea why. Tried reordering but says something went wrong. Even called my bank to verify the card wasn't blocked and it fine. Dissapointing for first time online grocery shopping otherwise would be 5 stars

too many issues can't login...had to uninstall and install twice in 1 day just to put my order in. if your on it too long it freezes on the page, also I have noticed that the total amount is different when you go to checkout to what it said in basket :s asda really need to look at their site.

I've changed this week, I moved and started Asda online delivery aug 22, It's been adding to my cart, I've sorted but it goes to did you forget,you at first don't know what this is, but next shop it's items u brought last or any other time, but if you happen to get the front door etc, you have to go back on but I ended up due to this, missing items on delivery but I don't have time to check at the door. If you don't and not happy,a refund is only better at a store,Tesco or Morrisons all day long

Worst groceries delivery app! They cancelled because they couldn't process payment which shouldn't happen, everything is good with my bank account. The other day delivery man didn't show up, didn't call and said later that address was wrong. Will never even try to order anything there
I love the app but it limits the items you can buy like mayo why is there no Asda mayo

This works up to a point, but it still has some intensely irritating shortcomings, one of which is that items are shown as being in or out of stock *at the time of ordering*, meaning that they can be out of stock by the time of collection having been in at the time of ordering, or the other way round. The payment quite often doesn't go through. Another thing is that if I'm going through " My favourites" and I do my shopping, then decide to type a different product I'm after and then when I click "Back" it takes me to the "Home page" rather than the "My favourites" where I was before.

I used the previous Morrisons app all the time, it was great. Now I'm told that I have to use this version if I want deliveries. Favourite items haven't transferred over, can't see previous orders now, can't search on offers. It will say there are 20 items in a category but you can only see 6 - or sometimes nothing at all! Likes to close itself for no reason. It looks like they were part way through developing it and just released it anyway. Really poor.

Worst shopping app I've ever used. Can't see when vehicles are in my area. Search doesn't work properly. I can view more products on the website (although the website is much worse than it was a few months ago). Favourites and order history have disappeared. Order history isn't correct - a lot of my items from the last shop aren't showing up, making it difficult to quickly reorder. No 6-9am deliveries any more. Its so frustrating trying to order and not being able to find anything.

The reason I have stayed with Morrisons for over 5 years was the original app. It was easy to use, instant shop, one click additions all which made shopping very quick. I echo lots that has been said on previous reviews, in the hope that improvements are made. The sort options doesn't sort, it tells you there are 20 items in the category but only shows 4. All details were lost between transfer, even the delivery pass. Fingers crossed morrisons bring over what worked well on the old app!
Orders always wrong. Stealth substitutes thay just sent what ever thay want without letting you know or updating the order.

Absolutely shocking, todays order... mouldy carrots, mouldy onions and mouldy black dust on the cherries, they used to be great but now it seems they are getting rid off there dead stock on the people who cant see what there getting, the longest shelf life was two days, it feels deliberate but why?

I agree with recent reviews. The first warning we had of the change was when the old app just stopped working. The lists that took time to set up were lost and a shop that used to take 5 minutes now takes an hour. It's disappointing to see the same stock answer from you on this site which enhances the impression of poor customer service. I will go elsewhere when my delivery pass runs out and will be sorry to leave a service that I always recommended wholeheartedly for speed and convenience.

Been using since August 2019 and it's as bad as the day I installed it. Half the time I get "we're unable to update your trolley details" which renders the app useless. There's no separate fridge, freezer and cupboard section in the basket which makes reviewing what I need difficult if I have limited freezer space. So many menu categories that are just empty. Spelling mistakes all over. My stored favourites are 20 items that repeat down the list - 90% are missing so I often forget my essentials!

The is no notification that payment hasn't been taken, the shopping just doesn't turn up. No email, no text, nothing. It just quietly cancels the order when you go back in to find out why you have no food in the house 2 hours after the delivery was due. Not helpful when I'm quarantining. Garbage. Let me know if there is a problem with the payment so I can fix it!

I can do online shopping with this app put everything in the shopping basket add the delivery address details but when it comes to the checkout according to My bank to approve the payment to Morriston it doesn't work I have try 25 times to make the payments my bank told me that Morriston keep asking for ¬£ 0.00 so I am going to unstall the app because it doesn't work it and I will be going to asda instead to my shopping

So awkward - crashing, dropping connection, clunky menus, too many of them, difficulty accessing functions that were easy, sometimes finding they no longer exist. Selection reduced badly. Constant unavailability issues, things end up vanishing from my trolley for no reason. Other times the trolley duplicates an order, usually when I want to edit it, and today it wouldn't register adding items until I viewed trolley, so I was having to do that between each addition. Customer service nonexistent.

Having used the original app and being forced to move to this one due to local delivery changes, I echo the experiences that many others have expressed here. The app is slow, the one click add is missing and since the June 10th 2019 update my Favorites (which I had to rebuild since switching apps) are now missing again (thankfully they still show on the website). When browsing categories, many items are missing and entire categories are empty even though they have a count next to them.
replyContent:
Hi Matt


We are very sorry you are having trouble with the Morrisons app and our apologies for the inconvenience caused. We have released a new version of the app with a number of fixes which will be available for you to update shortly. Our sincere apologies.


Regards, 

Morrisons Online Team

content: Terrible app. I regularly order from Morrisons on the PC or iPad. I log in on my phone and the app insists they don't deliver to my area. Fix this, or I'll use Asda to order on my phone (which works fine)

I then had to go through editing the whole order. Apart from that, all was good.

Absolutely awful app-cannot believe that this 'new' version, of what previously was actually a really good app for completing my online shopping, has turned into the most basic version. Obviously lost all my favourites, but they removed the 'quick add' function, which I really liked & on the browsing section, it seems be buggy- categories number more items that it actually contains. I use my phone for the majority of my grocery shopping, I will seriously reconsider using morrisons from now on.

Being a Morrisons online customer for over 3 years and never having any problems previously this new update to the app is absolutely awful! The layout is very poor, my previous favourites I've accumulated have all been lost due to the update, no estimated expiry dates on any of the products and i can no longer make lists which was really helpful for me. The 'one click' add ons has gone as well which was brilliant. Very disappointed! I've moved to Tesco which is actually a lot better!

Terrible app. Slow, not as much info, few offers, sales etc. The recent change to the app and moving to local store delivery have been rushed and not thought through. This new app is a step backwards, on the old app you could create your own lists. When choosing a delivery slot it let you know if they were already in your area this doesn't. On items you could click 'show me more like this'. The list goes on! Please improve Morrison's!

One immediate result was our address disappeared from the app. No matter what I try the app will not recognise our postcode. I see from other comments that this is a common problem. There is no option to manually type an address, so placing an order is now impossible, although frustratingly we can waste time selecting the groceries!

I have been shopping with Morrisons online for couple of years without any issues. But now they've just upgraded the app and there is awful lots of teething issues. Does not work, could not use as it says delivery not available in my area so had to use website.

It needs a filter so you can search for specifics like frozen or fresh only; not everything. Top of the search results are adverts, cannot disable them. Can't email morrisons, as app will not open email app. A very amateur app compared to other supermarket apps. Devs got work on their hands to make this a useful app

TERRIBLE....I used the old app which was the same layout as the ocado app and was great. There were no other better apps out there for grocery shopping. This new version is slow, horrid to use, so much so I'm likely never to use it fully to complete a shop..I tried, it just annoys me. This is why i dont shop with other supermarkets apps very often because I prefer the convenience of a well laid out easy to use and edit app..whoever designed this did a poor job

Been using this app successfully for over a year. Now, like other users here I've just been get the message "Something went wrong, try again later" for the past 7 days. I called Customer services and was told by technical help that they can't do anything, until at least 10 people report the problem, otherwise they put it down to individual devices. I have reported the fault now and clearly others are getting the same message in the last few days. Please can you fix this ASAP. Thank you.

The new app no longer has my favourites nor allows me to import them from other shopping sites like the old app did. I decided to just go ahead and do a shop which took forever and then when I went to check out it duplicated all the items in my basket. I tried to reduce the quantity of the items but it wouldn't let me. So frustrating I just went to back to Tesco/Sainsbury's and Ocado!! Such a shame

I always used to use Morrisons because I found their app good, selection of items good ans rarely had missing items. i don't know what has changed here but it's a disaster. Deleting my just started order now.

content: I am very tempted to take my custom else where.. each week since using this new app something has gone wrong, whether it's delivery drivers parking in stupid places and ringing telling me they are outside my address when they're clearly not or substituting my shopping for other items that I cannot use, not to mention they've taken away the "request refund" for an item I'm extremely angry and very upset about tonight's experience. Please bring back the previous app..no problems with that at all!

I am now considering cancelling and shopping elsewhere. NB: The email address listed under contact developer sends a response advising that the email address is no longer in use.
Has been down now for a week, can't get to my shopping orders

This app DOES NOT WORK! The app does not connect to the Product Database, and so does not show the price of a product. It only shows the error message, "There are no products in the category". The send an email to report a technical issue, also does not work; and the main website has no facility to report technical problems with Morrisons app. Very disappointing for a bing supermarket chain like this, to have such bad IT capabilities; and no one checking to see if the apps actually work.

Worked perfectly fine until they moved deliveries to a central hub. Now doesn't recognise my address or for that matter any postcode!!! Deleted app, reinstalled it, changed email address, nothing works, now thinks I live in Beverly!!! That's the otherwise of the country. Been in touch with customer services and it's still not resolved. Hence I have been having deliveries from asda instead. So disappointed.

It's useless and yet since these very problems that I've repeatedly reported, and so have other customers, you keep issuing supposed updates for what I don't know!!

Horrendous app. Placed an order, went to change the day, managed to duplicate everything then cancel the order by accident (never had an issue on other app). Not a problem as can just use the order again button- nope every time I did this it wouldnt recognise anything in the basket. After 10 minutes of trying finally gave up and used website only for payment to be cancelled at midnight (order due 9am) to say order has been cancelled....cheers for nothing!

What have you done. Why have you introduced a new app which is far worse. 1) if my wife and I both log on at the same time it duplicates everything in the basket 2) the pictures on the grouping of items don't even exist to be chosen 3) when you check out and items are missing you can't easily add replacements 4) Ordered last night can got 6 items missing for next day delivery. Some Muppet thinks replacing chick peas with kidney beans is ok ! You might as well replace it with a toothbrush!

You do not provide us with a choice to print out our order to check. This is needed if you only have a smart phone and are over 70 with eyesight problems. Used to be able to print out from the email version. But the way you do it now it's useless

Truly awful! As an ex IT professional I believe I am qualified to recognise a clever, intuitive app. Unfortunately this isn't . I only used this once. Never again. How can an app let you order loads of items then tell you you are not in the correct service? Would not let me check out. Also locked up several times causing me to have to close manually. My advice? AVOID!!

Furthermore, the delivery pass I paid for just over a week ago has disappeared. So I've logged into my account but nothing has transferred across? Absolutely useless! Will be avoiding this app and just use the website I think.
too many prompts to keep adding before checkout. supposed to get a discount due to previous poor service but not applied üòï

The app is no longer functional, will not show any pages, reading error message: "We're currently unable to update your trolley details". You're then unable logout. Before this fiasco there was also problems with it not syncing to their main desktop website. Offers on the app would not show on the desktop. Hi Ian


We are very sorry you are having trouble with the Morrisons app and our apologies for the inconvenience caused. We have released a new version of the app with a number of fixes which will be available for you to update shortly. Our sincere apologies.

Morrisons Online Team

content: Excellent service. Would be better if orders were delivered bagged or in cardboard boxes.

Useful app which I mainly use for smaller click and collect orders. I would really like a substitutions option though - where I can tick whether or not I will accept another brand if my preferred one is not in stock. Other supermarkets do this. Some even allow you to write a description to specify alternatives you will accept. This feature would be really useful - it would stop me having to pop into the shop after picking up my order to replace missing items (like a different brand of bread).

For those having problems... Go into settings, and then apps and notifications, then select the Morrisons app, then storage and cache, then delete cache, and then delete data.
