Slow and unreliable. In terms of the service, frequently send food that will go out of date within a couple of days. Regularly fails at the checkout stage (sometimes the checkout button will be greyed out, sometimes the pages that are part of the checkout process just won't load). Any error messages encountered have no details as to what caused the problem. The navigation seems broken and often doesn't take you to the page you've requested. Also wish it would stop begging for app reviews.

Once you place an order you cannot amend it and then you have to cancel the entire order, rebook your slot and then do your entire shopping again in order to make any amendments. Tried calling Sainsbury's helpline only to be in the queue for 45 mins and not get through. I definitely won't be ordering online with Sainsbury's anymore. App is useless and so is the groceries website. It just keeps crashing.

Constant errors, example can't place order yet I receive an email stating I've ordered and my bank has charged me. Can't retrieve order details error. Search throws up 400+ results for searching for mint, the majority of the items listed aren't even mint adjacent. You show a review count but on the app you can't read reviews, only on a browser can you see them, seriously, Asdas' app you can see hundreds of customer reviews. Thoroughly irritating app that needs serious work. Do better!

The service and delivery drivers are excellent, however the app is absolutely shocking, various bugs and issues, twice within the last week I've been unable to check out changes, on both the app and website which seems to be equally unreliable

New to the app and its rubbish, keeps loading so can't get to my orders to amend them. I have to login to the website instead. I usually use ocado, their app is amazing. One click add feature is brilliant, no rush refunds through the app, no comparison!

Charges are ridiculous. Wanted to order some wine glasses couldn't get in shop. Had to do time slot delivery for this , no other delivery/postal option. Said it would be ¬£2 for slot I picked, then wanted ¬£7 because my order was under ¬£40, my wine glass totaled at ¬£20. Minium spend had to be ¬£25 or over. So ended up costing me just under ¬£35. UTTER RIP OFF, WILL NOT USE AGAIN!!!!
Why can you not have one app for all groceries, smart shop, and nectar points but you have three or more different in which it makes it non practical to use.

For quite a long time, this app was great. However, the recent update has scuppered that - on my phone anyway. Previously, if I typed "un", unsalted butter would appear as, presumably, the most logical choice. Now I get "unamplified", "unbelievaballs", amongst 8 other completely irrelevant suggestions. Likewise, typing "who" (for whole milk) gets me "wham" and "whamtastic"! Please amend the search function - to, at the very least, show items stocked by Sainsbury's...
Latest Update renders this app utterly useless as I just get stuck on the home screen with a flashing trolley! Uninstalled and then reinstalled and it's the same - nothing works!
Another useless app...search is hopleless,keeps closing ,payment system unreliable ....All these apps used to be simple,functional & reliable .8.7.2023now keeps losing added items .John

If you have something in your trolly for a saved order that becomes unavailable, when you update the order you can't delete it in the app, and it will not let you check out with it there. Utterly infuriating. Pure junk.
Awful. App is full of errors, and fails to update basket. Also, there is an error which occurs when trying to checkout.
Bad UX, and since the last update it's become an unreliable app, basket won't update and can't complete orders.

I'd love to know how to redeem my nectar points. The simple way I used to historically has disappeared from the app. I've searched & searched to much frustration & negative this review. Can anyone advise? Please.

2.5 years after my original 1 star review & this dreadful app somehow gets even worse with every update. Checkout still randomly hangs, but now also keeps disconnecting my Nectar card from my account, requiring me to go into my Sainsbury's account through a browser to reconnect it. The app STILL reverts to delivery instructions from over 3 YEARS AGO, however many times I change & save them. And still no way to remove an item from the basket if it goes out of stock before checking out. Pathetic!

Continually terrible. This app has been terrible for years with an endless list of problems that take months to get fixed. Now, it won't start, or if it does after several attempts and a protracted delay, then it won't load your basket etc. Editing orders is slow and gives errors. I've stopped shopping at Sainsbury's because of the number of items received with as little as zero days life and then being told this is "policy" by customer service, who then try to fob you off with a voucher.

Sainsburys for the love of all that is holy please sort this app out. Your produce is fantastic, your delivery drivers are lovely but this app is driving me INSANE. I can't use the app with ANYTHING else open and I can't remove out of stock items from my basket which then makes checking out often impossible. You aren't the cheapest supermarket around, please spend some of your profit in improving this abysmal app! Also please allow comments alongside product reviews.
Once the app is installed it won't allow you to log in. It doesn't go to the signing on screen

No longer able to order an online shop. Payment has failed on both mine and partners cards. It isn't an issue with our banks, clearly an issue at sainsburys' end. This happens on the app and also online on the website.
Since the last update this app is unusable. They still show, in the app, items that are not in stock. If you add them to your basket the order is then cancelled! Really annoying.
Never had an app that gives a 403 error everytime. This is just the worst possible app in the world. I would complain about the performance but since the app won't even start up it isn't good.
Very poor. Constantly loading, hardly working. Doesn't matter which device or browser I use. Waste of time waiting around to try to do shopping when it won't load or even search for items

Just about to do usual shop using app update flashed on screen..did this..now I only have use coupons option not coupons or nectar points was customer services any help either nectar or Sainsburys..were they heck..just wanna spend my nectar points on shop same as I have done for years...going to cancel delivery subscription if can't get this sorted..sent round in circles on the phone..

Glitching, coming up with errors, not letting me add certain items, removing or doubling, just had to call up as it booked my shopping for 9-10pm instead of am and then, changed it on the app to 5-6pm and it did not go through and having to do click and collect half an hour away! When checking out it always has error but doesn't go into detail with what the error is, it's been getting worse and worse lately to the point I'm unlikely I will use the app

this WAS a great app, and when it works it is easy to use. Unfortunately a recent update has caused major stability issues. For the last couple of months it has been a pain to use. It either crashes or fails to open, showing a blank screen and progress indicator. I also keep getting a basket error warning and it adds an extra item to the basket. It's the same on my partners phone.

APP STILL ISN'T WORKING! Keeps leading me to the website! Very frustrating as I had a lot of items in my basket. Out of all the supermarket apps, this has to be the worst. You can't zoom into pictures, pictures don't load, pages don't load, no reviews, the scroll position jumps to the top of the page when you navigate away from the page, generally very slow, the list goes on! Please take note from the supermarket you are trying to merge with - their app is the best!

This app is so bad it hurts. A few weeks ago it was giving an error referring users to the website every time it was opened. Then it worked for a while... now it immediately crashes every time I open it. Even when it works, it's fairly rubbish - tiny fuzzy pictures, a lot of products with no pictures at all, no product reviews, freezes when adding items to basket. Developers, please stop wasting time with pointless updates like the "pride" splash screen, and just make the damn thing work.

Unresponsive, unreliable, seems to be unavailable a lot of the time of late. There's a really annoying issue with search too, the app takes you to your basket after searching for a product and then you have to search for the product again to bring up the items you want to purchase. I have tried clearing all data from the app off my device, uninstalling and reinstalling the app but it doesn't solve the issue. Please fix.

it doesn't show prices properly, it crashes constantly, it won't let you book a slot for delivery (literally no place to go for it some times that's just missing along with the favourites section). Just when you get to the end and you're trying to check out it crashes coz you don't want to swap something. shop somewhere else and save yourself a who lot of time and frustration!!!!

Every time I search for a product it kicks me back to my basket, where I have to search for it again (usually does the search 2nd time around). Usually have to open the app twice as it fails to open properly first time round. Often crashes at checkout taking me to a page that has no checkout button, and the only way to checkout is to go back to basket and do it again. Sometimes more than once. Badly needs an update.

Incredibly frustrating. So many glitches and faults, I don't know where to begin. The search functionality is broken so you have to search multiple times before you get results - it just pings you back to your basket. The cookie preferences box pops up when you go to check out and causes the payment to fail and get stuck on some random screen. It is a faff to find and edit all but your next order. Just AWFUL. How does such a large supermarket get away with something so poor?

Useless! It looks like the app merely directs you to a web address to log in, but as soon as you try to enter your account password it loops back to the home page, and round you go again, unendingly. However, if you use the phone menu to open the log-in page in your browser, you can continue as normal. Clearing cache and data makes no difference. Uninstalled.

Seriously unreliable, constantly buggy. How can you not get this right in this day and age? The newest bug is that when I attempt to add a coupon to my order it goes to a totally differently 'processing order' screen and just sits there. I eventually have to press the back button on my phone, remove the coupon and then place the order. What's the point in getting coupons anymore if they can't be used. Please sort these issues out. Update - 4/10/19, now 1 star because you can't even search.
App has become ridiculously slow and won't load my orders page etc. I have to use the web page now.
The worst shopping app. It cuts off especially during the day. Can only use at night. It's a shame as the products are fine.Sainsbury needs to have a better app that, can be used 24 hrs.

Talk about a buggy ****ing mess. Shopping cart doesn't update when you add things to it. Want to change your account details? Then look forward to having to go back through every screen you went through to do it to get back home! Just done all your shopping only to find the cart forgot what you'd put it in (once it finally works). Give this a skip and go to the store, or a competitor.

This app is very unreliable. Very poor at finding items based on your search terms. I've had orders lost due to inability to checkout changes (app could not verify my address with Uber Eats!!!) so get an incomplete delivery and have to work out what's missing then go to get it myself. Twice the work. Would be easier not to use it at all! Really needs improvement!!

We use it but it's by necessity. The website is undoubtedly more resilient. The app has too many "can't connect too server", "slot unavailable" (despite it being the one being edited!) or, a new one, "can't update slot as it's after 23:00" despite it being 22:01. The visual design could be better. The choice of font sizes, etc is a little confusing.
Horrible! It won't let me log in anymore! Have had to resort to using the computer to make my orders.

App developers... please read these reviews. I've been using this app for a few years and it has always been a bit flakey but a quick reboot sorted it out. Since the recent updates, it's practically unusable. I thought my tablet was getting a bit old, so i checked these reviews and reinstalled. All the things listed below still happen to me. I've had to call customer services a few times to straighten my basket out.

Poorly designed. There isn't anywhere to look at orders already made. 3 times now I've made my shop, booked it in, paid. Only to find no confirmation email was sent and as I've finished my order when I go back to the app it's all gone and I have to start over. No money was taken from my account but a lot of time was lost The help center, contact us and a lot of the sub menus all lead you round in a crucial. To make matters worse it's the only app on my 2 month old galaxy note 10 that crashes.

Was looking forward to latest update, very disappointed, still no simple way to add items into favourite list. This essential feature alone could easily boost your sales, I just don't understand why after so many years your business development team, engineers, designers, no one thought about it, unbelievable really, this is basic stuff, especially that you now added option to remove items. Also, there are more bad programming/design practices, but I have run out of space to describe it all here
Sainsburys whole UI/UX is just terrible, both the app and the website. They are horrible to use and they constantly crash and big out. Weird for such a big company to have such terrible systems

More recently, when during the checkout process I am told that an item is unavailable, and I accept a substitute, the app then takes me to the book a delivery slot page, even though I have already booked a slot. Obviously if this happens the day before the delivery, there are no slots left. Presser fix this. When I go to a previous order and put the entire order in my trolley, the app only puts in one of each item.
After the update to Android 14 this is very temperamental. Often just won't open and stays on the throbbing orange basket screen.
Search facility doesn't work. Says everything is out of stock.
Can no longer search for items even though the app it fully updated totally useless

Unusable. First time install and cannot do anything. Searching tells me I have no connection; I do. Browsing groceries tells me "something went wrong. please try again". Logging in fails with an error message, again hinting at my connection. Using Wifi or mobile network makes no difference. Can use other apps at the same time and they have no issue connecting.
Cannot view my orders which is concerning. Please fix. I cannot believe that this app hasn't had an update for over a month. Sainsbury's should sack their developers!

Once I get to checkout the app begins flashing backwards and forwards. I have to touch 'continue' many times before I get to place the order. Then it refuses payment, saying the bank has not responded. Then I run upstairs to switch on the PC to pay. Tonight I was updating an order and the updates weren't on the PC so I will have to go to Sainsbury's tomorrow to get the shopping I missed. Really annoying! It's a recent problem so I wonder if it's the fault of an update? In future, I'll do the whole order on the PC and abandon the app. It's a waste of time.
replyContent:
Hi Joanna, 

Thanks very much for getting in touch and sorry to hear about the issues you've been experiencing. Would you be able to give us a bit more detail on this so we can try and diagnose the problem?

Thanks again for your feedback,
Sainsbury's GOL App Team

content: UPDATE: Incredibly unstable/unreliable app. I do my main shop on a PC as the app is not as fully featured as the website. IF I then have to make a minor amendment, I try to use the app - but so often after making the changes, I cannot complete checkout - the app says 'cannot connect to website - please try again'. Despite having a perfectly working internet connection and the website being accessible on the PC. Only way to fix the issue is to force stop the app, re-login again, hope that it has kept your changes and then checkout. If Tesco can avoid these kinds of issues with their app, why can't Sainsburys. Falls way short of the similar Tesco app - which works flawlessly all the time and has a much slicker interface and usability. This Sainsbury's app keeps timing out, showing errors or not letting you save your changes to slot time or basket...Have to resort to my PC to make the changes.

It's very temperamental app...hangs all the time, particularly if you're using anything apple.if you forget to book a slot at the beginning and then go to check out, you lose all your basket and have to start again..tesco's online does this easily. You often can't check out once you've made changes because there's a problem with one error or another - virtually every order (we've placed over 150 orders so have given enough chance). mother-in-law should be ordering from tesco - it works!

This app has become terrible with recent updates, you are scrolling down your favourites and it randomly jumps up the list now and again, when you switch app to look at a message or a shopping list it goes all the way back to the top, your shopping cart doesn't show all the items properly and searches don't always work, they will give you an item count but am empty list, and showing sponsored results in my favourites is annoying. I have given up and use the website because it works much better.

I use the website but last night I thought, is there a Sainsbury's app? This is quite possibly the most frustrating app I have ever used! There seems to be no way of look at the details of any items and trying to click on an item or even to add an item results in taking you back to your basket. Not only that, but somehow I was able to add many items that I didn't want! Simply bizarre. Avoid and stick with the website!

Horrible horrible app. The worst I've used so far. I like to add things to my basket as the week goes on so I don't forget them, then checkout once it's full. But most of the time not all my items make it through to checkout. This has happened numerous occasions. At first I thoight I'd maybe forgot to add them, but several items I KNOW I've ordered haven't arrived this week. Also the quality of most products isn't anywhere near as good as even Aldi! And way more expensive!
Awful. Unreliable. Now telling me that NO day slots available for over a week at my local store even though store says they're operating as normal. Sort this shocking app out. I'm off to Tescos.

Not sure what happened to the app but I cannot now checkout changes to my order on my Samsung A10 phone. When I get to the payment stage, it's only giving me options to select a voucher, so I click on that and it immediately says payment failed. I've had to resort to using a tablet or laptop which is a bit inconvenient when I've been using the app on my phone for months.

Useless app since update. Full of random bugs. L I had a problem checking out previously that rectified itself after a day of worrying I'd lose my slot. It worked a couple of times and this time it refused to recognise my address for Uber Eats (whatever that means). For those of you looking for a fix, I did it via the website on Chrome and it went through without any trouble. Fingers crossed the delivery arrives...

Not very happy 1st time some of my shopping items not available been changed with cheap quality one, 2nd time part of the items missed & been charged for all items the good thing I contacted customer service I asked for refund, 3rd time the driver refuse to bring the stuff to my door he said he is (fasting) plus he is not required and allowed to deliver the stuff to door as this is a safety measures by Sainsbury's itself
Thought Id use it for the first time to oppose using Tesco but this is a truely terrible app. I cant even add things to the shopping trolley and the search function is awful.
Cannot view orders or e-receipts since last app update :(

I can finally see all my favourites rather than just 30 and prices no longer overlay the description. But, I can't get through the processing payment stage, it just hangs. This is EVERY time. The only way to complete an order is to login through their website. Seriously who releases these updates without trying them?! I also frequently get 'no internet connection' or items (favourites) will not load. All very frustrating and I can't see myself renewing our delivery service!

It's a complete lottery as to whether the app will load on one of my devices. Usually I can get it on my phone or tablet without having to fire up the laptop, but it's far from convenient. Items that you don't buy regularly enough drop off your favourites list, so, for instance, if you buy the biggest bag of dishwasher tablets, they will have gone before you need another bag. Update - the app is now completely useless, as it is impossible to check out, and backing out empties your trolley.

This app is broken! Last week the app and website kept crashing and I just about managed to amend my order before the cut off time. Today, every time I try and check out my order on the app it comes up with an error message, and I can't view the order in the app. The app search function is useless. If I'm searching for bananas I don't want search results for grapes, yogurt and baby food...just bananas! Maybe time to ditch Sainsbury's and shop elsewhere.

I've down rated this app from 1 to 2 stars as it's gotten worse instead of better. There are so many problems with it I don't have enough space to list them. I use all the other supermarket apps & this is the worst. It, at minimum, trebles the amount of time it takes to shop. Crashes frequently too. It's horrible to use, but their mobile site isn't much better unfortunately. It's really letting Sainsbury's down. If they didn't have specific items I wanted I wouldn't use it at all.

The positive: I used to have the problems that Ryan Tebbit decribes about the add button being unreliable and the favourites not showing properly. I do not have that problem anymore.  The negative: When I try to open the app it just shows: "Oops. Something went wrong" and closes.  If you are looking for an app that shows a static error screen with a cool rainbow background, this is the one for you! Everyone else, use a PC or shop with a competitor.

The app doesn't let you cancel an order. You have to use the website to xance. Frustrating to checkout. Had error message on checking out that this could not be processed as some items were not available but didn't state which items. Had to revert to website and checked out OK. Searched for laundry detergent and results included conditioner doubling number of hits. If I wanted conditioner I would have searched for it. Would be useful to sort by price per item etc

If you build up a basket this cannot be easily added to a pre-existing order. In fact if you edit a pre-existing order any items in your basket are lost! Also the range of goods you can order is much reduced compared to what you can buy in store.Often you can find things via Google on the Sainsbury's website which are absent from the app. Also the app isn't that stable and searches have to be frequently retired. I don't find the Ocado app anywhere near as frustrating.

This app is awful, i cant remember the last time it worked properly and me not have to login into the website to place my order. From timing out when trying to search for items, or erroring upon adding an item (nearly ended up with 14 bunches of bananas, 21 blocks of butter)For the last month i have been unable to confirm delivery orders and have to go over to the website. No point having an app if it never works!! Also upon trying to sort items by low to high, some of the items no longer appear

Since the latest update the App just won't open, all I get is 'Oops something went wrong - try again'. I have deleted and downloaded again several times but still won't work on either of my Samsung Tab or smartphone. Really annoying as I now have to sign in via the website everytime. It's been like this for a month or so now. Please correct whatever you have updated and put the App back to how it was or you will lose customer to your competitors whose App's do work.

Terrible! I have been using this app for months with no problem, then the update came at the end of April 2019, and all of a sudden the thing is useless. It won't even let me open the blooming app! keeps redirecting me to the web page. Really annoyed! I have now reinstalled it 3 times over a week, still not working! Ridiculous!

This app is getting worse, keep having to reinstall as keeps freezing. Plus although nectar card linked and I have loads of points it won't convert to a voucher for my online shop, says I don't have enough points! Infuriating!!

I have to refresh every time I search for an item, delete an item from the trolley and half the time anything I search for doesn't come up in the box. Just sits there trying to find an item. I have close down the page every time I do something pretty much including checkout. Don't even try to remove something from the trolley and checkout, you have to close it everytime. Please sort it!!!

When checking out, occasionally the app takes you to a checkout page without a checkout button, just your list of items and "add new card", you need to cancel and log into the website on a pc to finalise the shopping. When adding previous shopping baskets to your current shop, the system adds unit items as weight items.

Search feature is poor: search for "garlic powder" and the first actual garlice powder item is the 42nd in the list (sorted by relevance). UI isn't great either; after searching for and adding loads of items to get back to the beginning I have to use the back button and go through each of the previous searches.

Been using Sainsburys for delivery since the beginning of the pandemic and paid for an annual delivery pass. Past couple of weeks there have been problems using app and couldn't do my last update on items required so ended up with half my shopping being delivered. Past two days the app won't even open so I've had to go to another supermarket. Going to lose a lot of custom if this doesn't get sorted

Has anyone at Sainsburys even used this app? Navigating is a joke...other supermarkets you can navigate through broad ranges, like 'Tinned goods' without having to navigate either through the entire ambient section or narrowing it down to single tins of tuna before you see the products. So frustrating and time consuming to use. Cancelled the order, couldn't be bothered any more! The website is even worse.

The app is very confusing and not very clear. When adding my address there was no continue button so I had to go back to the beginning, it then asked me for my address again. So I came out of the app and next day went back into it where my address had been saved. Something happened when adding my card, then same again to pay. I then added items to my list a few days later and it's charged me for my whole shopping trolley again! If I wasn't shielding I would not use this app at all

Unusable after the last update nothing loads properly and basket keeps disappearing. Very frustrating after using the app for years without many problems. I can't wait any longer for you to fix as I'm disabled, so difficult leave the house. Some people rely on this service it's simply not good enough. I will have to order from your competition Iceland or Tesco. You may loose a customer for good if I like them.

Terrible communication and navigation. Comms: it keeps offering me a meal deal on pizza (and I guess sides) but no where does it say what I'm actually supposed to pick! Not when I search for the deal, click in to the deal or even click on one of the items. Also navigation is terrible - hard to get back to the main menu, the back button either takes you back not far enough or pops you truthy it of the app to the home screen. Sad to say but the Asda app is much better!

Ive just spent absolutely ages gathering a basket & it's suddenly emptied on it's own.! ! Logged out & back in - the same, please get this sorted, I tried the app because the web version crashed my browser, its loading way too much data, it needs to wait until all sub categories have been chosen & THEN show results - not after each selection & have to re-enter 'filters' over & over again, eating up all my mobile web data & browser / device memory, not happy tbh

Hopeless and frustrating. Constantly crashes. Needed to make changes to my order fairly close to the 11pm deadline but with 10 mins to spare, then the app froze while 'processing' and they didnt go through in time. I'm starting to think about using another supermarket as time is precious and this app is not saving me any!

Badly coded. You have to uninstall the app every other week and reinstall in order to complete checkouts. I've tried bringing this up with their Twitter help, but they just say they can't possibly be expected to create an app that doesn't have loads of issues. So rubbish customer service and rubbish app... Great combination!

When it does work properly, which isn't that often, if you navigate/click back, you end up seeing the results from your first search; there are now loads of 'sponsored items' that appear at the top of the search; plus now loads of unrelated items - I searched for Pizza and got Burgers, Wedges and Sausages listed... seriously?! You also now get items listed that aren't even available, even after selecting a delivery day/time. Keeps getting worse, not better.

Navigation and categorisation is PAINFUL. I'm vulnerable and isolating, but because I'm not on a "special list" I can't get delivery. Can't contact. Can't email. Can't send complaint. Terrible customer service options online and through the app. FAQ or write a letter only, by the looks of things. Useless! A real let-down. Better off with Tesco! Edit: found out today that I can't book any slot of any kind. Press on "reserve slot", countless times and nothing happens!

Since the recent update, the "add" button has been unpredictable, sometimes adding more items than you want, sometimes not adding items at all. In addition I can only see 30 items in my favourites even though the app says i have over 100 items saved. Some items online are listed as unavailable even though they are available in store. Please respond Sainsburys as this is becoming so frustrating. July 2019 update has made no difference, i still cannot view all my favourites. Rubbish.

Sainsbury's has inserted sponsored products in to my favourite list. To my mind, this is completely unacceptable. It has made the whole shopping experience significantly harder. Instead of just clicking everything in my list like I used to do, I now have to sift through all the adverts (of which there are many). It used to take two minutes to shop now it takes much more. Sainsbury's, making life just a little bit harder.

Everytime I've tried to amend an order it shows all my individual items 2 or 3 times which is confusing as I thought I'd doubled up on some items at first & deleted them. I couldn't read any reviews on any of the products so wasn't sure if I wanted them or not. Every time I logged on it said my trolley was empty!! Lots wrong with this app & prefer to shop from the website. Probably the worst app I've used!

I stopped using this app to checkout my orders. There are to many flaws to rely on it. Its frustrating when you think you have a slot to find days later its disappeared and you have to book again for a later slot. Sometimes the checkout process fails altogether. It can be difficult to edit my substitue list within the app The app will hang while updating and to continue i have to shut it down and reopen it. Now I only use the app to add items to my basket on the go and checkout later from my PC

Really getting frustrated with app. this is second shopping that i amend the order and checked out clicking twice check out button and thinking how I finally got to the end of the bloody offers Only to receive unammended order because your app seems to ask me if I have forgotten something a 100 times instead of checking me out. You should call the button something like "next" not "checkout" if it's not actually going to check the person out. Considering moving to different shop!

I'm thinking of stopping using this device due to bugs. Example - this week I can't amend my order because the "following offers are unavailable for your slot - please remove" but the list of items to remove is empty. Emptying the trolley to start again doesn't fix it. Neither does clearing the app storage and restarting the phone. Who knows what is coming now on Friday night!!?? Update - no longer able to use this app as it gives the above error with every new attempt at ordering. Useless

Used this app for shopping for a fair few years now and only had a few minor glitches and bugs here and there but not really had any major issues ...until now. Clearly untested software. I've been using the app since the 1st lockdown & the App is getting worse. The frustration of using the Sainsbury's app is not worth the annual delivery fee, if one cannot place order. I will not be renewing my delivery after this year and will want a refund due to being unable to online shop!

Always got same issues with this app that never gets fixed. When scrolling down the page refreshes and adds a whole bunch of new items so i now have to scroll back up to where i was before and start again, it happens every time i make a new search. Similar thing happens in the basket when removing an item the page scrambles all the items up so i now have no idea where the next item i wanted to remove is i have to scroll to the very beginning and work my way down through the whole list.

Worse product range than in a mid-size store, items we purchased regularly swapped for more expensive ones and an expensive delivery pass system that is unlikely to save you money. Add this to an intuitive but badly conceived app interface and a lack of the smart shopping features you would expect, I don't see why you'd bother. Getting Sainsbury's home deliveries is mildly more useful, but much more frustrating than stores. I am now deleting this app and going to ask for a refund for my pass.

Unuseable and it appears Sainsbury's don't care as they don't respond to the repeated complaints. Keeps crashing and closing even after re-installing. Page jumps when you try to add more than one of an item to the basket even on web. Layout problems so prices and text overlay each other and are unreadable. Favourite disappear from list if not ordered regularly - somethings are only needed infrequently. I need to use online shopping and favourites due to disabilties caused by chronic illnesses.

This a really clumsy ap, navigating back from anything is not intuitive and swiping through on your phone you frequently select things by mistake and flick back to the main menu. Really poor design, and no suggestions or related items linked to the products. This was also the first time we used Sainsbury's delivery and having had everything delivered at 9pm the dates on nearly every fresh product were to be used that day. We won't be using them again. Heading back to Ocado.
Can't easily find barcode for checkout wants me to log in to nectar app. I'll not bother. Tesco's app is far superior.

This app has bugs. If the user does not check the quantity in the shopping list before placing the order then that product that you need 1 is charged for 4 and also delivered 4. Second bug being that inspite of good internet connection, the categories when opened shows problem with internet connection.
Why can you not have one app for all groceries, smart shop, and nectar points but you have three or more different in which it makes it non practical to use.

UTTER RIP OFF, WILL NOT USE AGAIN!!!!
Extremey rude, unprofessional service and support
App has become ridiculously slow and won't load my orders page etc. I have to use the web page now.

Constant errors, example can't place order yet I receive an email stating I've ordered and my bank has charged me. Can't retrieve order details error. Thoroughly irritating app that needs serious work. Do better!

This app is broken! Last week the app and website kept crashing and I just about managed to amend my order before the cut off time. Issues definitely. Now it doesn't allow me to check out... Sighs

Unpredictable This app is so frustrating! Too often it buffers for ages or gets stuck. There are 2 main issues that I find really frustrating with this app. 1 - it allows me to book a slot, choose groceries and check out for the first time, so obviously that's good, but then if I need to go back into it, I can't seem to amend my order either because it freezes or it says that I don't have any orders, so I end up going it via the website to make changes. 2 - I'm continually being asked to enter my email/password, which gets a tad irritating. Most apps remember credentials!

Such an outdated app, poor user experience. As others have said, if you view the details of an item and then go back to the list you are right at the top again. This is made worse by said list only part loading until you scroll down. Also, what is the point of having the ability to view a larger image when all it does is stretch the low res one. The Tesco app so much better and user friendly.

Re reviewing as I'm annoyed by changes. I used to get on really well with this app but now it's virtually unusable. The app allows you to add products to your trolley which are unavailable for your delivery slot, it doesn't tell you they are unavailable until you try to check out, at which point a pop-up helpfully informs me "product unavailable for delivery at this time" (or similar wording) but not WHICH product. Am I supposed to guess? You can't check out 'till the mystery product is removed

Basic functionality doesn't work. Filters and search functions don't actually filter the search results. You get stuck in pages when checking out, like in the add card page for example, I had to restart the checkout as I the back button simply refreshed the add card page. It's 2020 and we are going through a time where more people will be using online shopping!
This app started off really good, now issues with being unable to checkout due to out of stock items, and now I can't even spend my nectar points - the option has disappeared. What's going on?

Sorry, but the App is a complete mess. There are so many bugs it is virtually unusable a lot of the time, and I usually have to use the desktop site to complete my order as the App simply stops responding or gets stuck if an item is unavailable when you try to check out. I would expect better from a company of this size and reputation.

I don't know what's happening this week, but it's taking ages to load, plus when I delete something from my trolley when scrolling through to check, the items shuffle about and go in a new order, so I have to start reviewing my trolley again. From my cart, I can't click home and land there. Checkout has improved though, it's much quicker and doesn't need multiple attempts anymore. Few issues, it works okay and I get there.

Despite several updates this app seems to get worse. Basic bugs are not fixed for months, and then new bugs are added with each update. For example I have just tried to book a delivery using the new system, which crashed and now the app won't load. These frequent issues, combined with the problem that I can't order many of my favourites online, means I'll be looking elsewhere at the end of the contract.
It's got a lot of functionality and if it didn't hang all the time I'd have given it 5 stars.

Great when it works, but more often than not it's so slow to load, I can start my pc, log on, open the browser, log in to sainsburys web site, and complete what I needed to do before the app even connects. I also found a bug tonight. One of my choices was unavailable so the notification popped up. But when I clicked ok expecting to be able to choose an alternative, I was taken to "book a slot". Going to the pc again saved the day. Little gen lettuces were unavailable, not the slot, and there I w

Normally a good app but recently the search regularly fails. The first search just returns to the trolley, so I have to search for an item again and usually it will come up a second time, sometimes I have to search 3 times before I get the page of results. It isn't due to mistyping as that would return a "no results" page. Sometimes it has registered the search, so it appears in the list below the search bar, and other times it hasn't. Sainsbury's please fix!

Slow, buggy and generally not user friendly. Constantly hangs on payment and simple features found on competitors' apps are missing, such as being able to add one item to an existing order without having to go in and edit the order and checkout (and get stuck on payment) again... Badly designed and I really would expect better from one of the UK's biggest supermarkets.

Nowhere near in the league of the Tesco app. Every time I go to use it on my S20, it's crashed and I have to restart the app. Same happened with my S7. Like others, I find it frustrating that it changes the order and scrolls through when you remove an item from your basket, so that you lose your place. Also, unlike the Website, there is no apparent way to add a whole previous shop to your basket.

Disappointing. I am a regular Sainsbury shopper and do my shopping through the app, its such a shame that there are so many crashes. I use it on a samsung Android, the app unfortunately doesn't work well. It is my main shopping app so I can just about get what I need to done but I have to go online to finish transactions as I can't do them on the app. It loads pages, adds and removes items from the basket extremely slowly with multiple crashes and seems to get worse with every passing update.

Quite buggy, often crashes on checkout so you don't know whether your order has been processed, items sometimes don't appear on the app but are available from the website (and in real life in store). We've missed entire loads of shopping when trying to make last minute amendments before the 11pm deadline. Not easy to browse the store and not particularly intuitive to use.
The new Nectar prices does not work on the app so they are practically and effectively useless. Updated to latest version and checked compatibility, all fine.

Disappointing as the app has become almost unusable of late. I'm a very long time user who is now frustrated with the updates which are not fixing the underlying issues - number of favourites keeps changing with many missing, keeps saying to check internet connection despite nothing being wrong, items are unavailable for weeks on end despite being available in store - now some have re-appeared but with no add button! Need to get it sorted before I go looking elsewhere.

Lots of bugs, doesnt like you editing orders literally crashes when you try to use the menu to browse for items. Also defaults to top of list when adding something to the basket, annoying if you are scrolling for deals through hundreds of items. Also pictures are fuzzy and awful. Descriptions for products not very good. Come on sainsburys you charge a premium for your products your app could at least match the high prices

I use a Samsung Galaxy Note 10.1 tablet. This app was pretty horrible to use. It only showed in Portrait mode, not landscape. Some bits of the regular website were missing such as the Free items/competition bit. Scrolling up and down was awful. Once it comes near the bottom of the page, it jumps up 1.5 pages really quickly, so each time, you have to memorize what items are at the base of page, and scroll up to find them again! I only tried the app out, as the site was so slow on my pc.

Useless, I have been using this app for years and suddenly without warning I am unable to use it properly, I can book a slot make my initial choices then check out, BUT after doing that when I go into the app again to make changes thats when it all goes wrong, it just will not allow me to make changes, it just goes to the checkout page. Owww frustrating...

The app itself is fine for searching and adding to trolley, but for the last couple of weeks I have been unable to check out, as I just get an error message saying 'could not order product at this time'. I then have to go on to the website and check out there (no error messages there) I've tried uninstalling and reinstalling etc and nothing has helped. I get the same error message using the app on my tablet and phone so its not my device.

Sainsbury's are great.. Their app isn't! I have been an on line shopper for years. I'm constantly frustrated by their search criteria, when I type in a search, then get a list, look at an item on the list and want to return to the list, EVERYTIME it doesn't go back to the list, just the search term I've typed in. Also the substitution allowed area needs updating. As others have said not as good as Tesco app. I've let sainsbury's know their app and Web are sub standard but do not address it.

Seems to have a bug where if you change the weight of a joint of meat to anything other than the smallest available size on ordering, it defaults after saving to the smallest. When you amend your order you can see this, and despite deleting the item and re-ordering with the correct weight, still the item delivered was too small to feed my family, meaning I need to go out and buy another.
Why can't I book a slot? The app seems not to be working for the last 3 days.

Its ok when it works, sometimes it won't let me check out. Takes a while to load at times. I have had to go to the desktop site instead to check out and order. Not the best app needs improvement. I would also prefer it if it grouped together bakery dairy food cupboard and frozen but It just has them randomly on the list. The asda app I used to use was much better showed in groups was much easier to see what you had. But prefer shopping with sainsburys. Just wish the app could be better.

Going to have another go at downloading this as had to uninstall the last one due to the website being permanently 'unavailable'. Not the best app, in fact the only one that I use that has so many problems and glitches, you'd think such a massive corporate would have this sorted wouldn't you? Will try to install again as it would be handy if I could get it to work! Not holding my breath though, it's clearly not a priority for them.

Frustrating Favourites UI. When you click into the detail of a product, the back button takes you to the top of the favourites list again so you have to slowly scroll back to where you were. As it very easy to accidentally select product details when scrolling, this can happen several times, making the App almost unusable.

Used this for the first time after deciding to swap from Tesco. In comparison, this app is buggy - it closed down and stopped working 4 times during a single sitting when doing my shop, all prompted when using the search function. Hopefully fixes will be applied otherwise I'll probably look at other supermarkets as a shopping app that works well is a big requirement for me.

Poor - for the second time it has just shown my basket is empty while I'm changing an order (but it shows ok on the web). Product images are low quality compared to web. No option to print an order. The menu items to report a bug or suggest an improvement are currently doing nothing. Update July 2022. Still not good... Sorting of Favourites by "category" is terrible - the categories are very poorly chosen with many items in wrong category or categories just stupid. Now just crashed on checkout.

The app is good, but there is a huge range and variety in store. What's available online has been stripped back, and many items aren't available. I found this out with 5 minutes of using the app, where several of my staple foods aren't available, and I will have to go into the store to buy them anyway, thus rendering the app, and the online delivery service, worthless to me. This was my experience of online ordering around 7 year ago, with other retailers as well. Its a shame this is still a prob

Very temperamental. Won't always let you checkout or make changes to your order. I've had the same issues on two separate devices; wasted an hour today having to start everything from scratch. Also cannot use e-gift cards through the app had to checkout again through the laptop.

Not allowing me to select a slot for 2 days now. Can click time then when I click reserve it does nothing. Or, something's says try again. I click that to no avail. Have deleted cache and reinstalled - no change. App's been a real pain, this is just the latest. Constantly having to tab out of it to clear screens, redo commands etc. Changing your slot's not an obvious option either. Please look at Tesco app, which is very smooth.

We used to use this app for our regular shop but it seems to be getting more and more glitchy. To the point where I spent ages booking a slot, filling my basket, only to have a constant loading circle when trying to pay. When refreshing the app, I found it hadn't even acknowledged the booking of the slot never mind the basket. Please sort this out ASAP, surely this is a critical part of your service now? I'll be going to a competitor with a good app in the meantime.

The app navigation is built for iPhone users who need to have a back button added to apps. Android users already have a native back button but the app just does not work well if you use it. Use any type of page that updates data and the native back button gives you a horrible experience. No such issue with Tesco!

Slow & laggy. Often unable to amend online orders on the app and have to do it via the website. Would like more input re: substitutions. Tesco & Waitrose apps both have a note feature to input substitutions info. 19/8/22 Edited to add that since posting the above the app is even worse. Stuck on a picture of an orange trolly, can't navigate away & only solution to uninstall/reinstall.

Fairly awful. I downloaded this so I could assist with my mother's shopping remotely. I find it less intuitive to use than some other comparable apps - that's fine, I can deal with that, but it does mean my less tech-savvy mother finds it hard to use. Her ability to use the app is compounded by the many glitches we encounter using it. As a result she'll frequently think she's done something wrong, when it's actually the app. I'd expect more from Sainsbury's.

Used to work fine but now takes ages to first load up even when on connected to fibre broadband. Puts you off using it. Also once you have placed an order they make you go a really long way around to open that order up and change it. Other than those two huge issues it's very good

I normally like shopping with Sainsbury's app and find it easy. It has some shortcomings as other users pointed out but for someone who shops every single week, the most frustrating thing of all is that I am unable to check out through the app any more! It's been more than a month now that there is an issue with bank verification stage of the check out and in order to do so, you have to go to the website! That is defeating the object of the having an APP. Please fix it otherwise I suspect you will lose customers, me included. (App developers: Please don't ask me to email you with this issue as I am sure you are well aware of it by now.)
replyContent:
Hi Natasha, 

Thanks for taking the time to get in touch and sorry for the difficulties you've been experiencing. It looks like you're using quite an old version of our app - are you able to download the most up to date version and let us know if you're still having issues?

Thanks again,
Sainsbury's GOL App Team

content: Unreliable... Keeps freezing, dreadful lag... Keep having to clear cache and refresh the app, then it skips and jumps and the orange symbol goes round and round. Recently updated this app too and it keeps asking me to log in! I continually put in correct log in details and after 8 attempts its finally logged me in. Rubbish app.

It is very disappointing that the pictures are soooo small. I want to check the lable of a prosecco to see if it's dry but as I can't zoom there is no way to check. Nothing in the description of course. Same with nutritions on the back - there is never a picture of it
replyContent:
Hi there,

Thanks very much for getting in touch to share your feedback - we are constantly working to improve our app and we think your suggestion of having zoomable images is great - it's on our list! Please do continue to share your thoughts and feedback with us ‚Äì we really do appreciate it!

Thanks,
Sainsbury's App Team

content: What happened to showing whether an item was available or not ? Theres been a change for the worse so now I have to guess if an item is available ... Clicking add and then being told no in a modal popup is rubbish. If this is the price of progress then can we have an explanation as to how this is better for the customer and not easier for your back end developers ?

This app is too complicated which should not be. At the checkout the voucher should appeared and available to just click to claim. I can not find 'My coupon wallet' here either! When change the order it should be able to just update the order rather then having to checkout again. Annoying at times! That's why I don't shop too often here!

Complain and complain but no one is listenning, nothing changes! For crying out loud fix your app - PLEASE! It's so full of gliches, frequant basket errors, crashes frequantly or app just won't open, poor search engine, items not listed that are in. (Should mention no problems with anyone else.)Try Sains large frozen prawns 250g - it won't put them in basket saying 'basket error', click open item for info and the app crashes! Why? Its soo infuriating especially when you really want that item.

Disappointed. Has never worked properly on tablet device or Samsung phone. Crashes often and says I am not connected to internet but I am. Can't see all coupons or vouchers on there. Have to log out after every shop or payment crashes. No reminder if you forget to check out and slot is lost. Search function awful with in stock item's often never even shown.

Very hit and miss since last update. Often doesnt log in, just spins 'loading' and gets no further. Also often doesnt let you complete check out so end up having to log on to a PC to complete shop. Defeats the object of an easy access app. Please fix.

Constantly logs me out (no I am not clearing cache or data). Doesn't work with password managers (lastpass). Forces one-time password / token through email and Doesn't allow apps (Google authenticator or authy). Inconveniences but needing to log in every. Single. Time. I. Open. The. App... can be tedious to say the least. Would give 4 stars otherwise. Pretty standard ui that works without being cumbersome. Product images could be larger or allow for zooming in.

Unfortunately the app is full of bugs, often freezing when you try to check out or amend your order and items you originally put on the shop are made unavailable when you go in to add something on to the shop.. it's very clunky and rather disappointing. Update dosnt appear to have improved it much!

The new app was not easy to use. It kept coming up with basket error. Also at checkout it wanted to offer alternative as one item was no longer available. I did not want the alternative but until I went back and removed the old item from my basket it would not let me check out. Did not like the updated version.

Have used this app for a long time but in the last year have experienced numerous problems. Each time have reported problem and been told it would be reported to the IT Department and they would get back to me. No-one has ever got back to me. Eventually I am able to get back on the app. Have been a Sainsburys customer for over 40 years but seriously considering changing to another Supermarket

I really dislike being forced to update an app. I had the same problem as others, when I updated the app, it kept telling me I need to update. So I uninstalled the app and reinstalled. I was then able to login... after hunting for the verification email in spam. I have recently returned to shopping with Sainsbury's, so I'm not impressed
Constantly having to log out and uninstall and install just to get it to work. Adding on to an order takes ages, annoying message of Oops something went wrong keeps popping up.

The app 'could' be great. Searching is difficult, if you spell a product wrong is doesn't recognise it at all rather than a 'did you mean?' Adding multiple same items is laggy. Amending your order is a NIGHTMARE! & we need to see the same product reviews as on the website.

Always have to re open so it goes straight to my account When searching it goes back to my basket so I have to re search Now it won't let me checkout, it's just buffering, so I have to start up my laptop to make sure I finish the order And the new page that opens when something isn't available is not good, literally doesn't take you to any page of the app.

The app does not seem to load very well. I often have to close it, stop it from running and start again otherwise it just doesn't work. Half the time the pictures of the products do not load and when they do load, they're poor quality.

Latest update fails to checkout ? Life is far too short for this . No logging out when item unavailable and somehow swapping the subs . Previous update not sorted out errors in loading, peculiar search results or display of item count in trolley. Repeatedly fails to complete booking of a selected delivery slot ? The stress is mounting! Previously, checking out made tedious as ap pushing more purchases. Also the repeated substitution option is moot given the lack of certain products .

Compared to main competitors this is poor Its fine if you're logged in (you often get logged out) and you do your shop and that's it The problem is when you go back later to tweak your order. Often when you try to checkout again you get told you've lost your slot. The website works better on my laptop than using the app, which feels old fashioned

This app drives me mad. It is always crashing!! Edit: YET AGAIN today, I booked a slot before shopping, and on checking out 20 minutes later, was asked to book a slot, thus losing my original slot. Additionally, all of the offers that had been on during my shop were no longer there once I checked out...within 20 minutes.

Recently the app has become unusable. Search/browse functions don't work properly - for example when I browse ice cream tubs only one item shows up. The same thing happens for several other products, in many cases there are no products found for common items.

Quite difficult to add one off items to the order without checking out again. If there are ANY issues with an order, the only option is to call Sainsbury's, which is really difficult as they don't answer the phone. They don't have an email address, and the customer service team cannot help via Twitter. Ocado is FAR superior.

Still very slow to add items to your basket & regularly crashes or doubles up items if you try to add any quantity higher than 1. Not worth using - stick to the desktop version unless you have time to double check every item line by line after you've added it.

Very temperamental on payments. once checked out & you want to add just 1 item more to the order you have to go through entire processagain, morrisons are great at this with their one click process you can add to any pre-booked dates without having to go through checkout again. If Sainsbury's could sort this out this would be great

Not sure if the issue is app or staff. But the fix could be done in the app. Keep getting substitutes that are not declared by the app. Example: substitutes are non vegetarian alternative to a vegetarian product. Not too hard to add diet subs into the app and would prevent drivers having to do refunds. Customer service for app based purchases is also sub par. Sainsburys is making improvements in its digital interface but lags the competition with its app and understanding its customers.

The app is terrible..When you make changes to an order it sometimes wont let you checkout and you cant keep the changes unless you check out! ive added some items to the basket and been trying to checkout for 20 minutes. every time i tap checkout it takes me to the screen that tells me i must checkout to save changes. because of this palava every week i have stopped spending my ¬£80 quid a week here and will give it to morrisons instead!

Not there yet, missing half of my favourites in new app, and when opening a product for info keeps returning to the top of the page instead of current item reached. Given up using the app and continuing shop on the desktop. Having just read other reviews I'm pleased I gave up trying to use the so called improved and updated app!

Has utterly stopped working. Can't scan in at any store. I downloaded and deleted and downloaded again multiple times. The chop chop app also has double charged me on more than one occasion. I get promised a refund but it never appears. This app has not worked since the last update.

Works well while choosing products, but trying to check out is a nightmare. There's some kind of glitch in the software that means you have to click it dozens of times before it works. A message comes up saying that you need to confirm the address used by Uber Eats, but then doesn't let you confirm the address. Are Uber Eats now delivering Sainsbury orders?? Its happened several times now when putting in an order or updating an existing order.

Since the update the pages keeps jumping when scrolling, it's extremely annoying. Pervious to this I have had trouble checking out on several occasions, it looks like other people have had the same problem!

Search function is erratic and unreliable.. this app is your shop window it should be perfect .. ie Search for 'Sainsbury's fish fingers' I got 609 results with everything that mentioned a finger or fish... Like chocolates, gloves, cat food, Bread, Fruit. I can't be bothered to mention anymore, but it was ridiculous. Even so it is an improvement on before.... A while back when I tried the same search, it included everything that mentioned Sainsbury's That search results We're in the thousands .
everything is difficult. Sometimes it doesn't even work. When it does loading times are horrible. Booking of slots is very unintuitive and prices are unclear. An app from a past era.

The app is a pain to use for myself most of the time. For some reason there is a issue with typing products into search bar on my phone, it stops typing what I want to type on a frequent basis making the process of ordering slow.

Decent app, but quite a few issues recently. Can't modify order, it always says website issue when checking out changes. Sainsbury weekly nectar bonus points vouchers not available in application, it's very inconvenient to switch between shopping app and otherwise useless nectar card app to find the vouchers

App malfunctioning - having been a well functioning app, it has now become unstable. Problems when selecting products - won't add them to the basket, returning nonsensical 'basket errors' - and problems when booking delivery or click/collect slots DAYS in advance when it returns another odd error that its past some cutoff time.

I like to be able to see the images of my items once I have added them to basket. Unfortunately this is not possible with this app. This has been an ongoing problem and one of the reasons I usually order from tesco. Their app is a lot more user friendly.

Unstable platform. Errors are fairly common, unable to save your shop, lose your slot altogether, cannot checkout as an item fails but does not show which one. Some bits are good like the favourites and being able to book without plastic bags

Doesn't deal with things becoming unobtainable well. Just had to abandon all my changes when it got stuck and wouldn't check out. It kept asking me to change the delivery slot which would have been a disaster.

Hard work, hate that when checking out it tells me my slot is no longer available, always gives me a heartattack! So clunky. Would be good if all items were on here. Would be good to have 'find similar' on items too rather than clicking back several times to find the search
Constantly unreliable. Slow, unresponsive, and very frustrating to use. If it's not sorted out soon, then I am seriously thinking of changing to a different supermarket online app !

I've only just switched to Sainsburys after using Asda for a long time but I have to say the app is nowhere near as good as the Asda one. you could potentially be losing customers because it has so many glitches. It's hit and miss as to whether it works most days. Once it decides to work it seems fine. Better than the web site.

The app is constantly letting me down. You try to checkout and the timing icon goes round and round. You cannot checkout and the time you have sent adding items to your trolley is a total waste of time. Don't bother with the app.

The time I have wasted using the inconsistent search facility. I entered pickled eggs and I had 895 items to choose from. I later asked for eggs I got 14 items to choose from all were eggs only eggs no pickled eggs no scotch eggs no other varient of eggs. Please sort out the inconsistencies of the search parameters. So frustrating I can only give 2 stars.

The app will not save delivery preferences. I do not change the position of my kitchen between shops, or even when I change slot! No matter how often you save, it clears next shop (and then the driver complains about having to move to the other door)!

So so slow recently! Takes ages to show search results meaning a shop takes forever. Items I add to basket and see increase the cost of my shop mysteriously never make it to the checkout. This only becomes apparent when the item(s) don't appear at point of collection in my shop or on my receipt.

Well, I expect more analysis capability, on my previous spending, and the wider market actually! Also there is no way to scan an item thats finsihed reorder it. Voice recognition would be lovely "hey Google add Robinsons orange and pineapple squash to my groceries list". Also i cannot add clothes and other stuff sainsburys sell to my groceries - which is a shame. Good effort, Must try harder.

Will not connect to my account. Was working brilliantly, I set up a delivery pass to make life easier and since then I have to log in every time through the website and that sometimes takes more than one attempt. Coincidence maybe but a real pain!

If you amend a placed order when you have items in your basket, it deletes your basket contents once you've saved the existing order changes. It's infuriating. A 'one click' order feature like ocado has would be better - it's way to faffy to add items to placed orders.

Terrible problems for 2 weeks-app is useless now. You can't book slots for upcoming dates as it tells you its past the cutoff. Would not add items to my basket on the last 2 slots, so I've had a useless shop as it wouldn't even load the page to add or even checkout.SORT IT OUT SAINSBURYS!!!!

Doesn't work too well. Have to use the website. Complained twice. Had zero response. - issue being once I have ordered, I cannot access orders or amend them, app tells me I'm not connected to the Internet! I think I am after non stop Internet use! This is not an isolated incident, it is what I now expect from the app. If it starts to work properly I'd be very surprised. Love sainsburys, hate their rubbish app. Website is only just marginally less clunky.

Sainsbury's food and service is great... This app though, not so great. Checking out when items are out of stock is a nightmare, constant crashing when trying to replace items out of stock from a previous basket.
The load when opening the app is terrible. I've tried through multiple connections and 7-10 seconds is too slow for me, I've forgotten what i was going to add to my order by then!!

Extremely annoying that the app doesn't show previous orders properly. When selecting a previous order I want to see what I bought, at what price and what substitutions Sainsbury's made to my order. Instead I see only a list of items that Sainsbury's wants me to buy again. Why? This functionality is already covered by the "favourites".

Its like all the other online shopping apps, but, it does not retain my password, and i have to login again, wait for code. This happens to many times, and considering i use this app for my mums shopping, the code goes to her email account, and she cant use her email (she is 89) and i don't live with her, so it means i cant order food until i go round to open up her emails on her tablet to get the code. Somewhat frustrating!
You can't add e-gift cards via the app. Only through the website.

Been ordering weekly for a month now. Every order times out with 'Processing' which never finishes. The layout and usabilty are somehow worse than the mobile site!? Also, no reviews of products are shown in the app.... Going to stick to the site in future - just hope that works, or it's back to Tesco I'll be forced to go...

Unpredictable This app is so frustrating! Too often it buffers for ages or gets stuck. (my WiFi is fine & every other app is ok, so it's not a connection issue) The only solution is to uninstall/reinstall. Annoying when trying to amend an online shop before cut-off time. It's been like this for some time and nothing appears to have been rectified.
No offers because I can't sign in
It's got a lot of functionality and if it didn't hang all the time I'd have given it 5 stars.
Why can't I book a slot? The app seems not to be working for the last 3 days.
Can't see a way to review, or even read the reviews.
Having issues with amending order.

Cannot book a delivery slot despite slots being available because i keep getting message that I must remove products from my basket as not available. Message does not tell me which these products are so how am I supposed to know ? Very frustrating and I cannot place my order. 4thJune update. APP has not worked for past 2 weeks. I keep getting error message or app just stops. Have reported this 4 times and told someone would get back to me to help fix it but they dont.. Unsatisfactory..
Why is there nothing listed under "Sugar & home baking"? Two updates later, still nothing displaying - minus another star
I haven't been able to book a delivery slot for 2 days as it just keeps saying try again

The App is useful for comparing prices to other supermarkets and for shopping. But, it takes too long to use functionally for shopping on, compared to other supermarkets (W & T). There's no way of saving Favourites, only removing them once bought. 2/5 is being generous!
You can't add e-gift cards via the app. Only through the website.
Constantly having to log out and uninstall and install just to get it to work. Adding on to an order takes ages, annoying message of Oops something went wrong keeps popping up.
