I cannot find a way to request a refund in app.

Have been using the app for years, never really had too many issues with it, but for the last week or two I haven't been able to log into my account and uninstalling/reinstalling doesn't fix it. Hopefully there'll be a fix for this soon.
The gripe that I have is being unable to add coupons or gift card through app
Constantly having to log in on a day to day and now I can't log in at all.
Dislike because they force people to update

Happy with the overall shopping experience after moving from Morrisons however there are two major limitationd compared to their app. Firstly, there is no quick 'Add to order' button on a product. Secondly, the wife and I cannot both edit the same basket without it getting its knickers in a twist (the basket dies not seem to be held online until you checkout again so the other phone won't show the updated order until that point.
It's OK to search and select but if you go to the trolley, it keeps duplicating each entry. I have to log onto the website to check my trolley order in single entries.
Up from a 1 star 6 months ago 3.5
Do not have an option to spend nectar points online without calling customer services ... annoying and long

I have on/off problems with this App...and one most recently... wanted to amend my shopping couldn't add anything it kept saying its after 11pm it wasn't,early evening... ended up cancelling the order... and managed to get a slot with another supermarket... please get this app sorted ...

Don't like that it makes me log in from scratch every time I launch the app now. I can appreciate the double level of security the first time you login, but surely not every single time you use the app. Not only does the app ask me to log in every time but it now needs a security code to be emailed to me each time too.

Love Sainsburys, but frustrated that they started giving out marvel cards to collect, so we got interested in collecting them, I bought the collectors book, then they stopped giving out the cards, disappointing
You could learn a trick from Aldi, with their tray liner

Normally have no issues, we order for collection and ordering is no problem. But lately sometimes whole sections won't load...such as today the sugar and baking section... previously it was laundry...also the search is getting ridiculous, even when I'm very specific I still end up with a hundred items with nothing to do with item such as searching for caster sugar it came up with baked beans
First class

App is pretty intuitive to use but this is occasionally spoilt by UX bugs (e.g. cannot see search text entry box if there are lots of search suggestions) and lagginess. My main bugbear is: why can't I pay with vouchers or giftcards in the app?
Slow but effective
App is good but there should be delivery tracker to track the orders..as I faced problems many a times where delivery came late..and I have been not informed and made us wait 1 hour extra...very bad
Glitchy
Keeps Doubling up items
It always logs you out of your account, no recent update for Android and just not entirely user friendly
When it actually comes to having your grocery shop delivered its excellent.
Quite often cannot access this site presumably as it is busy. Never a problem with Tesco. When inputting numbers required of an item the app struggles to keep up and even appears to work backwards.

Normally this app is fantastic. For the last few weeks it won't even open. Just stuck on the basket loading icon. When I finally get in I try to search and it starts errroing again. Please fix the issues.
Disabling substitution items dosn't work.
Not sure I it's my phone or not but it keeps kicking me out when I try to log in. When I'm logged in I can't add to basket
Fix the app its abit of a nightmare to book things on
When the app is working it's very user-friendly but recently there have been issues that mean you can't add items to your basket or book a delivery slot. Frustrating.
Summary of items costs in final order is not easy to understand. Except for total order cost. Promotion savings not itemised in bill.
Does not seem to keep my favourites one week they are there the next they are not
Why can't we have a " nite" section like Tesco?????
Continuous faults but you can get an order done
Where are the product reviews?
Telling me to update so I have..then saying app is no longer available update it which I've done twice grrrr never had a problem before??? What's going on here
Questionable usefullness I fail to receive the items making me use the app contnuously, which makes me question the reason of the app's existance.

Annoying- no warning of a time lapse on placing an order in the chosen slot. Got to end of my large order and checked out only to find out my slot for tomorrow was no longer in existence I wasted an hour of my time choosing what I need for tomorrow.... seriously not hard to code customer notifications to warn them you shut down orders post 11am even if selected... please think of the client experience when developing apps.
Items in basket have started duplicating for some reason?
Blurb
App was slow, when I amended an order i couldn't check out. Updated app but you need to clear your cache and data for it to function correctly.
Good app..but sometimes they provide wrong products

Since using this app I have experienced a few problems. Last week there was an issue that meant all products were showing as unavailable and I couldn't update my order before delivery. Today I am unable to book a slot that is showing as available! Very frustrating.
Can't login after an update! Had to uninstall and reinstall to use the app.
Some option appear to be missing (e-receipt)
Much better now that they've changed the login method.

Fairly good app. It would be better if I could view my trolley by department, at the moment goods are added in random order. I'd like all my veg together, all frozen together, etc. It makes for an easier shop when you can see at a glance what you're missing..
Whenever I have used thus App it does not let me pay as the "website is not available". I have then lost the delivery slot I've reserved. This is very irritating.

We've just switched from Ocado and a glaring omission in this app compared to theirs is that there is no "one click add" button. Everytime to want to add something to your basket you have to log in, add it, then check out again.

Review based on the app rather than food quality/availability (which has been hit and miss lately). App often has bugs; the latest of which is where items that are unavailable are no longer flagged as such. Instead, adding it to trolley brings up a confusing message about the item being added successfully but also that unavailable items have a warning and have not been added. The experience of finding that many of my favourite items are unavailable is somehow even more frustrating now.

App regards punctuated delivery instructions in plain English as "invalid characters". I've news for you, Sainsbury's - a full stop is a necessary character for clear directions for country addresses. Also 170 chars not enough. Get your act together, you're not helping your drivers and are trailing Tesco on this one.

It seems to have a lot of connection issues. You just never know, after having loaded your basket, if you will be able to checkout or not. Kind of annoying. The navigation is fine, but the connection bugs need work.
Would give a much higher rating if the recipes section of the website was better linked with the app... other than that the app performs well.
Easy to use. Search results do not show all examples. Do not know how long promotions last for.
The app is ok. The substitute policy is not. They will give you an offer and then substitute offer item with double the price nonoffer one.
No ability to refund from app?

Design ok, poor user experience. It's easy to navigate and use, but it is glitchy and slow to load or often will not load a page. Checkout process sometimes goes round in circles. Search function could definitely be improved, often does not find products even if you type in the exact name. There's an issue that it often says things are unavailable that I know are on the shelves, probably a stock management issue rather than the app itself.
Slow to load and clunky at times. Not as clear as it could be. Delivery slots all over the place
Struggling to load pages
Could be better but decent enough.
Is good but a bit buggy
Will not ever allow me to spend Nectar points can only do it instore
Can't find the way to accept/ not accept substitutes
Really good app and easy to use. Would be 5/5 if you could amend your order.
Expensive

I do actually like this for shopping, however you really need to fix the issue where the ability to make changes to your basket just disappears. This happens when you try and log in online as well but very frustrating the day before your order is due and you need to make changes!
Couldnt check out at all ,rang them , go through there web page sigh in on that site and you can check out on there ,üëçiv deleted the app and redo later
App often hangs up leaving order uncompleted.
The app keeps logging out. Randomly shows errors when trying to checkout. The app doesn't allow the toggling of substitutions like the website does.
Great if you never want to change your order... When I do try and change it it's 50/50 whether it'll have a complete melt down and mess up/not let me check out.
Keeps locking up. And also when trying to checkout it just doesn't do anything so have to keep going to the website to check out. Very frustrating
Sometimes wont let me checkout when I'm updating a shop
Never connects
Very clunky and unreliable

Generally very good but the basket listing just shows items in order bought rather than being grouped by department/shelf making it tricky to see all vegetables bought etc. Could also do with a "Same shelf" function to list related products.
Unable to checkout on Samsung Tablet for the last few weeks. I can book a slot and add items to the basket but can't check out. I have to use my Samsung phone to actually checkout, it's a nuisance!
App constantly resets losing your orders, so you have to go to website. Painful to use
Good Why Why
Temperamental
Keeps crashing and looks a little untidy

This App is frustrating to use. Firstly it logs me out nearly every time, so I have to log in each time I go into it. Also it crashes randomly and I have to go I to App setting and force it to close. The trolley does not order the products in any way, so it is hard to check you have any duplicates/have too little veg etc Poor descriptions... images are small and not to scale so hard to work out which is the size you want... easy to end up ordering the wrong size of a product.. Could do better.
Sometimes will not allow basket to be updated.
Glitchy
Extremely erratic
App unstable, service good.
It's ok but can be a bit glitchy.
I normally have no issue with the site or delivery... But it keeps crashing when I go to update my basket! Not great when it constantly does it on the last day before delivery! Please fix!
Sometimes difficult to get on.
Not good enough

Used for first time, normally use Tesco and this app is below their standard. It's a bit laggy, no option to add a note to the picker for individual items but most of all, there is no end date for the promotion's so I've no idea if I will get the item at the discounted rate come delivery. Tesco not only tell u the end date of the promotion but will prompt you at checkout if it ends before your delivery and u remove it. This would be helpful! The confirmation email format is also not great.
Was good, tried to amend now told website not working so it's stuck

No thought is given to previous purchases when a chosen item is not available on delivery day. To add an item to an existing order, it is necessary to edit the order and go through the entire checkout process again. Why not just have the 'add to order' facility as others do. Also, not possible to have more than one order in the system so weekly shops are not possible Customer service by phone cannot be faulted, however but online chat is non-existent
Very limited, cannot amend a delivery date/time and not easy to apply any vouchers
Can't check out! I've uninstalled app and reinstalled still the same issue, deleted cache., still the same issue üòî
I found it difficult to amend order or change a payment. It is far from easy. Perhaps it's time to update for your customers

Could there please add a logo or text on each product to know what is veg/vegan and halal. Because I am unsure if I can get particular items or not. I rather not take the risk and wouldn't buy them. I'm sure I'm not the only one talking about this. Please do somthing. Thank you
How about having a feature to sync to Calendar/gmail?
Problems trying to link Nectar card. App doesn't want to know. Linking Nectar to Ebay was so easy!
Can't manage delivery passes or orders in app
Does the job but quite slow, especially when completing orders.
Very unstable. Can't always get straight back to current order
To slow far to many problems
I just used to shopping there. I like the sainsbury's.
Try reporting item in store not on line app just takes you around in circles
Annoying that I have to frequently login to my account when I open the app. It seems to log me out if I login on my laptop to add items to my trolley. Please fix this!
Moved to Sainsbury's because the Ocado app is still not available 10 months after it crashed at the start of the pandemic. This app is fine when it works, but often won't open.

Since the latest update it's now really annoying as I regularly jumps so you end up ordering the wrong thing. It's like the lost is constantly updating so it jumps as new thing are added, really frustrating.
Cant seem to make a list that I can use each time I order but otherwise cant complain

Great when it works. Randomly it will log you out and you have to log in again just as you start shopping. Today it wouldn't recognise the scan code for loose carrots and then froze. Couldn't use it any more. Had to unpack my shopping and go through the checkout. I don't have a car so have to use half hourly bus service. Don't have time to fiddle about with an app that doesn't always work.
Not sure yet ( new custumer)
Impossible to browse. Christmas list for example keeps rolling forward. Have to keep on scrolling backwards to see what I've missed.
Good app but can't add current basket into next order so either have to remember list or go into order and amend each time - a pain! Also app won't work when I have VPN switched on - why??
Delivery slots malfunction alot so have to go onto website.

Overall, the app works well. It would be great if you could add substitution notes like Tesco. The weekly Nectar points offers no longer show the date they expire, which is very frustrating. The other annoyance was that my Nectar card was unlinked from the app with no notification so after several weeks of puzzling over why I couldn't spend my points I eventally managed to reinstate it.

Overall shopping experience is ok but the app is not always intuitive, for example when adding favorites. Can't seem to find a way of having bespoke shopping baskets ready to go. So far no big issues with stock at our Sainsbury.
Easy access, runs well on my android phone. Just wish Sainsbury's would allow delivery slot booking more than two weeks at a time.
I've used the app for many years and the only criticism would be that not all of the produce that are available in the supermarket are available in the app.
First time using online grocery shopping. Time consuming initially, both to set up and to navigate. However, should be easier with more use.

Great that you can make changes right up to the night before. I've found it really easy after a couple of gos as I'm not that great with apps, very impressed with the whole service. Been struggling for months to add nectar card, still not sure if its linked and unable to access yet. Not everyone is a wizard on phones, less impressed now.

Gets stuck at a crucial part of the checking out screen sometimes and scares me, as I've just invested time and consideration into my order, and feel like I'm about to lose the lot. But that's not actually happened so far. I may have to back out of a swirling 'processing order' screen, and luckily find that everything went through ok after all. Feel a tad sorry for iPhone users. If it wasn't for this little glitch, I'd definitely give 5 stars as the app itself is superb. Very intuitive and easy.

My shopping experiences have been very positive. shopping arrives on time and the range is fab, better than Tesco who seem to be dropping many old brands. The app is quite well laid out and works quite well most of the time. It does however sometimes throw a page not found error, for that reason i rated it 4 stars. I would like to see better categorisation. Clear and logical structure to sections such as table sauces and vegan. I hope these improvements can come, perhaps via a beta programme?

Some things I would like in the app : search ability in your trolley; trolley listed in groups I.e fresh frozen etc; don't have 'go to trolley' and 'empty basket' in the same space! Too easy to make a mistake!

First time using this app and yes I was thrilled fond all the items I wanted and savings prices then I checked out with Simple verifie then on the day of delivery all items where available no substitute driver was happy and helpful will be using again cheaper prices then other stores.

I find this app relatively easy to use. I particularly like that you can click on the product and get so much information before you buy. It is not so easy instore when you are proving to be an obstacle to other shoppers. If I could improve the app I would try to make it possible to add an alternative should a product be unavailable. So far the alternatives made for me have been rejected or given away. I now block all alternatives with few exceptions.

I read a few reviews before i downloaded the app and i feel they may either be a bit outdated or just not true. I find the app really easy to use with no real issues, i had an issue with an item that was delivered and was able to get a refund via the app without having to make a call etc. I think its a really good app, i only gave four stars as some items that i know are available in store aren't on the app, i would say thats the only issue i have found.

This app makes online grocery shopping very easy. I have had a couple of issues when updating an order which meant I had to login via the website to complete the checkout, but these appear to be resolved now. I would like to see calendar integration so that deliveries and collections are automatically added to my calendar (like the Tesco app). I like the way I can easily remove items from my favourites (unlike the Tesco app).
Generally very good, had a few hours when payment would take and siblost slot and lost all my saved recipes. More monthly recipes for main suppers .thank you.
Overall just fine but for some reason there's no option to read reviews from within the app. If I want to see these I have to access the website via Google & then that option is readily available.
Good service, simple, always on time

Better than it used to be. Used to lag / not always synchronise / payment thing not always complete. Not had these problems last few months. I would like there to be a function where you can actively save your favourite items or create lists as a reference for future orders, rather than the app just allocating as a favourite if you've bought it a few times etc.
Almost perfect - when going through favourites wish one could get back to where you had left when checking an item over then returning to favourites.

The favourites is mostly everything you have ever ordered. It's easy to search for other items you need and you can either add or remove a favourite just by clicking the heart in the corner. Updating preferences for substitutes is pretty easy too.The new ability to save the order to your calender is great although the title needs changing as the default is that a delivery is coming. My only issue with it is that there isn't a finger print login for mobile, still have to go to email for code.
I understand security is very much an issue and is even more so as time goes on. I am finding it easy to make a mistake with the number of items to put in to prove it is me.

Easy to use, can switch between app and website during shopping. Favourites is handy unless they relist something then you lose items. You can build up your list over the month as and when you think of things to put in your basket. It supports dark theme. A bit buggy at times though.

Vastly improved search function that allows you to return to the search bar for editing to find similarly named products and variants, instead of having to start from scratch with every search. Some products are still not found, but this is not down to the app, but to data entry.

Great updates to the app this week! Checkout was a lot cleaner and smoother. Also found it easier to find what I was looking for when loading my basket. Just need to be able to book and manage multiple slots more easily if possible and it will be near perfect. Look forward to the next update!

I do really like this app but there are 3 things that would make it better. I would like to be able to sort my favourites by custom order so I can have recipes or have breakfast, lunch and dinner in order. I would also like to be able to add a product to my favourites as I am searching. Finally, if I could save products into recipes for quick adding.

Almost perfect. The only thing that needs sorting is the shopping cart, sometimes the images of the items doesn't show - while glancing through it makes it tricky to see what I have and haven't added without reading each of them.

Easy to use only sometimes difficult finding item via search as the most weird products are included for a simple product! It would be good if there was a note option in the substitute part to explain you want say green bananas or a very small size sweet potato as I've been sent absolute giant and and brown bananas! Otherwise excellent thank you.

Very good, great that you can purchase from the whole stores range... even non food and non grocery items. great its stores previous orders. did crash a couple times during use. and would be nice to have alternatives suggested when browsing what you have selected

I'm too old for modern technology I need it to be simple as the previous app. I am very happy with the service from your help line they have been brilliant. I do not want to phone an order I like to browse because I forget things due to my age (90). please keep things simple.

Update 28/02/2021 The app has definitely been improved, it's smoother and has less bugs. Still has more work to do, but heading in the right direction. The app needs to include everything that the website offers in a grocery shop, find that something's are not shown ok the app which isn't helpful.

Easy to use app, only problem is I use the shop nearest to where I work, but the app changes it to the one closest to my address (even after I have set it to my preferred store) which is 15 miles out of the way and of no convenience to me, should make it easier to set a preferred shop for click and collect, as have not realised the change until gone to collect the order and then missed the slot at the other store and had to deal with very stroppy staff!!

Very good app, apart from when i go back to favorites after a search i have to start at the bottom not from where i last was in the favorites list.bit of a pain when 250 objects to scroll through. Other than that a great app. Would be nice if the password could be finger print authenticated saves having to remember it occasionally.

I was dubious at first, but now I much prefer the app to the website. Its so much quicker and easier to use. I'm glad I decided to give it a go. You can move backwards and forwards through the different shelves without having to go right back to the beginning which is what I found frustrating with the website. Its also good that the Nectar app can be linked to this app.

Pretty great, the only thing to make it great is if the basket could be organised into fridge/freezer/cupboard/cleaning etc to make it easier to spot if you've put similar items over time into your basket(as soon as I run out of anything I'm straight to the app to add to my basket so it's there when I finally make the order). Other than that I'm more than happy with it

Midweek delivery pass. Changed from 3 month to annual cos it does what it says on the tin. 4.5 stars really. Check price charged v offer price, can have glitch. After 4 deliveries I'm impressed I can use on android phone & MacBook. Easy to amend, thank goodness. Constant updates to confirm. I rate this app for my needs, 2 weekly delivery.

The service itself is good and I have never had a problem with it. you are able to amend your order until 11pm on the night before delivery. Like most food delivery services they tend to send foods close to the expire date. There is also a just a good mainstream selection, where as going in-store you are able to find products they dont sell online. Anything damaged is refunded straight away as the delivery persons check yr delivery or wait for you to do so.

Easy to use, intuitive, quick - makes my life easier. However, when you delete something from your shopping list it reorders the list of products which makes it hard to review your basket before updating it.

The app is quite easy and straight forward to navigate. Have had three orders so far and all have gone very smoothly. Just had one rather strange substitution but was forewarned in confirmation email and returned to driver on day of delivery.

The BIG shop done from home. During all of these lockdown(s) Sainsbury's have made sure 85% of the stuff we order turns up. The app works well to help get to the stuff you need quickly as well as browsing the isles if that's your thing. I like some of the recommendations offered but there are always personal choices everyone could comment on. If they could do a stock list of what I have in my house so I knew what I had left would be great so I'm not looking through the freezer for things used.

Generally very good, but you have to keep your eyes on it as sometimes it makes multiple additions when it says about an error in adding something to the basket. It would be also very useful if it told me that if an item was in stock and if not offer me an alternative.

Like it as just stopped using tescos but few.things I miss from that all is If you got a order and not clicked change you see something you haven't got the option to add to the order without going to that order before you scan it Nice to have a bar code scanner so when you run out just scan the product then it will bring it up and then you add it to the order But nice app like it so far

Been using this for quite some time. Usually does everything I need, only one major glitch that even the helpline had never come across, but they were very helpful in putting things right. Straightforward easy to use app, would recommend.

Great app. I love how quickly you can add things to your shop and the app updates with items you buy in-store too. One improvement would be to make it clear where we can add e-vouchers. Other than that great little app - shopping at your finger tips.

Great app, use it to make a shopping list then get the shop sent to us when there is a cheap slot. There are too many "favourites" even if you've only ordered something once it becomes a favourite, which seems ridiculous to me.
replyContent:
Thanks very much for your feedback Stacey, we're glad you're enjoying the app. And thanks for your suggestion on our Favourites feature - it's on our list! 
Thanks again,
Sainsbury's App Team

content: Only the second time I have ordered i was not aware you had to put your address in for delivery again I assumed it would be automatic unless otherwise stated. My groceries would have gone to the local shop if I hadn't checked. Customer service sorted a delivery, excellent service!!

Pretty good but some technical issues still exist, the latest update has brought new problems When you are scrolling through your favourites list the list jumps to new pages every few seconds, which means you then have to keep scrolling back Really annoying, needs urgent fix (this is on Android Samsung Galaxy S10) 14.1.2021 update ,most bugs seem to have been fixed. I use it every week and it's a breeze to do a online shop

I love the interface, best out of all the shops. But often I load my basket but then the app, (and website) won't let the checkout process complete and I end up losing my delivery slot. So the whole effort is wasted as I have to actually go to the shop anyway.

So far for us is been good...hardly had any substitutes,however some weren't mentioned as being substituted and I had the delivery drivers delivering earlier which for me was fine,for others might be a problem,although they do call 30-60min before. I see they had some app changes,so now the order I am expecting today appears as previews order ....I am unable to track it or check substitutes because of that ...

Generally the orders are covered, there has been the odd item out of stock, there was only one time I never received my order, this was due to snow, and the reason I gave a 4 star rating was due to lake of communication on that day it was not delivered. All veg and fruit are always fresh. All delivery drives are very helpful and polite.

Great app, simple and easy to use, can usually find everything quickly. There is always the odd item that takes a bit of finding but the checkout process is easy and the shopping is far less stressful than doing it in a store!
Very good overall. Cons: too easy to change number of items ordered by mistake while swiping through list. Some searches miss items even though they are there.
Have had a more or less seamless experience. Sometimes the app has crashed on me but no-one is perfect. Browsing and categorisation of items is pretty good and straightforward

Whenever something is highlighted, to read more about it, then the shopping returns to the start! So if am half way through, shopping for cat food,, i high light item number 150, i go back to item 1 and have to scroll through again.

It would be nice if the dietary filters only needed to be applied once, also somewhere to feed back to the actual store who fulfilled my order, so I could inform them where they need to improve, for example my local store just place potatoes loose in the box which isn't the cleanest, also staff don't seem to know the difference between a savoy or sweetheart cabbage.
I do Love shopping with sainsbury I like there food. They have good quality food. Not bad prices to.
No problems at all. Just occasionally out of stock of some items.
Some issues grtting the app to work, may be internet connection!

Overall a good app, occasionally the app seems to have server issues but then most of the apps have an issue from time to time but overall my experience with both the app and delivery of chosen items from Sainsbury's i have found to be a positive experience
Good app and easy to use. The only thing I'd like to see is the ability to quickly add products to an order in process. As it is you can't add a short list, you have to amend the whole order.

Thanks for update overnight. Booking delivery slot much easier! However keep getting "Items are not loading" message floating over the top of favourites, which are loading perfectly. Have screenshot if you want it. Pixel 3 phone.
Like the shop it's not always perfect
The website as been really slow lately when trying to place orders so I downloaded the app and so far it has been a good experience. Much quicker and quite easy to navigate.
Usually a straightforward process. Sometimes locks account when an item in the basket is not available at checkout. Can work round it now. Altogether a good experience.

Overall Sainsburys are a decent ccmpany to deal with. Generally reliable but last week they cancelled deliveries to my area due to traffic at the local agricultural show - They didn't inform us in advance ! On the other hand this week they had to substitute one of my orders with a more expensive item - they immediately sent me a credit for the difference. Very fair and very impressive.

App/store system computing OFTEN freezes or more OFTEN fails to update. Have had several deliveries of bread one day over date and more often only one day remaining. After complaining to drivers on several occasions nothing changed. Now buy from local shop (FRESHER UP TO 5 DAYS REMAINING) so less happy than used to be. Deliveries are always on time do far and drivers usually excellent.
Easy to order my shopping from mobile. l like to see photos of the products, sometimes they are missing. Great to have the favourite option for repeat purchases.

Great app but after ordering, when you go back to check what your ordered it gives you a list of the food but not the amount that you ordered or the cost of what you ordered. Very irritating. And when things are out of stock it should be more up to date on the app too.

Excellent online shopping app. Asda online is very glitchy, it can take hours to do an online shop as it crashes and empties the basket and tesco dont give decent dates for fresh food. Sainsburys is very reasonably priced, their own brand foods are really tasty, the meat is RSPCA assured and they offer an 'eco deliveries' service where a delivery is booked in your area and its cheaper than standard. I wouldnt use any other online shopping service.
Good, easy to use, simple and quick. BUT doesn't have all the features of the website I would like such as reviews for products or the 'discover' section.

I cannot log on to do my food shop a lot of the time unless I clear my browsing history and then turn my phone off. When I switch phone back on I am then allowed onto the website. It is a very annoying problem. I have thought of moving to Ocado but I do like Sainsburys.
It can be annoying at times. I do tend to find the Tesco app better behaved generally. This one seems to be quite glitchy which can be frustrating. However,I do like shopping with Sainsbury's.

I have had great service. I live in Wales do wasn't on the first data list. I phoned the at risk phoneline got through right away gave my customer number and it was sorted . Had an order 4 days later and will receive another 10 days later tomorrow. They have a list that they work from and you must have a grocery account number.
ok but has its glitches which can be annoying at times. it also isn't the most user focussed. some of the menu options don't flow as well as hey could...

replyContent: Hello, We are sorry to hear you were facing issues with login. We have now resolved the issue. Please give it another try.

content: Since the latest Android app update on 25-Sep I can't login. I have tried over 10 times. Just checked and there is no new update to fix it. Managed to login eventually and successfully amend my delivery order.
I think the app has improved - I don't find it losing my order as much these days. The search function can be quite poor on occasion.

Initially I had basket issues which were very frustrating. Now it works fine, just sometimes shows "basket error". I need to close the whole app and open again. Otherwise all good. Please, can you SELL SOME POLISH FOOD ONLINE?

When my shopping arrived alot of the items were loose and not bagged up. I had to go back up stairs to get a carrier bag myself and fill it myself. Apart from this the whole service is very good.
I didn't like the app in the beginning due to it randomly logging me out, but the more I use it the easier it seems to get. I use it every week now, without any issues.
Perfect but I just wish we could keep the trays and then give them back at the next delivery it would make the change over so much quicker as the items are not in bags.
Sometimes it skips past items on list and then puts them in a different order so its very difficult to keep up. E.g. I ordered 2lots if bananas one week.
A few minor annoyances (having to login frequently), but otherwise does the job. They're often our of staples for months on the app, while they're available in-store.

I'm not sure I will ever go back to shopping in the store. It's so nice to be able to complete my order and have it brought to my front door, especially in these scary times. My only "complaint" is that there are quite a few items that are on the shelves, but not on the online shopping.

Much prefer Sainsbury's app to others, especially as a person with allergies, online i can select ingredients and it highlights products containing this. favourites pop up first when searching for products.

I do Love shopping with sainsbury I like there food. They have good quality food. Not bad prices to.

I'm also being asked if the app makes me happy. Personally there are a whole list of things I'd get more joy out of than wading through little pictures of groceries but it's okay.

I've been using the app for 2 years and have been really happy with it. It's easy to use (place an order) and deliveries are 99% on time. They deliver with crates you can unpack and give back to the driver, so there's no plastic bags which is great.
Always drove through to do my shopping,I decided to do it online. Fantastic delivery. I'm disabled & the driver "kevin" was so helpful. Will shop next month too. Just great. Fruit n veg so fresh.
Ordering my shopping for delivery Very easy, and will be delivered tonight. Offered substitute s for some things, which i will accept.

Decided to try the app even though the reviews were terrible. I have a Samsung tablet and I find it works really well. Quick response while adding items, the search is quick and easy, favourites useful and work well. Can turn off the item substitution. Easy to change or add items. You can see what offers are on at a glance. Really pleased with it. Ok so you can't pick a delvery spot if it's already fully booked or see where the driver has got to! Nobody comes to cook it for you either!!

As someone who loathes having to go grocery shopping in an actual physical supermarket, this app is an absolute gem. It works perfectly (well, it always has for me). It's very user friendly, straightforward and easy to navigate. I can book deliveries with ease and amend orders wherever I am and whenever I realise that I've forgotten something vital (all too frequent an occurrence) or delete things that I suddenly discover I have a forgotten hoard of. Personally, I wouldn't be without it.
Great service, very friendly and helpful drivers. On time and products excellently packed.

Excellent app for shopping on line. Once you get used to it it's quick and easy to use. You have a choice of delivery options at various times and prices and you can book a saver slot which starts at ¬£1. The app remembers all the things you order so you can click on favourites for quickness and/or browse for other items and offers. When you check out you have the option to tick if you want substitutes or not and you can view all your previous receipts. I can't recommend this app enough.
Great - reliable delivery and helpful staff.
Very easy to use when looking for groceries

Review Sainsbury's - Drivers always happy to help unload. App is easy to use and rarely do they never have an alternative that is suitable. Meat always taste's good and with Aldi price match who can complain. Shopping arrives without any damaged packages. Would highly recommend.üôÇ

Excellent service and delivery staff. Fabulous value in all products, especially within the meat and vegetable products. As an 83 year old pensioner the service is exceptional and makes life easier.

This Sainsbury's app is very simple and straight forward to use. I prefer using the app to the website when ordering my weekly shop. Couldnt recommend more for grocery shopping. However, instead of writing a list, I just add to my basket ready for the end of the week when I complete and pay for the groceries.
So easy to use ,and great to shop online.

Amazing using the app yesterday for the first time. Was so pleasantly surprised. Super efficient. Works a dream.

Being able to link nectar account to the app and also tie offers of products we buy regularly that gives us extra points is a lovely added extra. Would highly recommend

Great App now demand has peaked. Presumably like everyone on the planet, covid impacted lots and maybe that's why some of the reviews are sub optimal (check the dates Vs covid peaks). it's fairly easy to use, sometimes the search facility isn't as intuitive as it could be, you have to be careful how you word your search but it's easier than turning out to visit a store (my nearest is 20 minute drive each way. I'm also being asked if the app makes me happy. Personally there are a whole list of things I'd get more joy out of than wading through little pictures of groceries but it's okay.
Has everything you need, really handy if you're out and remember something you need on your shopping list
Straight forward, really easy to use.
Amazing using the app yesterday for the first time. Was so pleasantly surprised. Super efficient. Works a dream.
Very good service

So many problems with this app that it's hard to pick the most infuriating one to review. The "favourites" list (actually a list of everything you ever bought), which by necessity is the main way you choose your shopping, seems to have been deliberately designed to drive users potty. It constantly pings you back up to the top for no reason, and then as you scroll down it pauses to load every few items. Most of my shops I spend more time trying to scroll back to where I was than I do shopping.

Before the app used to chuck you back to the beginning of the list of favourites if you navigated off the app or got a phone call etc. This was very annoying but I could deal with it. But now it's doing it randomly whilst scrolling the favourite items. With 500+ items in my favourite list, I am not having to scroll back to where I left off to continue to add my shop every few minutes. The apps now unusable!

This app had been working perfectly well until I updated it before using it tonight. When shopping favourites it randomly frequently jumps right to the start of the list. I got really fed up and annoyed so checked out before finishing my order. I can see numerous complaints about the same thing over the past few days, yet this is still happening. You obviously have no idea as to how annoying this is when you're trying to trawl through a very large favourites list!! Please fix it!!

Please please please for the love of God stop this app jumping back up to the top of my shopping list every time I add or tick off an item!!!! I use this app to do my shopping in store so that I can see if an item is in stock, the prices, any multi offers and which aisle to find each item on my list. The infuriating and downright frustrating jumping about all over the place is driving me insane. I used to love this app but not any more.

I've been using previous app/apps for years without any issues. This one is absolutely horrible, I set up a payment and next day I get whoops something gone wrong and I need to set it up again, I did it again and it worked once. I've done that 3 times over the week, but now I'm fed up. Same for exchanging my point for rewards, all I see is "Sorry, we are having some troubles" and can't use my voucher. Disasters.

Is there anything more frustrating in an app or website than one that reverts you back to the beginning, each time you pop in & out of the app/website? This happens in the favourites list, even when the app continues to be open in the background. Until this is resolved, the experience is far from frictionless.

Rarely works. I hardly ever get this app to work at the checkout which has cost me money when I can't get the discounts. On the few occasions I have managed to use it it's been painfully slow and left me with a terrible impression of Tesco. Definitely not a positive shopping experience. I've had to give in and order a plastic card, which I hate doing and seems so unnecessary.

Search function useless. Favourite list pointless, usuals list pointless, "Chosen for you" is stupid . Have to make sure confirm email arrives after checking out, otherwise it won't have really gone through properly and you'll be waiting for shopping that won't turn up. Typical generic app that is not suitable for what its supposed to do but has all the buttons every other app has so people will think it has useful features.

Absolutely horrible app. Despite the fact it us on your phone you have to sign in every time you try to open it. Usually through tex message verifucation. As UK has pne of worst Internet and cell connections, some stores do not have any connections inside. So you cannot sign in. Also if you want to try to take screen picture of the code so next time you do kot have to hold a queue for 10 minutes in order to sign in, you cannot due security policy ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è I just do not use it. Too much hassle.

Used to use this. No longer shopping with Tesco, because the app has become unusable. Every time you try to use the favourite list to add things to an order, it randomly resets position back the top of the list. We used to go through the list each week and add in the bits we needed, but scrolling the list has become impossible. We're now giving up online deliveries and going back to shop at our local morrisons.

Favourites are broken, constantly throws you back to the first items. I have built up a list of about 600 items on there and I literally cannot get past the first 100 items without being thrown back to the beginning, as of writing I cannot fullfil my order unless I navigate the app to find everything all over again.

App won't let me log in. Have closed and reopened app, reinstalled app and restarted phone but can't use app unless I log in! It only lets me select the options bar at the bottom but nothing above this bar works, it's as though my screen has stopped working apart from the bottom 1cm, but obviously this is not the case, it only does this odd behaviour on the teaco app.

This site WAS very user friendly until today when I tried to place an order. First of all it wouldn't recognize my password, which I have used for 4 years so I had to change it, then when I finally managed to do a shop it wouldn't let me look at what I had ordered (there is usually a basket in the right hand top corner,). I could only do this by logging out and going back in again . Has anyone else had problems with the "upgraded" site????

Useless app. Designed by committee and poorly tested if at all. Every time asks for username and password, but never accepts due to signal, broken app etc. As a result can never make use of vouchers. Always seems to work if I access when not shopping which is convenient for tesco

Terrible app. Received a notification I had received new coupons. Clicked on the notification. Checked the app. No coupons at all. More importantly the process for using coupons is awful. Why in God's name do you have to 'add' them to the clubcard?? It's pointless, not intuitive and why are we made to do it. They've just made a mess of what used to be a good separate clubcard app.

Despite your assurances that the bug has been fixed, I am still unable to enable the card for in store payments after following all the steps suggested numerous times. I go on to receive the security code from nationwide. I type it in, then there is abrief message saying about redirecting me, a brief error message you usually see when a website fails to load. After that I can see endlessly spinning circle. Many app updates later it still doesn't let me enable the card for in store payments.
replyContent: Hi Maciej, could you please let us know the name of your bank so that we can do some more checks?

content: When using the Favourites list, whilst scrolling down through the items on your list, it keeps jumping back to the top making it pretty much impossible to complete your shopping. Been suffering this for a few weeks now and waiting on a fix. This needs to be high priority as others have also reported this.

Bloody annoying. I can't even add items to my shopping via my favourites because it keeps scrolling up after I put three items in my basket. I uninstalled and reinstalled and it just became even worse as it literally scrolls up every 2 seconds to the point that I can't even scroll down the the item that I need to add. The most useless app ever. Will have to do my shop via my laptop. Sort it out!

Like others the app is now unusable for shopping as everytime you scroll down the list of items and it has to load the next section, it resets you back at the top. Worst of all, I tried just scrolling multiple times to preload all the screens so I could then shop in peace and the whole app crashed. Don't know what update was done recently, but it needs to be rolled back as this makes online shopping impossible unless you want something in the top section of your app.

Seemingly unable to work! It keeps saying check you have Google Play installed (I have) and its up to date (it is) and yet I can't get beyond the landing page. Very disappointing. Have uninstalled and then reinstalled. It worked once! And is now once again throwing up the same message before closing down. Never had so much trouble with any app let alone a shopping app. All my others work eg Waitrose, Asda, Ocado without any issues EDIT: i uninstalled it, re-installed it, it worked just once

Really so disappointed. I've used the old Tesco Pay app with little or no issues for year. Now Tesco have decided to merge the apps (I'm guessing to save money) and its rubbish. It crashes and I've had to do the one time verification of my bank details at lest once a week over the past month. Of course this always happens when there is a huge queue and I've no other way of paying as generally don't carry card anymore. Why oh why change what isn't broken? Very very disappointed Tesco.

Awful! Every time to remember strong password for a shop without auto insert! Who needs password there in the first place? Fingerprint in the modern age. Plus card authentication often! Why! Even bank app is easier to use! Who needs to break into my shopping account? Fetish app

Coupons are not usable. Saved the coupons on the app ahead of going into the shop, got to checkout, the app loaded fine and the coupons opened, only without displaying the barcode - making them absolutely unusable. Customer service said they can't do anything as that's Clubcard app issue, which is separate from store issues. Logged into my Clubcard account on Internet browser (on phone) and same thing there - coupons displayed but not usable as the barcode is not showing. Absolutely useless app.
Bug using the favourites list. As mentioned by others the page keeps jumping back to the top, this is super annoying and frustrating. Needs to get fixed as a priority.

It wasn't working, so I missed my driver as I thought there was a problem as it said preparing the order still. I was hanging out the washing with my mobile and landline phone (just incase). Driver was on the rd but didn't contact me, so I missed the shopping delivery. So yes if it was working I would have least have known it was actually on the rd on the way to me. What good is an app if it doesn't work. Or the driver doesn't check you're in. Do better Tesco, rant over.

Club Card deals suck. Get to the check out, open the app. Updates and logs out. Then it does not verify the club card so end up paying full price. Absolutely useless, updates break everything and logs out at the most inconvenient time, when your going to pay

I'm a rookie when it comes to online shopping, but now I've got the hang of it I find it quick and easy to use. I left this review about 2 years ago. Sadly today I don't feel the same. After its latest update the app continuously returns to the beginning, which is annoying enough when you're trying to get the shopping done, even more so when you're nearly at the end. Also it wouldn't take a voucher even though I had satisfied the requirements for it.

Before latest update, app had been glitchy at payment stage for a while, necessitating hitting 'continue' to finalise payment. Since update, glitch still there, but hitting 'continue' no longer completes transaction. Had to give up on app and process payment via browser instead - not ideal!

Awful app. Even with full internet the clubcard will not load which is very frustrating when this means that the clubcard discount is not added at the till. I would not recommend this app to anyone, and I'll be using other shops that have their apps / discount cards in an actual working condition.

Went to Tesco's on Woodfield Plantation, Doncaster DN4 8SN. I tried to open the app only to get a message saying could not connect. I tried using Tesco's Wifi / Internet, i even put on my mobile data. No matter what i tried to do i just got error messages. This is not the first time this has happened at this store. It seems they are always having a problem with their Internet, which is why half the time the scan as you shop is down or failing that the scan as you go tills are out of order.

Difficult to use app. When you shop from your "usuals" list, it returns to the top of the list every time the page refreshes. When scrolling down through over 500 products and it continually returns to the first product, it takes an age to rescroll each time and by the time you get near the bottom of your list I am fit to shop at Sainsburys.

Improved! I must be using a different app. I kept on being jumped back to the beginning of my favourites. It is frustrating and a waste of my time. 1 more time, and I was going to shop elsewhere. If it happens next time I order, I will swap to a different supermarket. How can this be better???????

Not working properly. Trying to scroll down my list of favourites and it keeps jumping back to the top all the time. Very frustrating. Tried loads of times over last few days and keeps happening. Still not managed to get through my list so gave up. Please fix.

The app has been updated and is incapable of use properly, as every time I use the shopping list and tick an item, the keyboard appears and has to be cancelled to continue shopping. Not all of the items have aisle numbers. It would be helpful if the shelf codes were added to ease our experience.

App is generally fine, but giving 1 star until they fix infinite scroll issue on a Favourites. Every time it loads the next subset of items, it scrolls to the very top of the list. For a long list of favourites, this is extremely annoying, and I nearly threw my phone against a wall because of it.

Last review I did was 2.2.19. The app has been, not perfect, but quite functional, generally satisfactory. In this review, despite emailing Tesco, nothing has been done to address this serious issue, the app with its latest update still keeps stalling. It's now unustable. You can't finish shopping let alone pay. 2min in it freezes. It's Infuriating. 21.02.23 Had enough. I've uninstalled the app. Update: 20.05.23 I was contacted by Tesco Tech, whom eventually fixed the issue, all is good again.

App continuously asks to verify clubcard number which because of there being an app don't carry around anymore! What's the point have having an app if you still need the physical clubcard to authenticate against?? Can't it be address or email like virtually every other app that exists?! This is particularly annoying as you'll only find this out when stood by the checkout and it then doesn't work. Will most likely delete it and go back to using the physical card as the app serves no purpose.

Used to be great but recently the favourites list has broken so everytime you try to scroll through it you get forced back to the top making it unusable and tempting to just abandon the shop. The availability has gone really poor too, can never get fresh fruit via online ordering any more but if I go into the shop that feeds the order they always seem to have plenty of availability for the the things the app says are not there

Really useless app. Needs to be online to work but, guess what? Our local Tesco, a huge store in a major city doesn't receive a signal. Always take my wallet because it's so unreliable. Old app worked well so god knows what they thought they were improving. Interface is very clunky too

Since last update, app keeps resetting to the start of Favourites list each time new items are loaded on the page. Can no longer use the app to shop as requires user to scroll through hundreds of items every time the next 5-10 items are loaded. Great if I want bananas (Favourites item 1), not for much else! :(

While the idea of consolidating the apps is good. The fact that the app has to connect to the internet to display your clubcard barcode is a rubbish and senseless idea. The abrcode doesn't change so why? Of course most Tesco's are tin sheds with rubbish data signals so acquiring a data signal is a slow process increasing till dwell time.

The latest mobile app update has issues in the favourites view. When I'm in an order, the list of favourites resets to the top every time new items are added to the bottom of the view. This is very frustrating. I've no idea if this is also a problem on the web app

Dropped score to one star. Old pay+ worked perfectly. This one is garbage. Have had to re-enable my payment card 3 times. Frustrating. How can an app be worse than a previous version? Awful UI and can no longer see a list of transactions when paying in store.

Possibly the worst app and service of all grocery delivery apps. Be warned if a payment doesn't go through, no way to rebook or simply duplicate old order. Customer service is grumpy as are the delivery drivers, why such bad attitudes? Ordered 6 times, each time adds a new low level of poor service. Food though is of good quality.

Trying to use clubcars vouchers and coupons is a nightmare. It never used to be easy and quick, but now you can't add more than 1 to an order. It is extremely frustrating as the coupons expire before you can add them to your order

The app is unusable when shopping on your favourites section. As you are scrolling through, it suddenly goes back to the beginning, making it virtually impossible to get to the end of the favourites list. Please fix this!

This app cost me ¬£5! I opened the old app, it locked me out because for some unknown reason I HAD to switch to the new one, all my clucard info was gone and I was unable to get it scanned. Whilst holding up a que at checkout. Terrible experience, the clubcard was the only reason I still shopped at tesco and with this random erasing of my clubcard info in the new app (yes even after logging into my account with my info) I think its time to look for shopping elsewhere.

App has started freezing every few minutes since the last update. Pleas correct this. Using Android v13. Update 31st May - I have a favourite list of 558 items. I can now add 2 or 3 to my basket before being shot to the top of the list. What have you done?! It's unusable.

App is unusable. Favourites is the main way to order and it keeps jumping back to the top of the page making it impossible to complete the order. I'll have to do it on the website instead but normally the app is much easier.

A overwhelming maze to navigate, not user friendly, trying to find my actual clubcard and I have to download another app apparently, what's the point of this app if I can access a digital clubcard? I also can't download it as I'm on android. Not obviously organised, and so much junk to click on. Design by monkeys and full of adverts instead of your account. Gave up.

Rubbish! And now the ultimate annoyance on here. Whilst going through your shopping list ticking boxes, it continually flicks back to the beginning of the list. When it's a long list, this can drive you nuts!!! Like I said, complete rubbish!

Badly designed for security as it kicks you out regularly forcing you to sign in and doesn't allow saving password in secure locker. Only solution is either to write password down or use a simple password. There is no reason to make the user re-enter their password, this is a freaking loyalty app - What's an elite hacker going to do with a hacked phone? Get a discount on their shopping when they could just get their own club card for free anyway? Disappointing.

Having issues trying to actually finish my order as the favourites keeps jumping back up to the top it's so annoying you just can't get very far down before it jumps right back to the top again..it's so frustrating so iv given up. Please fix this issue Tesco.

Terrible app. Not well thought out at all. Never get any coupons for extra points anymore, which I use to get all the time. Putting everything onto the same app was a terrible decision and unfortunately I've lost interest in it.

Very very Poor, got original app, each time I open it, I'm told to update to this app, which it does, but isn't retained by phone, so I have to go through the same routine every time,which is frustrating to say the least.

Not fit for purpose. Unlike the discontinued Tesco Pay, this one needs internet connection to use pay-in-store but they don't offer WiFi if you don't have reception so you have to collect the points the old fashioned way with two separate transactions.

Works half of the time. Sometimes you can't press anything on the app. So you can't press the clubcard bit to scan whilst you're in the shop. Uninstalling and reinstalling doesn't work. Last app didn't have this issue.

Keeps logging you out and won't log back in for ages. I don't know what is going in with this app at all but the odd time I call to tesco and pull up the app for the club card I'm stood there for ages trying to get it to work. Logs you out and you can't log in for ages. The developers of this app need to get it together it's a nightmare!!!!

Keep finding that the amount of items I've added to the basket is increasing and it's not me doing it so when the shopping arrives I end up with double the amount for some items. If my husband takes the delivery he doesn't realise and we end up paying for more things than we could eat!

What's the point in having notes for each item ordered, when no one reads them? - This is bad customer service. Usual's show few regular products, most are from purchases made a very long time ago. Substitutions are often sent back because notes are not read by anyone. Get way too many damaged items delivered, what customers wouldn't buy in-store!

Every now and then I'll end up in a tesco wondering why I don't go there very often. Then I see the over inflated prices made bearable only with a club card. But that's OK, because I have one on my phone. Except it's logged itself out every time I'm in tesco. And every time it asks for verification using the actual club card (even if I did it last time). So instead of paying ridiculous prices I just leave ¬£40 of ice lollies wherever I'm stood and remember not to go to tesco for a while.

Not used it yet so no experience to report. Would be better if we could add nicknames to cards or an image of them like on the old pay+ app . Won't sign in with biometric, just asks for pin (set to use biometric) No logging of card use, now need to keep receipts again!

The app is ok except for the coupon part. Since being pushed and encouraged to use the app instead of by post, i have not received any coupons for over a year. (When i installed the app). I've rang Customer service several times but they don't seem to care and just fob you off with any old excuse which says a lot about tesco Customer care. Probably won't get a reply with this feedback either. Lost faith in Tesco's big time..will shop elsewhere..

I have been shopping with tesco for years. New app update has made it impossible to do a shop from your favourites list because the app keeps returning to the start of the list every 2 minutes. Immensely frustrating and I've moved to sainsbury.

This app is completely non-functional on my Motorola phone. Most of the buttons don't respond at all to me tapping them, leaving me unable to even sign into the app as the sign in button doesn't work, even after reinstalling and restarting the app in my attempt to solve the problem.

How do you remove a single item from an in-store shopping list!? It used to be easy but now when you tick an item it just moves to the ever-growing Picked Up section without giving you any option to delete it! The only way I can find to remove items is to delete the entire list which is not what I want to do! The app is either horribly unintuitive or missing a vital feature. Ruins an otherwise ok app. 1 star until it's fixed please.

UI is okay, but current version seems to crash constantly and without warning. Don't know if it's just with my particular device (Pixel 6a), but it will just freeze while I'm in the middle of placing an order. Easily fixed but still frustrating as it can happen several times in a single session. UPDATE: At least 3 updates later and it's still crashing/freezing. If anything, it's worse than ever. Please sort it.

Never had a problem until recently. It's hard to complete your shopping as everytime the screen refreshes it takes you back to the top and by the time you get back to where you were it's refreshing again.

The app was fine until the update. Now after every item placed into the basket it jumps back to the top of my favourites, very frustrating and time consuming, I will shop elsewhere if this isn't fixed.
Since the last update the app is unusable. Scrolling through my favourites and keeps jumping to the top of the list. Have been using for over a year with no problems before hand.

So annoying when you're putting an order together and it bounces you back to the top of your favourites list when it loads a bit more of the page or when your screen goes off. Then you have to scroll all the way back down to where you were

Latest update isn't working. Keeps jumping back to the top of my favourites list, causing me to have to scroll back through all the products. Can't get through to the end of my favourites list at all, keeps bumping me back to the start.

for goodness sake, sort out the scrolling!! impossible to use when going through your favourites, it constantly jumps to the top. most frustrating and timewasting experience of shopping that you could imagine.

Garbage at its main job. Half the items in store need a club card for a discount, but I get to the checkout to be asked to reauthenticate my club add. Which I need my physical card for, which I haven't got. This happens almost every time. Literally the reason I don't shop at tesco unless I've got no choice. No other chain does this.

Change my review because After recent update. There is an issue within my favourites on the app once the scrolling down the page it auto-reloads to the top of the page every time making it impossible to complete the order. Very frustrating.

Unusable. Every time I try to use the favourites I get part way down and it goes back to the beginning again. It appears to have a very small bar at the side but I am pretty sure I am not accidentally catching it.

Keeps Crashing and won't open unless you go back to Google Play and press open. Quite embarrassed with a que behind. Just slows down the shopping for yourself and others. Why can't you just use you card/fob and have the option on the screen to use your vouchers....

I didn't appreciate going into a store and then at the checkout find the app has been changed which required an uninstall, new install and login when I use the app to present my clubcard. Left the shop without being able to get my clubcard discounts.

All screens are available but they all freeze when opened. Just deleted and reinstalled the app, the first screen is asking me if i prefer to shop online or in store. Can't answer because the screen is frozen. Can't even sign in. I'm off to asda to shop.

In order to change your wrong phone number to your right one, there are only 2 options, receive a verification text or verification call... you see the stupidity here. With the wrong phone number, the app is useless, so one miss click means you might as well delete it and go back to lidl.

WORST EXPERIENCE EVER! Easier to go to the shop! Search for a product i.e mayonnaise, add it into your basket and the whole search result refreshes and moves with "Inspired by your choice" suggestions. Have to search again to add more mayonnaise... Nevermind, go through your favourites, no chance! Scroll too quickly and it'll end back up the top of the list. Removing a product from you basket? Check again, it'll probably add it back in 1 minute later! Sack the developer and hire a better tester
Unusable at the moment. Cannot shop from your favourites list as it keeps jumping back to the top of the list when it loads the next batch of products. Don't bother and use a browser instead.

But at least finally there's a way to open an app and show the clubcard code right away and not hidden behind 3 or 4 taps like it used to, so +1‚≠ê for that! Maybe eventually this will become a reasonably useful and pleasant to use app - but there's still a long way to go.

Check stock in your local store is a great concept, if it were accurate. I went to my local store specifically to buy dill, which it said was in stock. This is an awful user experience. I use this app weekly for my shopping and there is some sort of glitch that causes your favourites to refresh about 15 times in the space of ordering. Also not a great search function and you can type the name of a product you get in store and it doesn't always show up. Also, so often items are unavailable but if I call to store they aren't!

Just updated app ....bad move, now it just keeps sending you to top of favorites list, I gave up and had to log onto computer to finish shop, what with delivery saver and other price rises may have to ditch tesco!! Very frustrating

I've been using this app since it first began, it has been getting worse. Constantly time's out and returns you back to the top of the list forcing you to scroll through again. Only problem is this doesn't stop this from happening for anyone with 2 brain cells and only makes life more irritating for the rest of us.

P.S. the app asks me to rate it every time I use it. I also HATE the new, unavoidable, sponsored items which get right in the way.

App keeps freezing. So frustrating. Have never had a problem with the Tesco app before and I've been using it for years. Item descriptions are poor, doesn't even tell you the weight of some items. Doesn't show reviews for items. Doesn't allow me to apply a clubcard voucher I have to my basket, without going to that voucher and getting the code, Should just be able to click apply to shop.

replyContent: Hello Ryan, thank you for reporting this issue which we are now investigating. Please watch out for future releases as we continuously update the app to fix bugs and improve performance

content: I find it very frustrating that it doesn't automatically open on the QR code.
