I'd also like to be able to set my own favourites, rather than it all being automatically set for you.

Great for online shop, easy to use. HOWEVER, I now have to go through about 10 more steps when paying in store compared to the old Pay+ app, including turning on data as I can't pick up store WiFi in my local shop. With the Pay+ app it was open app, pop in pin, zap QR code, no Internet required. Now I spend so much time just getting to the point I can zap the QR code, I feel like I'm holding up the queue! All in one app is a great idea but it needs to work as smoothly as what it's replacing!

Its an okay app, dont really understand the switch from the old app as this one seems more complicated if anything. Theres also an issue with paying at the newer self service machines as its not guaranteed to scan which is obviously annoying as you miss out on the points or you stand there for ages hoping it scans.

The application is not that much usefull. It is still faster to use the key fob. I was unable to display my card number because of connection problem. I lost all the discounts on that transaction and tesco points.I decided to go off line but it is not possible to take the screenshot of the card because of "security reasons". It is possible to take a picture of the card and use it. Where is the logic? Card number/QR code should be available off line. Unlocked phone is security check itself.

The app is more secure than my bank, requiring a text code to verify my identity before I can access my Clubcard vouchers every time. Less than ideal at the checkout! The entire app seems to be needlessly faffy and difficult to use.

The apps ok and for the most part is easy to do your shop... but if there's a problem with missing items tesco makes it hard to address it, there should be an option to chat within the app or notify them about missing items but instead you have to phone them and spend time waiting for help.. i think that's their plan, make it difficult to get a refund and you'll just give up, well i am giving up for the sake of ¬£6 of items not received but i won't be using tesco again.

Ok but over the last couple of days the app when doing your shopping on the list keeps flicking back up to the top of your favourites list. It let's you add around 2 items then keeps going back to thr beginning. Not a problem if you don't have a lot in favourites but I have over 500 and getting annoying now.

Everything was fine with this app until I tried to use it at a store I hadn't been to for a while. The app launched but nothing loaded. The refresh button didn't work so I couldn't use my clubcard. Thankfully I had it in my Google Wallet. Seems you always MUST have a fallback for these things!

Easy to add or delete items. Not so easy to delete/cancel whole orders. It's a bit annoying that they don't leave ALL of the old orders up so that you can just tick the items you've bought previously.

I was a bit disappointed about getting charged ¬£5 extra, on top of ¬£3.50 delivery charge, which in itself was a lot more than other online supermarkets. I couldn't read anywhere to get free delivery for over 65yrs pensioners. I did read that online but couldn't find it on the Tesco app. I also read that there would be a charge for under ¬£25 and NOT ¬£50

Makes it hard to find offers now it's tesco clubcard offers. Can't work out how to find the half price items easily anymore. If you book delivery for a Tuesday and the main offers finish on the Monday you can't see what will be on offer. Also hard to find items as you have to pick the correct category and some items aren't under the category you expect

Makes it easy to manage weekly food shops for 2 households. Following the update I installed today, my favorites list now keeps jumping back to the top, makes it very hard to complete my shopping. I've had to resort to adding manual which defeats the point of the list. 06.06.2023

Usually the site is great, although why the developers had to split usuals and favourites is anyone's guess! Today everytime I clicked to add something the whole list scrolled back up to the beginning. So I gave up and ordered what I had in the basket at the time and will go onto Ocado to order the rest!

My experience has been good APART FROM the seemingly harmless invitation to store one's bank details/password right at the end after paying, when an inexperienced shopper might not realise the risk, or a shopper ticks that box by mistake. It says "Would you like to store your bank details in our wallet?" This invitation box left in place makes me want to change supermarkets, because its a risk for any person who does. I have heard of several people who have lost savings because they got hacked.
Problems when scrolling through 'favourites'. Keeps jumping back to the top of the page. So much so, that I had to type in the search, each individual item. Not happy!

Used to work really well - but now it repeatedly jumps back to the top of the favourites list. You can no longer see available vouchers in the app without additional steps. Tricky to add things you've forgotten just before check out.
It's not customer friendly enough, try and select 3 meal deals, no prompts and pretty sure I missed one snack, which I struggled to find, make it more simple or you could be seen as misleading

I used to go in and do y shopping with no problems at all. But the last few months I can't even sign in. A message is keep popping up as error in signing in. I have uninstalled the app and then reinstalled it again. Still can't sign in.
Ever since the recent update you can only go a quarter of the way through the favourites list before it goes back to the beginning. I've tried uninstalling and reinstalling the app but it dou help.
The app is easy to use and negotiate. Search is a little off but usually get there. Horribly glitchy though. Often crashes and often loses part of orders/changes.

I would have rated this a 5 star, but I do not understand why Tesco charges ¬£5 fir orders under ¬£50. It just sounds like a wicked rip-off! Considering the fact that everyone is literally struggling to live, you're not even encouraged to send a surprise shopping to your loved ones without Tesco making you pay more than budgeted. Why create online shopping via the app if it's not to help customers. I think it's just a way to make extra money from customers. Why compel us to shop more?

Nice interface, but I have trouble with constant crashes on Google Pixel 4a 5G. That it leaves you logged in is very handy though as the web app doesn't do this and it makes it very easy to whip your phone out and add something to your order. Or at least it would, if it wouldn't crash after 5 seconds of inactivity. I have to keep scrolling up and down constantly, which seems to stop this from happening for some reason

Takes twice as long to pay for my petrol now that the quick pay app has been merged into this. Because you have to relocate the page where you pay after scanning the clubcard, and it's not obvious where that is. It was way faster having a combined clubcard with my debit card. Even the forecourt staff say people complain about this a lot now.

Favourites list is too slow to load and scrolls back to the top every time I hit the still-loading part of the list. This gets more and more irritating the further down the list I get. Please fix so it stay where I am on the list.

Have used for years and generally very comfortable with how it works but 2 issues. 1) if the screen times out, or I look at a different app, the list of favourites I'm working down reverts to the top. 2) when I search it used to list my favourite items at the top of the results list and now it doesn't. Both these things make it more time consuming to find the things I want.

only reason why i not rate 5 stars, because it must be work as "scan and go" and not like now, get the qr code for scan then get the scanner... no! it much much easier if we dont have to touch the scanners after anybody else. Our mobile is enough personal and nobody touch it, not like the scanners in the stores. and we dont know is anybody clean them down or not. i never seen that, just put back on the chargers without any clean... when you will modify to scan and go then i give 5 stars.

crashes often and just says "servers are busy" when you try to access your favourites. web version and ios don't have such problems. Then worked better for 4 years until recent updates in 2023 - list scrolling broken and errors on checkout.

Much better on a smart phone than the web browser version but once you get into the payment sequence could done with a 'get back to search' button without having to click back, back, back. Sometimes leaves things in your basket wlthat you have definitely removed. Also, seems to flag items as 'loved' when only bought once (which obviously you don't know if you love without trying it first), and there is no option to remove the heart.

I preferred the previous Pay+ app which did the job perfectly well as I only use the app in-store to pay and get points. I've finally worked out that this app can do that too, (after having to up my payment details twice), but it's hidden away on the home screen, not the main clubcard screen. Clubcard screen only allows you to collect points, not pay as well..Why? It would surely make sense to have just one QR code in one place to do both. I would also like to use fingerprint ID to login to pay.
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for the feedback. We are working on the app navigation to improve accessibility of in-store features. Please watch out for future releases as we continuously update the app to make online and in-store shopping quicker and more convenient than ever

content: Quick easy and much better than going to a store. We especially use it to book a slot and then add things as and when we remember. Updated, since about January the app has started to crash a lot and sometimes I have to try 3-4 times to get the payment through. It's becoming very annoying. I've even missed products off because I thought a basket update had gone through when it hadn't.

Convenient but Not Comprehensive Handy if you want to update your existing order but Tesco tends to withhold budget stuff like larger packs and anything from world food aisles that might save you money, and you'll never be offered an affordable egg. Tough to search if you haven't got a product in your favourites and I've been offered some strange alternatives, a papaya does not not fill in for a coconut for example.

Allow us to put our clubcard into Google wallet / Samsung wallet. Its more convienient than opening this app which frequently hangs when loading or crashes upon opening. Edit** the option to save clubcard to gpay but there is an error saving the card. Please fix.

Would be better if you could change the order of your basket as I find its not organised in shelf order but the order in which the items are added to basket. This is annoying as I end up over ordering some items.

App is easy to use, but there are a lot of products sold in store that are not on here. My nearest Tesco superstore is just not easy for me to get to, so I then end up having to go to my local Asda for the items I can't buy from the app.

Find this very difficult to find some everyday items that i know are in the store all the time but even when i search for them they don't come up and it would be so much better and easier if things were all in order for example milk full fat semi skimmed and skimmed instead of them spread around the rest of the milk products.
Missing the option to set an alarm when the delivery is imminent. Also, the option to save multiple payment methods.
Was 5 star but latest update added a very annoying and useless set of click boxes that keep popping up in the middle of lists.
Buggy, often gets through the whole payment and get message confirming all went through ok. Only to find next day the app had an error and you have no delivery.

Glitchy, the app freezes every 5 mins or so. Have to close and re-open the app & work out whether the last few items you selected are still remembered and saved in the basket or not. You get there in the end but it's frustrating esp. when it freezes part way through the payment and you're unsure if it's gone through or not. The Clubcard vouchers sections work well though.

I had been saying that Tesco should combine their apps into one for a while, but if this is the result, bring back the old ones! Adding clubcard - worked. Adding cards to the wallet - works only if you can validate without leaving the app (SMS notification that shows the code is OK, anything needing other apps to verify returns to the home page without adding the card). Trying to set up in-store payments - "Something went wrong." Will use it for clubcards, but right now not for anything else

The app froze on several occasions. First was when I attempted to book a delivery slot. Then when I attempted to scan my plastic to pay the bill and then again when I attempted to continue following the second bug. There's lots here for the developer to be getting in with.
When trying to do my shopping, the app keeps jumping back to the top of the page. Not impressed when trying to get the weekly shopping done. Please fix!
Some negatives, app continues to refresh bringing you back to the top of your favourites list. No option to see rest of shelf easily. No easy option to remove items from Favourites

Only use the in-store section for vouchers and payment barcodes, which works fine when you have reception. If your local store has patchy reception (like Gateshead), then it can be completely useless, failing to load anything, leaving you standing around at the till. Have given up and dug out my physical payment cards on several occasions. Some caching of voucher and payment details for offline use would help.

The latest silent update has ruined the shopping list. You need to consider that due to recurring shopping some people never clear their lists and if you have a long list the simple action of unticking or ticking and item shouldn't throw every time at the top of the list because the focus is set on the search bar.

It should default to shop in store in my opinion. The signal in some stores can be indifferent which slows down connection. Then the less able and some of the elderly have trouble accessing and scanning which in turn holds the queue up which, in turn gets some folk in the queue agitated.

Good in store shopping list features. However, storing card to payment wallet doesn't work. After filling out the correct details, a error screen comes up saying, "Something went wrong" My card works for payment with other apps... would be grateful if this could be fixed.

They've introduced the shop in store part so you can now see where products are located and if they're in stock in your store. But they have changed the functionality on how you manage thd list. I can't see now how to remove items from the list, the option has disappeared. Everytime you check or uncheck a checkbox for an item the list scrolls back to the top which is so bloody annoying that I'm going to revert back to using the order online section for my in store list instead. Fix please.

I agree with some of the other commitments‚ÅâÔ∏è regarding the error's from tesco)(I have also been using them since covid) and(things are not going good on there app)(just hope they get it sorted some how)(but they are still my favourite)üëçüÜó next to Asda)(as they work very hard to make sure we got our grosery)(when covidüó£Ô∏èwas very bad)(so we shouldn't put them downüëáto much)üôàüôâüôäthanksü§ó
Half your groceries I still have difficulties finding what I want but it still cost me a lot more . The one thing that I really like is you have great staff they are brilliant.
Needs the ability to clear all favourites considering these were generated on my behalf and removing all 340 of them will take all night. Also lacks the "Rest of Shelf" option that the website has.
It's good, and convenient, but for some reason, they have the marker on the map wrong for my address, and I have no idea how to fix it, otherwise I would have rated higher
I like having all the functionality in one app but I can rarely get the payment bar code to scan. It took about 15 attempts today to get clubcard plus bar code to scan.

Annoying thing is the offers are sometimes too long to fit on the screen so I don't know what the offer is. IE pizza company meal deal buy 1 pizza 1 sid........ that's all I can see and it doesn't give any more than that.
Changed from 5* to 3*,they removed viewing ratings on products from the app, makes it harder to see what products are great, and awful

Just 3 stars because one of the features you use most which is scanning the clubcard, requires 3 taps since the last update. This should be immediately available with one tap/ opening the app. Update: Thank you for your response. Looking forward to the next updates.
replyContent: Hello Clayton, thank you for your feedback. We'll be making changes to the app navigation very soon, so that you'll find the Clubcard right at the top of your home-screen. Please watch out for future releases as we continuously update the app to make online and in-store shopping quicker and more convenient than ever

content: The shopping items go to the top every time the phone is in standby. Very annoying
Great idea but every time you stop scrolling (in favourites for example) it jumps right back to the beginning. Time consuming to keep starting again ‚òπÔ∏è
The app is generally, but as someone with a severe visual impairment, I would find ituch easier to use if it had a dark mode option.

Been using this app for years to do my weekly shop's but after the update it keeps jumping back to the top of my favourite list when I'm scrolling down. Making it almost unusable. If not fixed I will have to shop elsewhere
Favourites list keeps returning to beginning a quarter way down. Also annoying having to remember to click allow substitutions every order.
The app keeps hoing back to the beginning of my favourites. I put in fruit veg etc. Pause to check on supply and I'm back in fruit again. Very frustrating
Variable performance. Keeps returning to the top of the favourites list, very annoying. Take note Tesco - Sainsbury's app is better.

I have made some changes to my order . Had a look at the offers !! But no date's shown ? So don't know if I have missed the the offers I have added ? . Much prefer the way it was before üòï Or am I missing something ?
Hit and miss. Saying there's slots available but every time I click on it, it throws me off.. so I lose that slot. Only thing that annoys me.
It's OK but it's difficult or impossible to find how many carbs per 100g on some items. You can't see how many stars items have been granted by customers.
Used to love this app but has started glitching and sending me back to the startof my favourites section every minute or so. Very frustrating!

Easy to use to place an order. However, the customer reviews of products aren't shown. I find the reviews helpful if I'm choosing a product I haven't tried before so I will probably go back to ordering on the website, where the reviews are shown.

Irritating as offers are all down one side making list tedious to trawl through. If offers are multiple would be easier to see if they clumped together. Longer lists shortened into groups eg soaps, detergents cleaners.
First time user - struggled to find what I needed until I saw the search icon. Search icon should be displayed with the promo items. Will be easier next time
It's okay. But, for me, it would be a lot better if the fingerprint log-in actually worked. And yes I have checked the button in settings.
When scrolling through my favourites, it keeps returning to the top, which only happened this week. Plz fix it as it's really hard to complete my order Other wise good app

I'm having the app crashes to the point of being sometimes unusable I believe that the problem is the app is Not really compatible with Android 13 Tesco need to update their app to work with the large variety of Android capable Smartphones !! How do I know? When setting permissions for this app there's a message that says it's written for an older version of Android. I also have an iPhone and it works fine on that platform ! Tesco need to do much better
Totally thrown by new design of website.Much preferred how it was one/two years ago. Not an improvement to my mind especially for elderly people.
I wasted a lot of time. Everything appeared available until I got to the check and 10 items were suddenly not available.

App is quite good.However missing a couple of useful features. *Cannot see customer reviews of products? Or leave a product review? *No "Rest of shelf" button, to compare products? i.e prices/package sizes. Also does not give a start date for special offers, or club card price discounts, only gives the end date. For more detailed information, forget using the app, and go through your browser.. It's far better.

Been having issues with this app recently and it constantly freezes! I have to shut down the whole app and then go back to where I was. Very annoying if I'm pages into my favourites list. I've resorted to using the website browser which defeats the object of having an easy to use app.

Very annoying that the only way to set up subs for individual items is to go through your entire basket at checkout time and find the items one at a time. It would be so much easier if the subs options was always available whenever the quantity is enterable. Otherwise a prerty good app.

I can use it to get my shopping delivered.... but.... if you leave the app for a second (e.g. to look at a shopping list) the interface refreshes so you lose your place in your favourites list (to which Tesco adds EVERY SINGLE PRODUCT YOU BUY, EVER) or any other content you had displayed. Really, really bad UX.

Does what I need it to do to be able to order my food shopping although I don't think its updated as regularly as it could be when it comes to available products. For example I tried purchasing some fresh tomatoes tonight and there were none available. No salad, cherry, tomatoes on vine etc.. only in tins. I found it hard to believe they didn't have any tomatoes in s while store... ü§î

Used to be ok but now disappointed, unable to even view products whilst logged into my account - keeps saying there is some sort of problem etc. When logged out I can view products but that's all. Tried to contact support via twitter but all advice reinstall the app and that apparently my device isn't letting it to work (must be 3 different devices having same problem then). All was good before last update though, occasionally only lagged with updating basket.

I'm unable to add a payment card that is the Tesco payment wallet to pay in store. It fails after submitting the OTP, this has been happening since I installed the app over a month ago. This seems to be a problem with some other users. Can you confirm that you are working on a fix for this issue.

Love the shop in store feature but what would be helpful is if you could transfer the shopping list to online basket. Simply because I decided to order online but had to shop the items again. I would also like to see a comparison basket or trolley with the big 4 supermarkets, within the tesco app, on every item, so I can see any savings to be made in real time and choose what items I can save money on. I would hope tesco are brave enough and honest enough to show all price comparisons to cust.

Gets 3 stars from me. It's not terrible, but coming from a huge profitable organisation like Tesco, it should be much much better. It's a shame, but it's all a bit of a mess and extremely buggy, frequently getting the message "oh no! Looks like a technical hiccup".

Overall I like the app. But as a disabled person, I do not like the bag-less delivery service, nor the service fees and booking slot costs. It all adds up, and it's quite expensive. Also the updates are not always accurate.

No way to cancel an order on the app, must use the website. Does not always reflect products in store, I have seen bananas on the shelf but the app says that they are unavailable. Items that were shown as favourites have disappeared even though I buy them regularly. Items are shown as not available but I have seen them on the shelf. Items on the shelf are not always available to order.

I'm disappointed with the new app. It keeps crashing and I'm constantly having to close it and start again. I used the old one for 8 years and no problems. Tesco please sort this out! However when it works, it's great!

Good app, I've found it easy to use and navigate, love that I can see my account and my club card points in the app too. 3 stars because it constantly crashes and I have to keep closing and opening it while trying to do my shopping.

Bit annoying you can't add items to your shop when out of stock in the shop, as things will likely be back before the picking is done and leads to you picking other things. Numerous occasions we've had things were sure we removed from the basket still in the final shop too. It's also not build for 2 (or any shop wuth 1+) people logging in, I'm sure it's fairly normal for a family to shop together.

1. Why does it show items that are unavailable? 2. 'Rest of shelf' items should be shown when clicking on an item, it'll save time. 3. Unable unfavourite items on app. 4. When filtering choices, should be able to choose more than 1 option. 5. Is this app ever going to improve?
I've been experiencing issues with the app, it keeps resetting to default on favourites It's not much to moan at, just a little frustrating

Every time I open the app a pop up takes over saying download the app....highly annoying when I already have the actual app. Can't press back so have to click on link which takes me to play store and back again!! Please fix these bugs.
Too much every day groceries known to be available in store are marked as unavailable on line. Infuriating for those of us who are not mobile enough to visit a store!!!

Its Nice they updated the process... however just give the items cheaper in the first place, only reason you want us to use the cards is to see our habits... It seems all the superstores are creating reward apps instead of making it cheaper. Its just a play on words hoping people are just sheep.
Confusing and not as intuitive as the older version. If it ain't broke, don't fix it.

Now when I click on the app it doesn't open the app it takes me to Google play where them have to press play on there so to make the app actually work even though I have updated it! I've been using this app for ages and it works it seems to be ok but every time I open it it says it soon going to finish and I have to update it so I click on the update and it takes me to open I have to assume I've got the updated app but cannot be. So suppose will just have to wait and see if it stops working

It's convenient but a lot of the food options are the higher price plus the isn't a big selection of goods available. For instance I'm not able to get the Thick Hovis I usualy like to get.Most forgotten items ¬£7 Kenco Coffee!!!! well I would forget that too at that price.

Was pretty useful to me but the latest update has completely screwed up the in store shopping list section so that every single item has been duplicated and you can no longer remove individual items either from the live list or the picked up section, you can only delete the entire list. Why do developers always break what didn't need fixing?
good app. be good as part of tesco effort to make clubcard paperless to have a prompt in the app to turn off paper options like happens in banking app

I don't know what is wrong, but for not the first time I place an order and the day comes when goods suppose to arrive, my order gets back to basket like I was never did checkout. So I have to make another order placement and wait my goods for more time! It's annoying.

I like the app to do my initial order but when I go in to tweak it two days before delivery it won't allow me to get to the payment page so I have to use my old way to make changes. Extremely annoying. Please fix this.
I feel it could be better to navigate some of the other online supermarket apps are more user friendly.

Is currently very glitchy. Screen freezes constantly so have to shut down the app and reload. Luckily it does keep my order you to date. It wasn't always like this so hoping the glitch gets fixed soon.

It took me a while to locate the digital clubcard on here. I took it to customer services instore at Lewes. They couldn't find it. They directed me to the Tesco phoneshop. They couldn't find it either. I rang to 0800 number. What you've got to do is look in the email they send you when you first register, and enter the number. It would help, I suppose, if they told you that in the relevant section in the app.

Pay-in-store needs to have the option to add nicknames to the registered cards like Tesco Pay app had. Also the payments need to be accessed more easily. It takes too many clicks to reach to the payment screen
App is fine but constantly crashes. It's easy to get back to where you were, after fully closing it and restartin, but usually happens 3-5 times per shop.

If purchase in store via app and don't ask for receipt. I've discovered there is no way to see a digital receipt within the app and also no where to see amount spent too. This was a great feature on Pay+ app.

I haven't used the Tesco app for ages as they seem to be a bit pricey on some of their items but that could be with everything going up if it carries on like it's going we will be paying about ¬£7 for a bag of spuds and maybe ¬£4 for a loaf of bread. But just maybe Tesco will try and keep the prices down and help us shoppers we can only hope
App used to be very stable. However over the past two months it crashes frequently....Tesco need to solve this urgently it makes the online shopping experience very difficult to manage.
App has always worked very well but recently it keeps freezing and I have to close it and start again. That happens two or three times while doing my online shop.

The app is fine but the picking and packing is pretty trash they don't always give you the items you pay for and they sub things out that completely ruin meals, for example if I order a taco kit and beef mince they will swap out beef mince for pork mince and then ur taco Tuesday is just ruined, and often when you turn substitutions off you will only get half of ur order which leads me to believe that the app automatically chooses the closest store which is often a small store instead of an extra

Not great as total in basket was over the minimum required to avoid additional minimum order amount. However 1 item wast available which brought total to 14.10 instead of 15. 45. There was no warning that an additional charge was being added. Other than that its a good service
replyContent: Hi Russ, we are sorry about this. Please do contact us on 0800 323 4040 so that we can issue a refund for you

content: Received Notifications for coupons. But when looked for coupons in the app, there isn't any.

Hard to negotiate constantly have to reset sort options no display of update of order nowhere near as good as ordering via web page and checkout page lacks information of order costs disappointed on first use of the app versus online shopping option update 28th March marginal improvements to app versus web page but still having to constantly up date sort option surely it's only necessary to select chosen option once and app automatically selects on pages used?
Recent changes to points have devalued the massively. Beforehand, they were great, now, not sure if it's worth the effort
Usually easy and convenient to use but have had a problem the past 2/3 weeks of the app freezing constantly so having to come out and go back in making it very slow and annoying!
Constantly crashing recently and has meant I've lost my booked time slot for delivery because of it. Very frustrating but the app it's self is easy to use when it wants to work
Hard to navigate,need to go back all the time to look in basket
Taking ages to open instore. Had to go into flight mode today to open it. Ended up missing out on a ¬£12 voucher
This app used to work really well, but recently it's been freezing and I have to kill it and re-open. This once resulted in my updates not saving and not being noticed until I unpacked my shopping!
How come, I can scan and bag my shopping using the Sainsbury's app, the Asda app even the Waitrose app yet Tesco can only release a handset! Come on Tesco, don't get left behind...
whilst ordering from favourites, the list kept auto-refreshing back to the top..... VERY frustrating...easier to order online

Often when removing an item from the basket, it goes back into the basket so you have to double remove and also at times the quantities increase without you noticing. I've before received and been charged for multiple of something when I had only selected one for the basket. Also frustrating that items in the store are not on the app which isn't a stock issue, it doesn't give you the option for items I know to be available in the store.
It won't let me scroll through my favourites. It keep flicking back to the start so I can't select my usual favourites
Kept flicking back to start of favourites wasting a lot of time to get back to where I was browsing.

The app is OK. I personally prefer the old version. The new version is not as easy to see if you've added certain items to the basket. The older version was much clearer. I keep getting a glitch which copies an order I have made into my basket I have to keep deleting all these items from my basket. I also miss the link to the recipes as I liked to look for inspiration for different meals.
replyContent: Hello Ashleigh. Thanks for your feedback. We appreciate all of our customers' comments so thanks for your points around adding items to the basket and recipe links. We're sorry to hear you're experiencing an issue with the basket. Could you please send us an email with some more details so we can investigate for you? Thanks

content: Quite a few counterintuitive interface options which made it a bothersome experience the first few times, and other little frustrations. Changing delivery address appears to be impossible, for example, without cancelling the order and starting again. If you've moved house and forgotten to change this, it will be a problem. But the app does its job I suppose.

I have been using this app for a long time. Mostly it works fine but there are some frustrating features. The favourites list now includes everything you have ever ordered and it's not possible to delete any while you're browsing. So it takes ages to scroll through. If you come away from the screen for a few mins it returns to the top of the list again - more scrolling required! One really useful feature is it tells you on the day exactly when your delivery is likely to arrive.

Since the app has been updated I have had a few problems with it. Twice now I have opened the app to find the shopping basket still full from my last order despite having recieved it. This meant i had to delete everything before I could start my weekly shop. The shopping basket also used to have the option of viewing items side by side so it was easier to see what you had already ordered. This option has now been taken away which is rather frustrating. The old version was much better.
replyContent: Hi Eleanor. Thanks for your feedback. We're really sorry to hear you're experiencing this issue. Our team are aware and are working hard to fix it for our next release. Thanks.

content: The app is one of the best around. There have been some excellent improvements with search and user experience. The biggest issue is the favourites. It's currently a pointless option as it's not as helpful as it could be. I should be able to select my own favourites and very easily un-heart those that are not favourites. I get a lot of my household items from Tesco and it's irritating when I forget essential items because I don't always have time to make a list.

When using my tablet to shop, if I hit the 'back' button when searching through my favourite's or have clicked onto a special offer, it takes me all the way back to the beginning and I have to scroll through everything again to get back to where I was, bit annoying after 6 or more times! apart from that the app is ok, I would like to see the 'search with a list of items' on the app, the same as if you shop from a PC. That would be very handy.

The app has a few bugs which make it annoying to use. The quantity limit, 20,seems to be activated as soon as I add one of an applicable product, seems to have a time delay of a couple of seconds, in which time you can add more than 1. If it claims a product I've selected is no longer available, if I add an alternative I still get both delivered, this always happens with bananas. On the missed promotions screen, if I fulfil the promotion it doesn't register it.
replyContent: Hello. Thanks for your feedback. We're pleased to let you know that we've fixed the issue you were experiencing around the quantity limit has been fixed in the latest build. Thanks for your patience.

content: The app is great for easy shopping with good filters and search options. Downside is when you have ordered the maximum allowed for an item and you check out, it tells you the item is not available and will be removed from trolley, but this is not the case if it is just a max quantity issue and then it stays in trolley. Very confusing indeed. Needs sorting.

Handy app. Except for when it kicks me out and comes up with "something went wrong" whenever I try and get back on. And its inability to let you do loose produce by weight instead of by number (Clearly they -can- do it, since it works for fish/cheese etc). Or when it randomly decided half my favourites aren't favorites any more. Usually incredibly useful. But these are issues I have every single time I try and make an order. ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

A reasonaable app which is usually easy to use. That said, it would be helpful if the items shown after a search, were sorted to show our 'favouties' at the trip of the list. Also, refining a product description by adding descriptive terms can result in many more choices rather than less. This is because the search engine does an 'OR' between words rather than an 'AND'. This can be very frustrating.

Still waiting to be able to delete items from the favourites list in the app ... This is very annoying. Also, if I have to go away from the app to do something else in the middle of shopping, when it returns it jumps back to the start of the favourites list instead of returning to where I was, so I have to scroll a long way down to find my place again. Otherwise good.

Easy to use and does everything the website does, integrates my vouchers so I can apply easily at checkout, booking is simple and easier to view on my phone meaning I can do the shopping whilst on the move. Downsides are that search isn't very intelligent, for certain products I have to type the exact name and no suggested options come up. Favourites list is too long to be useful and the usuals list bears no resemblance to my previous orders... Fixing these would make it a lot more useful.

The latest version of this app has some frustrating features. It is difficult to add a clubcard voucher during. I tapped the screen in the relevant place, it took about 10 attempts before the box appeared for me to input the voucher code. Then it wouldn't let me add a second voucher until I checked out and had to go through the whole process again. It's almost as if Tesco don't want us to spend our vouchers! It needs to be more intuitive. And the constant payment verification is also a huge pain

The reason for 3 stars is that frustratingly, a few updates back I noticed that my basket changes at the point of ordering, which is highly frustrating. So I have items in my basket, which then disappear from my order without any notification that they have, in that second, become unavailable. It is not due to a lag between adding items to my basket and coming back to place the order later. it's then very difficult to look at your order and tell what has been removed. Please fix this!!

Not bad overall, favourites feature is a bit frustrating tho, constantly jumps to top of list and full of adverts and promotions. -- So I wrote the above review in 2018, now in 2020, the favourites feature still jumps to the top of the list when you edit it, doesn't allow you to add items you haven't previously bought and automatically adds items you have bought even if you didn't get them (i.e they were subbed). So, still pretty frustrating.
replyContent: Hi David. Thanks for your feedback. We appreciate all our customers' comments and use them to inform how we improve the app, so thanks for your points around favourites.

content: It's OK, but slots are becoming harder to book. It says repeatedly 'why not try click and collect' - the answer is my head injury and I'm now unable to drive. I fill in the 'notes' on each item (which now needs to be done on each order), but the pickers rarely take any notice; especially on sell by dates. This is more about the service than the app, but the whole experience could be better.

It can be very frustrating at times. Yet again I went to add another slot to my deliveries, but instead, & unbeknown to me, it changed my next slot instead! I was then left with no delivery slot for next week! This isn't the first time it's happened. Plus you have to navigate through a lot of screens to make alterations & as stated above, sometimes it just does its own thing, & you don't find out until it's too late.

It's ok. Search is a bit clunky. Filters are a bit short sighted. Could make adding to order a bit smoother. Does the job and saves a visit to the shop but only average compared to other shopping apps. Edit, gets really annoying being asked to rate the app every time I use it. This is a basic mapping issue. Please just fix it.

Favourites list frequently goes back to the beginning, meaning I have to scroll through everything again. No ability to remove items from favourites list. No option under dietary requirements to search for nut free items. And the new extra security at checkout is tedious, especially when making changes. But still better than fighting my way around the supermarket!

Overall, I like the app, but the favourites feature makes my eyeballs bleed. Everything, I've ever bought, both in store and online appears on my favourites list... even if I hated it. It's easier to start fresh then try to search through my favourites. And the usual list isn't much better. It would be better to allow customers to be able to create our own saved shopping lists within the app.

The app is useful for booking grocery deliveries, but could be much better with a little thought. I suspect the app creators do not use the app for their own regular shopping, or they would have changed several frustrating features. If they want to get in touch, I would be happy to suggest some simple changes that would improve user experience, and save time for regular users each time they order.

The app is great apart from that you have to click through loads of screens (5? 6?)every time you amend your order. It didn't used to be like this. I shop by adding things as I think of them during the week, often one thing at a time, so it's really annoying to have to wade through loads of promo screens and then enter your security code every single time I add something. It's often made me think of switching supermarket, the result being that often i just don't bother adding stuff to my order.

Not great functionality. On this app, you can't do all the things that you can do on the web page, for example you can't select a "substitute all" option for your shop, instead having to tick every item. This is irritating, as it means I have to go on the Web page every order, to select it. It also doesn't allow you to edit your favourites list, or look at "rest of shelf" for items.

Really easy to use and if you have a club card then the favourites options saves searching. A few issues with app offers, several times I've had to ring to get them added as it doesn't accept the code. And I'm puzzled as to why if I buy a product once, it is added to my favourites. Surely trying a product out once is not a favourite. So regularly I have to go to the tesco website on a browser and filter out something I tried and never want to buy again. But on the whole it's easy to use.

App keeps freezing since latest update. Get about 2-3 mins before it freezes and I have to reopen. On content, it is incredibly frustrating not having full product information (eg ingredients!) on mobile app. Have to go and double check things on we version which just makes the process tedious. Also, not being able to group items by type in basket makes it hard yo check what you have/missed eg in freezer section.
App keeps crashing and won't let u press anything

Edited to update, not sure whats been going wrong lately, but after adding items to order and checking out again, its not updating the order, and thus the previous order comes but not the updated order. Its getting very frustrating! Previous review: Clear, concise and to the point. This app is easy to use, great search, quick to add favorites. makes the food shop quick and painless.
Poor design. When password needs to be reset, cookie popup repeatedly obscures 90% of page area required to enter and confirm new password

Buggy but gets it done (mostly). If you take something out of the basket from a search results screen, or decrease quantity, it'll appear like it's done on that screen, but it's usually not actually removed it from your basket. Have to check the basket really carefully before checkout each time. I'd also like to sort by 'price per' low to high. And have improved milk free filters for everything that's milk free, not just specific 'free from' products. Also, please add yeast free as a filter.

Much more convenient than logging in on a laptop to make changes. Generally ok but some irritations To book a slot you have to process a full shop. This is really irritating now that slots are less available and you need to book multiple weeks in advance. When you make changes to the order they don't take effect until you have completed the checkout again. Checkout is multiple screens and it's too easy to accidentally miss one, resulting in none of the changes being processed.

It's fine most of the time but it freezes and won't allow you to update basket. It's irritating that in the app you have to physically check a box to allow substitutions for every single item. And it's extremely annoying when it tells you an item isn't available, so you select an alternative and then have the original item plus the alternative delivered

The app is ok but that's it. It loads back to the top of the list even when you're near the bottom if your screen closes. You can't easily adjust your favourites like clicking on the heart icon to remove them. Stuff that was ceased being sold months (and sometimes years) ago is still being brought up on the screen even when I've selected the alternative. The fact you can select a delivery/c&c slot even when you haven't got time to complete your shop is crazy It needs tweaking to be user friendly

Really useful in many ways. Rarely crashes. Agree with others that 'favourites' should be editable as things we 'try' go on there as well as substitutions that we get! Also think it'd be helpful to either remove the 95 item limit (!!) or allow a subs list, as well as not removing items when editing. If I edit my Dec 4 order on Nov 20th and store doesn't have, say, shampoo that day, that means it's removed from my basket completely. If I want to re-add it days later, I risk losing something else!
Too many new ads in search screens.
Seem to be having the same issues as others... App crashes unexpectedly and a good few times while trying to do shopping, a little frustrating! Using Google Pixal 6pro
Updated to say this now crashes every 30 seconds or so. Really difficult to get an order through. Very frustrating as otherwise is a good app
Problematic to say the least crashed at till wouldn't let me use my big shop. The old app worked much better

Its OK for buying shopping but the favourites are very frustrating. Everything you've ever bought goes into favourites so I have to go through what I bought at Easter and Christmas everytime and usuals only has half of the stuff I normally buy. Also, when you go out of the app to look at ingredients, when I go back in, it's gone back to the top of the favourites list and it takes ages to get back to where I was. It doesn't let you change your substitute options you have to opt in everytime.

The app works really well...except for one thing: when I'm searching for items to buy, the search results are too limited. If I make a search via Tesco's website, invariably the results will contain many more products related to what I originally searched for. I'm becoming more and more frustrated by this issue and, as a result, I am using the app less and less. I'm sure Tesco's would make much more money (not that they need to) if they fixed this.

The app is OK for most things but a major drawback is that you need a data connection to use the clubcard. It should be stored locally on the device because there are a lot of times depending on signal quality on store where it won't load. A real disappointment considering I never had issues with the clubcard app when it was available.

Good experience adding goods to the basket and finding products. But during COVID19 it shouldn't allow you to add more than 95 products to the basket. It was a total waste of time doing the shopping and then having to amend the order. It's also a bit frustrating not being able to save products in a list or your favourites for future searches. It only adds products to your favourites after you buy them. If you have to find the products you didnt buy due to restrictions you have to start from 0

Overall the app is fairly good and easy to navigate. My reason for marking it down is that in the favorites section, under usual, it lists items that you have ordered maybe once or twice and misses things out of the list that we order every week, like milk, bread, sandwich filling. There is that much missing from my weekly list that there isn't much point having the usual section.

App is easy to navigate and search for things. It does have a lot of problems such as the "browse groceries" section wont work unless I choose to edit an order first. Not good if I only wanted to browse items. It always says "oops something went wrong" when trying to complete my payment for my order, it usually take 2-3 attempts, then crashes totally, but when I reload the app after its crashed I can see my order did process okay. So there are a few bugs that need fixed before I gove 5 stars.

It's ok but missing some handy functions. The notes function for subs is great but having to put the note on each week is a pain. It used to save the note so you didn't have to add it every time but now I have to go through items every shop to record my notes. Also, it would be far better if when the shopping had been picked an email was sent advising of subs and missing items so that prior to the delivery arrival you can decide what you're keeping. Could be less clunky to use as well.

Great app, just wish the the new payment wallet actually allowed you to save more than one payment method. My husband and i both do shopping and with the extra security with needing to get a text message and add a code everytime we want to add an item to our shopping basket (we do this as we go). We want to tear our hair out. I'm actually considering going back to Sainsbury's.

App isn't as good as it could be. There are flaws in it, one being that it keeps doubling up on your order and asking you to book a slot even though you've already booked one but the items remain in your basket until you empty it!!! Also you keep having to remember to tick substitute box if you wish and add your note on every order (very annoying when you forget) where as before your substitute preferences were there everytime. Having to checkout every time you add to order is a pain!!!

Using version 19.41.0, the app keeps locking up on my Chromebook (Android 9), while scrolling through my basket. I can only force-close the app, which leaves me wondering whether the updates have been saved. Luckily, I was able to get into the app on my tablet (Android 7), and complete the order. Hope this can be sorted soon - I'd sooner use the app than the website.

Mostly good app. Improvements that could be made : * option to unfavourite things by pressing the blue heart. There's things that I don't buy any more (like alcohol) but I see them every time and it clogs up my buying experience * sometimes if I have to check another app when I get back to Tescos app the list resets and it takes ages to scroll through all the items again. It'd be great if it just stayed in that place. Thanks
Recently the app repeatedly freezes which is very irritating especially when trying to verify payment, waiting for a text, which comes but then can't be used as the app has frozen

Logs out all the time The app itself is great but, pretty much every time I try to use it at the checkout, it's logged me out. I have to log in again whilst everyone waits behind me. Logging in is made as difficult as possible by the developers: they have suppressed the use of saved passwords (Android), and even when one has found the password and entered it, they require a verification code. All of this is made difficult by the fact that my store's structure seems to block out mobile internet.
Make payments in store with what was the pay +. But now there is no way to see paymemt history, as there was with the pay+ app. Also more things to press just to get to the payment. Takes longer.

Used the PayPlus app with no problems.Worked offline ok. Now having to use the all in one app but this will only work if I'm online. Clicking on Pay In Store just brings up a message telling me I'm offline.

They really need to fix the glitch whereby you go back to change your basket and a load of stuff already in your order becomes unavailable! This issue is still not fixed almost eight months later. Most of the time the stuff comes anyway - but sometimes this means getting doubles as you've added a replacement or being without the item(s).
replyContent: Hi Ian. Thanks for your feedback. We're really sorry to hear you're experiencing this issue. Our team are aware of this issue and are working hard to fix it. We hope to have this resolved in our next release. Thanks.

content: Most annoying thing that I've only just realised it does is remove items from your shop after you've checked out without offering a replacement (presumably when they go out of stock). This means things you really need (like toilet paper!) just don't get delivered and there's no notification of this (unlike if they're out of stock on the day when replacements are offered). This is totally unacceptable and has meant I've had to go out and buy them separately defeating the point of home delivery!

The favourites tab is a better alternative to searching for items but it gets clogged up with every item you've ever ordered. It would be better to only contain items your buy frequently. Even better would be for customer to create a "default basket" that you could load up at start of shop in one go, then add and extra items and delete unwanted items. This would save a lot of items

Can be difficult to navigate. It can be difficult to see what day you are booking for as the date and times do not line up. I accidentally booked a collection rather than a delivery and had to go to the website to work out how to cancel it. You can't search with a list which takes ages going back to the search for each item. I will delete this app and just use the website in the future, much clearer even on a phone.
Easy enough to use. The swaps when an item isn't available is rubbish

2 vital things missing: 1) the ability to un-favourite items on the list. I don't want my in-store lunch purchases and discontinued items cluttering up my Favourites list indefinitely when making an order. 2) when I go into a different app (such as looking at a photo of my fridge shopping list!) the app favourites list jumps back to the top and needs to reload several scrolls. Infuriating.
Always have to authenticate my clubcard every time I use the app which is annoying as I installed it to use when I dont have my clubcard to hand.
This app does not give you near matches if you make a spelling mistake, not good for me who HAS dyslexia .
I'm not sure on my phone how I find how to look up items you've bought and to find where you put if you'd like substitutes or not.I can do this on my laptop but not on my android phone.
Ordering page is different and harder to use. Change is no good for thr sake of it.

The app overall is good. But there is a very annoying issue with it. When I am shopping my favourite list and if I am being interrupted when I am, let's say, in the middle of the list and I need to close my screen, when I go back into the app it takes me back to the beginning of the favourite list all the time.
Ok but no digital receipt function. Needs to work harder to match the Lidl app
Needs improvement. Doesn't place products in price order nor bring up only the products requested.
Can be glitchy when trying to pay & trying to scroll through favourites

Edit August 2021: I can't see any improvement since my last review. All the same problems, takes so much longer than it needs to! See below my previous review: 'I find it annoying how you can't opt to go to a particular food category within your favourites list. Also favourites jump back to the beginning when you're still shopping and you have to scroll through the whole list again.'
Can't see "rest of shelf" which was always useful.

It's broadly OK, but it could be improved. If a common item eg milk is unavailable, the app won't let you order it, despite the fact it will most likely be available on the day. It would be better if the app just warned you. Sometimes an item will appear in the basket ok, but the basket will not save. The message is just an unhelpful 'something has gone wrong'. Experience shows that if you painstakingly go through removing items one at a time, this can be corrected, but it is tedious.

App works ok, never crashes and is fast but I can only see two items on the screen at any one time when scrolling through a list so difficult to compare items. I never had that issue with the old App. My phone has a 5 inch screen. Could do with making more screen available for items.

Works well to a point but I still have to use the website as well. Substitutions are turned off by default on my app with no option to tick for all so have to tick individual items, so I start the shop on the website where I can tick it and use the app for adding items later. I would also like to have the option to view rest of Isle, so prefer using the website for that reason. Its usable, works OK but needs improvements.
Pleased with Tesco overall but find using the app on my mobile difficult.

Easy to use. One very annoying thing is that offers (in yellow background) are not readable on mobile. They show only the first few words. Meal deal: ¬£8 for .... And it's not possible to know what's needed to match the deal. Favourites are automatically added as we shop, but it's a real pain to remove them once added.
Can't find 'Rest of Shelf' against each item, which is really useful, but annoying that it doesn't seem to show up üòï
Very confusing.
Not as intuitive in my opinion as ordering through the website
often have issues viewing previous deliveries, and no user ratings for products are available. the range is better at Ocado but Tesco is cheaper.

I would have rated this a 5 star, but I do not understand why Tesco charges ¬£5 fir orders under ¬£50. It just sounds like a wicked rip-off! Considering the fact that everyone is literally struggling to live, you're not even encouraged to send a surprise shopping to your loved ones without Tesco making you pay more than budgeted. Why create online shopping via the app if it's not to help customers. I think it's just a way to make extra money from customers. Why compel us to shop more?
Buggy, often gets through the whole payment and get message confirming all went through ok. Only to find next day the app had an error and you have no delivery.
Was 5 star but latest update added a very annoying and useless set of click boxes that keep popping up in the middle of lists.
First time so will change rating if everything is there and experienced
Changed from 5* to 3*,they removed viewing ratings on products from the app, makes it harder to see what products are great, and awful
Good
It's not customer friendly enough, try and select 3 meal deals, no prompts and pretty sure I missed one snack, which I struggled to find, make it more simple or you could be seen as misleading
Confusing
Took longer to shop have to get used to new app, will probable be üëç
Please return to former method of ordering. The new method is horrendous
Confusing and not as intuitive as the older version. If it ain't broke, don't fix it.
Hard to navigate,need to go back all the time to look in basket
Taking ages to open instore. Had to go into flight mode today to open it. Ended up missing out on a ¬£12 voucher
NM Been mmn lol khud hn hn NM üòåüßÅü§©üéâ
Often breaks down / freezes
To many basic things like oxo cubes are unavailable I ordered 37 items but 20 of them were unavailable but I am happy with using the larger store and I get most of what I ordered
App keeps crashing and won't let u press anything
There are no longer any reviews. Why not?
Still glitches at checkout.
Not happy, old website was much easier to use
Ok but no digital receipt function. Needs to work harder to match the Lidl app
Needs the ability to clear all favourites considering these were generated on my behalf and removing all 340 of them will take all night. Also lacks the "Rest of Shelf" option that the website has.
Orders paid for but not processed if placed over a weekend for a weekeday, not great
Easy to use, useful to add items as you go
Half your groceries I still have difficulties finding what I want but it still cost me a lot more . The one thing that I really like is you have great staff they are brilliant.
really good

Often not working correctly. Scrolling through favourites list and it jumps back to the top. Today it only showed maybe less than a quarter of favourites. Frustrating enough for me, I have to wonder how people that really rely on the app cope with it.
Can't see "rest of shelf" which was always useful.
The shopping items go to the top every time the phone is in standby. Very annoying
Ordering page is different and harder to use. Change is no good for thr sake of it.
Too many new ads in search screens.

I cannot press on anything besides the bottom menu. It worked perfectly fine for months then all of a sudden it stopped working properly. I tried reinstalling the app and resetting my phone, but nothing seems to work
Pleased with Tesco overall but find using the app on my mobile difficult.

My experience has been good APART FROM the seemingly harmless invitation to store one's bank details/password right at the end after paying, when an inexperienced shopper might not realise the risk, or a shopper ticks that box by mistake. It says "Would you like to store your bank details in our wallet?" This invitation box left in place makes me want to change supermarkets, because its a risk for any person who does. I have heard of several people who have lost savings because they got hacked.
No place to use a gift card
Can be glitchy when trying to pay & trying to scroll through favourites

App is easy to use, but there are a lot of products sold in store that are not on here. My nearest Tesco superstore is just not easy for me to get to, so I then end up having to go to my local Asda for the items I can't buy from the app.
I like having all the functionality in one app but I can rarely get the payment bar code to scan. It took about 15 attempts today to get clubcard plus bar code to scan.
Irritating to the max
I'm not sure on my phone how I find how to look up items you've bought and to find where you put if you'd like substitutes or not.I can do this on my laptop but not on my android phone.
It's good, and convenient, but for some reason, they have the marker on the map wrong for my address, and I have no idea how to fix it, otherwise I would have rated higher
Needs improvement. Doesn't place products in price order nor bring up only the products requested.

Pretty hopeless for me. I live within 200m if a Tesco and am able bodied so I never have home delivery. I always order for my parents who are in their 90s 150 miles from me. It would be better if it started with who are you ordering for or could set a default address other than your own.
Easy enough to use. The swaps when an item isn't available is rubbish

The app is more secure than my bank, requiring a text code to verify my identity before I can access my Clubcard vouchers every time. Less than ideal at the checkout! The entire app seems to be needlessly faffy and difficult to use.
Favourites list keeps "jumping" back to the top

Often when removing an item from the basket, it goes back into the basket so you have to double remove and also at times the quantities increase without you noticing. I've before received and been charged for multiple of something when I had only selected one for the basket. Also frustrating that items in the store are not on the app which isn't a stock issue, it doesn't give you the option for items I know to be available in the store.
Doesn't show customer's reviews on the app!

I agree with some of the other commitments‚ÅâÔ∏è regarding the error's from tesco)(I have also been using them since covid) and(things are not going good on there app)(just hope they get it sorted some how)(but they are still my favourite)üëçüÜó next to Asda)(as they work very hard to make sure we got our grosery)(when covidüó£Ô∏èwas very bad)(so we shouldn't put them downüëáto much)üôàüôâüôäthanksü§ó

The application is not that much usefull. It is still faster to use the key fob. I was unable to display my card number because of connection problem. I lost all the discounts on that transaction and tesco points.I decided to go off line but it is not possible to take the screenshot of the card because of "security reasons". It is possible to take a picture of the card and use it. Where is the logic? Card number/QR code should be available off line. Unlocked phone is security check itself.

Quite good but not 100√ó/per sent as one year lost all vouchers to someone else who I did not know untill I found I lost my card and someone else used them and told I did it my self with what they said should be I ended up with just ¬£2-50 and told tough Mr Ken Spires
Missing the option to set an alarm when the delivery is imminent. Also, the option to save multiple payment methods.
5th July ‚Å∂a65

Annoying thing is the offers are sometimes too long to fit on the screen so I don't know what the offer is. IE pizza company meal deal buy 1 pizza 1 sid........ that's all I can see and it doesn't give any more than that.
How come, I can scan and bag my shopping using the Sainsbury's app, the Asda app even the Waitrose app yet Tesco can only release a handset! Come on Tesco, don't get left behind...
Never get coupons like I used to and yes I am opted in. So disappointed
Recent changes to points have devalued the massively. Beforehand, they were great, now, not sure if it's worth the effort
Always have to authenticate my clubcard every time I use the app which is annoying as I installed it to use when I dont have my clubcard to hand.

replyContent: Hello Matt, thank you for your feedback. Can you please log out, log back in and then try to add your card again? These steps have helped other customers with a similar problem. If no joy, then please contact our Customer Services team on 0330 123 0250 (opening hours - Mon-Sat 8am-8pm, Sun 9am-6pm) and they'll be able to assist from there.
