I shop using favourites. It's great your vouchers are there now so easier to use. But if you come out to answer a call or message it takes you back to the beginning of the list as there are no pages you have to scroll through it all to find where you were.

I like the app, it works well it wants to. I like the option to shop inshore and see stock levels, but I wish that it was possible to use the favourites list that is available at a touch when ordering delivery or click and collect whilst using the shop instore feature

It has improved and I like the previous order capability. It's the search that drives me insane. I searched nivea deodorant and it gave me sweet and sour chicken ready meals plus another 25 meal deal offers! Apart from the glitch it's pretty good.
Has improved over the last year. Pretty easy to use. Has occasions where you think it had saved changes and it hasn't.
Tesco app. It's a great app. Works well in a harsh environment. But, I think adding a new item to an existing list could be easier. Otherwise, it's great, many thanks.
Generally good. A bit jumpy when going through favourites list and kept going back to the start. Easy to make an order.
As shopping apps go it's not too bad. Would be better if it included the full range of products like clothing & homeware.

always has been good and easy to find items until the last couple of weeks now totally annoying as it keeps going back to top of list of favourites they tell me they know and are fixing it ASAP so let's hope its soon
Booked my slot and went to checkout in only 10 minutes and got a message saying my slot had expired. I couldn't get another slot until the nest day. I wasn't happy.
Its a good app, but harder to navigate than competitors. Easy booking for time slots.
Used to be good. Not any more. I find it very difficult to look through my favourites because it keeps scrolling back to the top. And I can't see all of the products on my list.
I can't find how to delete items in my favourites list. There use to be an x in top right hand corner of each item now there is a heart.
Good app, easy to navigate, good search facility. Sorting favourites can be a pain.
Fairly good but lacking on the user interface. Not a patch on the web site with a PC or tablet.
On my favourites list while shopping it kept scrolling back to the top, very annoying! Also why are things I've bought ONCE appearing on my favourites??

It is a great app. Pros: Saves me a lot of time shopping. Well designed and highly usable. Cons: sometimes crushes and need to restart the app. Feature request: Have sort functionality on price per gram instead of just total price of item.

Fine but no list function? Would very much like to create an instant basket for several situations, e.g.: camping food, or Christmas food etc, but no way to put one together and save? Considering choosing an alternative app to have this essential function. Otherwise it works well enough.

Generally really good. Easy to use and has up to date info on stock. It's rare to get subs or unavailable items when you receive your shopping because of this. It's a shame you can't remove favourites on the app. Apart from that, it's great.

+1 star for having the option of defaulting to in-store or online shopping. However, the Pay in store option is frustratingly hidden from view until you scroll down. Five stars if you make better use of the UI to have it all on one screen. Doesn't really need the big clubcard taking up a third does it..? üôÑ
replyContent: Hello Graham, thank you for your feedback. The Pay in-store button will be fixed in the next release, so that you won't need to scroll down to find it. Please watch out for future releases as we continuously update the app to make online and in-store shopping quicker and more convenient than ever

content: Quite good pleased with service. Except I always have job finding Tesco strawberry jam victoria sandwich ! I do eventually find then they are unavailable ,!
Tried ordering from previous order and nearly ended up with a double order. Had to do it from scratch.

It sure is a better and quicker alternative to shopping via the website and using a laptop which I always preferred. The only thing I missed was 'Rest of Shelf' - except maybe I didn't discover where it was.

This app is great and much more convenient then logging in online, however it does crash quite a lot this causes me to have to close and open the app a few times while completing my shopping, but other than that it is great and really easy to navigate and use.

Currently unable to walk so this app is a lifesaver, only problem is not everything is available online that they have instore. Remembers everything I've ever bought which is great and reminds me of staples I may have forgotten from previous orders which is a great help as my memory isn't always that good. Love that you can use your vouchers too if you want. All in all I give this app a thumbs up üëç
Different. Took time to get used to. Be easier when entering the app for those who find it difficult to use.
Easy to navigate and amendable until day before expected delivery A bit more expensive than some online shopping platforms but food is always fresh with long sell by dates

Used for years. Rarely an issue. Only thing that's annoying, is it takes six clicks to check out. 'You may want these, oh are you sure you aren't missing this offer, what about these' - you get the picture. Tedious when you add to basket all week like I do. You almost don't want to add that pint of milk..

The app is great, but the stock checker is rather usually inaccurate to what's in-store. Would be nice if you could see both in-store stock and what's available on the shelf. Also needs to update more regularly as some products are displayed as in stock but aren't available.

Just tried using this to pay in store, doesn't work. The online help says: Just open the Tesco Grocery & Clubcard app, select 'Shop in-store' and then select 'Pay in-store'. Not there, there is no 'Pay in-store' to select. Four assistants could not make it work either. Bring back Tesco Pay+. Update: 4/3/23 the app presented a promotion notice 'add pay facility'. I clicked on that, it prompted for a PIN code and the 'Pay in store' button appeared! Why didn't you inform people it was 'Coming soon'
Great, easy and convenient, only reason I've not given 5 stars is the dates on food delivered is pretty poor.
Previous version excellent, current one still a bit fussy and can't get my credit card QR code to fill. NOW WORKING WELL

Not as good as the previous app when it comes to using the Clubcard, vouchers are difficult to find and not as simple as the previous app, Why can't the Clubcard be on the main page/home screen as it is used more often.
Overall good. App is slow sometimes but on a whole I think it's improving well üòä
Need to delete old delivery address, but so far been unable to? Otherwise fairly old lady friendly!
Great and useful app. Thank everyone working for tesco customers. Well done. We can all do better, let's do it.
Generally works fine, hopefully this update fixes the favourites list jumping all over the shop.
Easy to use and great if u r looking to save points or just browsing for products. Great app for all
It asks you to physically deposit an electronic voucher, lol. Everything else works fine.

When trying to end purchase adverts popping up after coming back to site. Have to start payment from beginning again, happened twice. Very frustrating üò§ logging to bank and back 3 times to end transaction.

Very easy to install. Found login details from existing clubcard app on phone so didn't have to try remembering my password. Haven't used so far but my points and vouchers have appeared in the new app no problem.
Pretty good, annoying that they ramp up the prices on woosh A LOT considering the delivery fee but very quick.

Great app that's really convenient and massively improved. It would be good if clubcard points were not in a separate app. It would also be good if you had the option to add your regular items straight to your basket. I don't think the favourites feature is particularly intuitive at the moment. I like being able to amend the order and you can usually get a delivery slot the next day. It would also be good if you could search within your basket. I find the app responsive (used to be so slow!).

Been using this for years and it works fine. the new updates seem a little more intuitive and I haven't noticed any functionality issues. Now and again we have issues with products we use all the time being unavailable, even though you could go to the store and get the items off the shelves but I don't think it's the app that's the problem there (seems to be the same online).

Easy to use and fast. I didn't shop at tesco for a few years and coming back to it I notice the new app is much better than the version I used to use. It keeps track of where you are on your favourites when tapping in and out of different products. It makes ordering easy. The only negative I have noticed is that a couple of times I have booked a delivery/collection slot and begun loading the basket but when I come to pay, the slot is no longer booked. A bug somewhere.

So much better than the website. Once you have used it a few times, the favourites list is great for saving time. The search results are sometimes not quite right but you just need to try different wording. Frustrating that you can't see availability for a week that you already have a slot in, so if you want to change the slot you have to go into the order first.

Works well, had no major issues with it. One big flaw and that is that the items are shown the same as they are added to basket. There's no separation of the different types of food like asda's basket. Would be much easier to flick through and see what you have and don't have if it was set out better. There is also an error at times when your adding things into your basket and it doesn't let you know if it's out of stock until the end. 95 item limit is frustrating also as a family of 4.

It works. But it could be a bit more intuitive when you go back to check your entire order , after having made subsequent additions. Also when you want to pre-book a series of different delivery slots: it's easy to accidentally reschedule your next-up delivery slot when you don't want to, mistakenly believing you're booking an extra one. For these reasons I haven't learned to trust it yet.

Really easy to use doing shopping but there can be so many screens at checkout that you can think you've finished when you haven't. Which can be very inconvenient the last time you use it before the cut-off. Recently, my app is showing past deliveries at the top of the screen and when I open the latest delivery, it shows the contents of the basket but with the 'Add' button rather than the quantity. I then have to add something and choose the already-selected delivery to recover the basket

I am in my '70's and disabled, so this App is perfect for me. There are three issues, it is hard to pick out the real instore bargains, sometimes when they are out of a product they replace with a like item which is not always good, some of the fresh produce is not always up to the best quality, in store you can select a better item or avoid it completely. The App requires a comments section so you can say things like, If you are out of item ######' replace it with XXXX. Overall a great App.

This app works quite well. I've used worse. The only thing is that occasionally I believe I have removed an item and it has reappeared in my shopping but it was hard to tell what had happened. It would help if your order history was kept longer. I could not get a slot for 6 months (pandemic) and so went to another shop. When I restarted, my orders were too old to appear on the app even though I've shopped with tesco for ages. Didn't think of trying doing it on the website. Did it from fresh!

It is generally a good app and has improved slightly recently and looks more modern but would be good to see the following: 1. Ability to sort your basket into groups (fridge, freezer, food cupboard, toiletries etc). When you're scrolling up and down the whole list it can be hard to check everything we want has been added. 2. Receive the receipt and substitutions by email instead of printed off. Can't understand why it's printed. Ocado and and Iceland both email. Thanks

Largely idiot-proof way to order shopping. Easy on the eye. Easy to double-check. I like that vouchers are displayed and easy to use in-app. I would like to see it generate an update after the completion deadline. New: Also good that you now have the option of populating a new list with ALL your favourites. A real time saver; quicker to delete items than find them and add them.

It's ok, certainly better than some online shopping but they keep changing things which is particularly confusing for older users. Viewing which orders you have is tricky at times and how on earth you control lists and favourites is a mystery! Having said all this, it's been a life saver recently and after a bumpy start Tesco have been remarkable at stepping up to the challenge during these tough times.

I do like this app and find it one of the best for online shopping. It's easy to use and I would definitely recommend it. My only negatives: 1. If you're scrolling through your favourites and then leave the app for even a split second, mine sends me right back to the top of the list which can be frustrating. 2. It used to have an option for selecting a particular type of offer e.g. ¬£1 items or 2 for 1 deals. Now it just shows 'top offers' or 'all offers' which makes finding offers difficult.

MUCH better than the website. That thing gives me a headache. The only downsides I can see so far are that you can't "see the rest of shelf" which was handy for packed lunch foods and I don't think you can make a shopping list without booking a slot. (But this isn't SO bad since you can book multiple slots!) Delivery updates could do with a tweak...maybe being replaced with a van tracker? But it's fine.

Pretty easy to use, only thing that I think could be better, is when you have a brand of something on sale with different variants, it would be good if you could click on an item where it says what the offer is and see what else in that range is on offer too rather than having to search for it separately. Oh and be able to rate the products would be good too.

Really handy way of ordering, easy to use and usually flawless. There have been a few times it won't save changes, which is why I have given it 4‚òÖ, not more - but this is rare. Recently they have changed it so you have to enter your security number (last 3 digits of card) in EVERY time you add something. A little bit annoying, but not the end of the world. Would recommend.

I quite like it and it is constantly improving, although I would prefer more filtering options. For example, I order unsliced bread for my mum, and it takes a while to go through what bread is available, whereas filtering it would make it much quicker and easier. I would also like to be able to sort in order of, e.g. fat content, which I haven't found to be available.

One of the better supermarket shopping apps. The search is a bit naff as it will bring up results that have absolutely nothing to do with what you have searched for. Also, it is annoying when it takes you right back to the beginning of your favourites list if the screen goes to sleep or you delete an item(s), otherwise it might have got 5 stars.

I've been using this app for a couple of years. I find it easy and fairly quick. You can add previous orders to basket to speed up starting a new shop. Vouchers sent by post also show on the checkout page, it's simple to select the valid ones with a tick box. Useful to be able to store other addresses, especially if you're shopping for vulnerable people but you need to select their address before booking a slot as availability might change if they're come under jurisdiction of another depot.

We've been using the app for a few years and it's the best way to online shop, I can easily book slots and add just one or two bits to my basket to secure the delivery, then go back in as frequently as I like to add things as I think of them. I would have rated a 5 but the recent update whereby I have to put my card security code in every time I change the order is really annoying as it adds so many more clicks onto the process.

Easy to use for the most part. Favourites list can be frustrating as everything I've ever ordered ends up on it rather than things I've specifically selected as a favourite so every so often I have to go through and remove the one off purchases or duplicates that appear when an old product size is discontinued and replaced. Like that I can keep checking in on the status of products in my basket to see if anything had gone out of stock so I can chose the replacement.

In summary a good app, relatively easy to use, but some things could be slicker. Tesco delivery drivers are always happy and friendly. Niggles: The checkout process has a few too many steps. It's fine for a main check out, in fact I like the offers and things I might have forgotten. But when I'm adding just *one* item, it's irritating. The items no longer in stock is inconsistent, items often are still in stock!? Favourites is handy, but keeping the list pruned is time consuming.

Easy to use, it is a good app, but there is the odd bug - for example the current version doesnt allow me to scan items with my camera (using S9+). In regards to shopping (so I didnt score the app down for it) there are hefty restrictions on products, could be due to Covid to be fair, but frustrating that it is difficult to buy basics like eggs and flour... then walk into the shop to see full shelves. There are also a lot of items missing which I would hope by now would start to reappear.

Easy to shop with! I have been using the app for years now and very pleased to see how it changed. Very easy to navigate. All offers are displayed with a date on it, so you know until which date you can get the product at discounted price. Now you can add your coupon directly to basket, no need to type code ! Easy! The only negative, is that sometimes you put items in your basket, but by the time your basket is due for delivery, some of those items might be unavailable...so check carefully!
Easy to use and quick
Whoosh is great for someone like me that is housebound and only needs a few bits. I do wish it would let me purchase things like milkshake etc...

I've been using this for a few years now. Really happy with most of the changes they've made, such as delivery updates on the day, very accurate driver tracking, etc. I wish they'd add the option to add/remove things from your favourites list! And I miss being able to see stock levels on my order summary before committing to the "make changes" button. But overall, it's a very easy to use, clear, and well laid out app, which offers a very quick simple shopping experience. Thank you!

So easy to use, well laid out and clear. Only thing that's a bit confusing is that if you're a Delivery Saver subscriber, when you book your slot for delivery or Click and Collect, it will still show a price in the slot, but once you've booked it, on your order it will show delivery/Click and Collect as ¬£0.00, so you're not getting charged for it.

I've used this app without any issues for a couple of years, and it's been a joy... until the last week or so. It was great when I first started to use it but this last month it started to cut off mid order not just once but several times per order. Apart from that all is good. Since writing the above review, the previous problems have all disappeared. Great app. Thank you.

App easy to use and you don't have to copy and paste the clubcard voucher codes at checkout. Once you pass the verification process the app allows you to just apply each individual voucher, which are automatically deducted from the total basket value. Easy!

Easy to use with its simple format. I would like to see a favourites button next to an item so I can come back to something in the future and purchase. At the moment your favourites list only shows what you've bought in the past. Apart from that it's a very good grocery app.
Tescos app is very reliable. A amassive change from before. Delivery drivers are always very friendly and helpful, and the shopping is more often than not, packed really nicely.

Brilliant easy to use. I use it all the time it is also easier to add to your shopping if something is forgotten. Also if you run out of certain items eaay to get.Delivery is good carry your shopping in and have been helped to unpack as I have trouble standing and moving about.

I'm relieved to have home delivery with Tesco and the app too, it's got all my favourites on it and it reminds me about my usual basics like bread if I forget. My Clubcard update prompt led me to my online shopping account - so I placed next week's order. If Tesco & customers keep treating their staff, drivers & suppliers with respect, quality products, good pay/conditions, they could be Number One! ‚ò∫Ô∏è Can't always find my list to remove items though. Easy to use .I am an elderly lady who finds on line quite difficult to do but I had no trouble with this even able to cancel and add other items not needed this week exchanged for items I do need. A great easy way to do a big grocery shop. I have problems walking so this is ideal plus I can relax & take my time to make sure I've ordered everything I need. App is really useful. You can order from anywhere you can get a signal/find WiFi, so I have ordered whilst camping before! Ordering is easy, and made even easier as it remembers your favourite items and reminds you of things that you might have forgotten.

I have used Tesco home delivery for years now. Always friendly. Always punctual. The substitution items are always good on the rare occasion they do not have what I ordered, and on the odd occasion I have had the need to deal with customer service, they are also friendly, professional and have never failed to sort any issue. I cannot fault their products, staff or service. Clubcard points are an additional bonus too!

Brilliant, love doing my shopping from home and the app is so easy to use. I have shopped in different stores via their apps. This one is by far the best and their customer service is atleast in the same country, handles everything with ease and second to none. Excellent all round.
